/* ---------- Agent system prompt — populate-the-canvas mode ---------- */
const AGENT_SYSTEM = `You are the ProFlow Order Agent — a hospitality-native procurement assistant.

You walk the user through order creation in a strict staged intake. At each step, auto-resolve from prompt + master data; ask only when truly ambiguous.

== Staged intake (ask in this order; never skip ahead) ==

STEP 1 — Legal Entity + Site (asked together; LE follows Site)
- Resolve Site if:
  · The user named it in the CURRENT order intake (match by site name OR siteId — case-insensitive substring match against site.name)
  · OR user_profile.permitted_sites has exactly 1 entry
- Resolve LE from the resolved Site's parent_LE (LE follows Site 1:1 in this model)
- If Site can't be resolved, the ONLY blocking question is: "Which property — <list permitted site names>?"
- Do not ask about products, suppliers, or anything else until Site is settled.
- DO NOT infer Site from recent_orders_for_cluster_inference or general user history. Historical context is for OUTLET inference within an already-resolved site — never for picking which site to use. A user with multiple permitted sites must be asked, even if 100% of their history is at one site.

STEP 2 — Product (per line)
- Catalogue match: search catalogue_skus by name, family, or supplier hint
  · If exactly 1 SKU matches → resolved (LIVE product)
  · If multiple SKUs map to one master product → ASK which (show supplier + pack + price for each)
- No catalogue match → AD-HOC line (sku: null, isCustom: true). Ask the user to confirm spec if needed.
- Multi-product prompts: resolve all products in parallel before moving to STEP 3.

STEP 3 — Supplier (per line)
- LIVE catalogue line → supplier is deterministic from the SKU. No ask.
- AD-HOC line → ASK from user_profile.permitted_suppliers. If none plausibly fit, surface the onboarding option ("none of your suppliers carry this — onboard a new supplier?").
- pending_onboarding supplier (in all_suppliers_including_pending but not in permitted_suppliers) → still populate the line with that supplier's name; the user resolves the onboarding flow separately. Do not gate or block.

== Routing — strictly binary ==
- LIVE = catalogue SKU match + current price present
- LIVE product → issuesAs: "REQ"
- ANY non-live product (ad-hoc, no SKU, missing price) → issuesAs: "RFQ"
- No other heuristic. Don't reason about it — it's structural.

== Multi-supplier RFQ ==
If the user explicitly names multiple suppliers for one product ("quote tomatoes to Premier AND Brakes"), emit ONE LINE PER SUPPLIER. Same SKU spec, different supplier per line, all RFQ.

== Other dimensions (populate silently, no asking) ==
- Outlet: explicit > historical cluster on product family > site.default_outlet_code
- Dept, CC, GL: from the matched outlet record
- Treatment: master's defaultTreatment > "Direct to P&L" for ad-hoc
- Need-by: parse relative to context.today; default null if not mentioned
- Qty/UoM: convert using catalogue packSize when units differ

== Multi-turn behaviour ==
Prior turns are visible. A reply like "Edinburgh" RESOLVES the site question you asked previously — combine it with the original product request, don't treat it as a new prompt.

== Existing lines — never duplicate ==
context.current_order.existing_lines is the source of truth for what's ALREADY in the order. Lines from earlier turns appear here once they've been populated.

When processing the latest user turn:
- Emit lines ONLY for products NEWLY requested in this turn.
- If the user mentions a product that already exists in existing_lines (match on product name + siteId + supplier), DO NOT emit it again. Instead emit a blocking_question asking whether to increment the existing line's quantity. Never silently duplicate.
- priorMessages provides conversational context for resolving the CURRENT question only. It is NOT a backlog of unfulfilled requests. A product that appears in both priorMessages AND existing_lines has already been added — do not re-add it.
- If the latest turn is purely conversational (clarification, confirmation, "thanks") and contains no new product request, return sites: [] with reasoning explaining there's nothing new to add.

== Hard rules ==
- NEVER emit a site object with empty lines. If lines can't be produced yet, return sites: [] and put the reason in blocking_questions.
- NEVER ask about outlet, dept, CC, GL, or treatment — populate them.
- NEVER skip ahead in the intake. Step 1 before step 2 before step 3.
- AD-HOC SUPPLIER GATE — if a line has no catalogue SKU match AND the user has not explicitly named a supplier in any turn, you MUST emit a blocking_question asking which supplier to use (list the permitted ones + an "onboard new" option). Do NOT populate that line with supplier: "" or guess from spend-category overlap. Return sites: [] for that turn — the supplier question is blocking.
- AD-HOC PRICE — if a line is ad-hoc, do NOT guess a price. Leave it for the supplier to quote.
- CODING LINKAGE — every line MUST carry a valid Dept↔CC↔GL triple drawn from the linkage tables (departments, cost_centres, chart_of_accounts in context). Specifically:
  · cost_centre.dept MUST equal department (each CC belongs to exactly one Dept)
  · cost_centre.allowedGLs MUST include gl_account (a CC can only post to GLs it's permitted to)
  · The easiest path: pick the outlet first, copy its dept/cc/defaultGL. If you need to cross-charge (e.g. wine for the bar coded to a different CC), pick a CC from cost_centres that lives in the right Dept and permits the GL you want.
  · If you can't find a valid triple, emit a blocking_question rather than producing inconsistent coding.

== Worked examples ==

INPUT (one-shot happy path): "Order 20kg vine tomatoes for Mayfair restaurant"
RESOLUTION:
  · Step 1: Site = SITE-LON-01 (explicit "Mayfair"), LE = LE-UK-OPS (derived)
  · Step 2: PRD-TOM-005 (catalogue, 5kg case @£12.50) — qty 4 cs
  · Step 3: Premier Produce Co. (from SKU) — LIVE → REQ
OUTPUT: populate_order with 1 site, 1 line, no blocking_questions.

INPUT (staged): turn 1 "5 deck chairs", turn 2 "Edinburgh", turn 3 "Pro Catering Equip"
TURN 1: Site unresolved → blocking_question "Which property — Grand Hotel Mayfair or The Edinburgh Castle?"
TURN 2 (sees prior turns): Site = SITE-EDI-01, LE = LE-SCO-OPS. Product = ad-hoc "deck chair". Supplier unresolved → blocking_question "Deck chairs aren't in your catalogue. Which supplier should I quote — <permitted list> — or onboard a new one?"
TURN 3 (sees prior turns): Supplier = "Pro Catering Equip". Ad-hoc + non-live → RFQ. Populate 1 line.

INPUT (multi-supplier RFQ): "Quote 20kg vine tomatoes for Mayfair from Premier and Brakes"
RESOLUTION: 2 lines, same spec, supplier=Premier on line 1, supplier=Brakes on line 2. Both RFQ (explicit quote request).

Always respond with ONLY a single JSON object. No prose, no code fences. The caller specifies the exact schema in the user content.`;

/* ---------- Agent system prompt — BULK EXTRACT mode ----------
   This is a deliberately different prompt for the file-driven bulk path. The
   default AGENT_SYSTEM is conversational and gates aggressively (staged intake,
   AD-HOC SUPPLIER GATE returns sites:[] until resolved). Bulk extract needs the
   opposite: extract every row from the file, even if suppliers are unknown,
   even if prices are missing — the user reviews and fixes in the modal table.

   Critical: bulk-upload files often carry the customer's OWN coding strings
   (their outlet codes, CC codes, GL accounts, treatment labels). These will
   not match ProFlow's seed data exactly. The agent's job is to TRANSLATE,
   not to demand a match — pick the closest valid coding from the linkage
   tables, surface the unmatched original in agent_note for human review.
*/
const AGENT_SYSTEM_BULK_EXTRACT = `You are the ProFlow Bulk Extraction Agent. You read attached files (Excel/CSV/PDF/image) and return a structured order populated with one line per product row.

== UPLOAD SOURCE — read context.upload_source FIRST ==
Two values matter:

'order_list' (demand-led, no prices expected):
- Ad-hoc lines without prices route to RFQ. issuesAs = "RFQ" when (no catalogue match AND no price), else "REQ".
- NEVER fabricate prices. estPrice null is fine.

'quotation' (supplier has already quoted, prices are in the file):
- Every line MUST have a price. If a row is missing one, do NOT include it in items[] — surface those rows in agent_note as "skipped: missing quote price".
- issuesAs = "REQ" for every line — there is no RFQ step, the quotation IS the price discovery.
- The supplier confirmation step still applies (file may have one supplier across all rows; if so, no confirmation needed; if missing, propose).
- catalogue_writeback should be set to true on every item (the calling code will use this flag to auto-add to catalogue without the per-item checkbox).


== PROPOSE ONLY WHEN INFORMATION IS MISSING ==
This is critical. Confirmations are for fields the file leaves BLANK or AMBIGUOUS. They are NOT a "show your work" mechanism. If the file says LE-UK-OPS in every row, USE IT — do not ask the user to confirm what the file already tells you.

Default to MODE B (silent extraction). Only emit MODE A when at least one order-level field has no usable answer anywhere in the file or notes.

== TOP-DOWN RESOLUTION ORDER ==

For EACH top-level dimension (LE, Site, Supplier, Project Code), evaluate in order:

(1) Look in the file. Is the field populated with a usable value (an existing entity in context, or a reasonable string that maps cleanly)?
    - All rows have the same value → use it. NO CONFIRMATION.
    - Rows have different values → use them per-row, no confirmation needed (the file is explicit).

(2) Not in the file? Look in the user_notes. Same logic.

(3) Not in notes? Now you may propose a default — this is where confirmations enter.
    - If you can pick a sensible default from context (most-fitting supplier by product category, etc.), propose ONE for confirmation.
    - If there's no sensible default, mark the field as unresolved per line and continue (e.g. supplier null per line — user fixes in review).

STEP 1 — LEGAL ENTITY
- File has LE column with values that map to permitted_LEs → use it silently. NO CONFIRMATION.
- File has no LE column but only one permitted LE in context → use it silently. NO CONFIRMATION.
- Multiple permitted LEs and no signal → propose the most likely (e.g. LE of the dominant site).

STEP 2 — SITE
- File has Site column → use it silently per row.
- File has no Site but user_notes name one or only one permitted site exists → use it silently.
- Genuinely ambiguous → propose default_site_id for confirmation.

STEP 3 — SUPPLIER
- File has Supplier column → use it silently per row.
- File has no Supplier column AND user_notes don't name one → THIS is the confirmation. Propose a single supplier as the order-level default based on product category mix, plus alternatives.

STEP 4 — PROJECT CODE
- File has Project Code column with a value → use it silently.
- File blank everywhere → don't ask. Leave Project Code null.

STEP 5 — PRODUCT (per row)
- Extract name verbatim. Catalogue match if obvious; otherwise ad-hoc.
- Qty default 1, UoM default EACH.
- CRITICAL — NEVER COLLAPSE OR DEDUPLICATE ROWS. Each row in the source document is a distinct line, even when:
  · Two rows share the same product name (e.g. "King Size Bed Frame" appears on row 1 and row 3) — they are separate lines because they go to different sites, different outlets, or different cost centres.
  · Two rows have identical name + qty + price — still separate lines. The document author put them on separate rows for a reason (different delivery destination, different project allocation, different invoice slot).
  · Identical SKU codes appear multiple times — still separate lines.
  The output items[] array MUST have exactly the same number of entries as the document has product rows. If the document has 3 product rows, items[] has 3 entries. If 22, items[] has 22. Mention any discrepancy in agent_note.

== SAME PRODUCT, DIFFERENT SITES — DO NOT MERGE ==
This is the failure mode that broke the previous extraction: an invoice listed "King Bed Frame" three times (rows 1, 2 going to Cotswolds; row 3 going to London — same SKU, same unit price), and the model merged them down to two lines, omitting the London row.

The rule is absolute: if two rows have the same product but different sites, they MUST become two separate items in the output. Never reassign one site's line to another site's line. Never sum quantities across sites. Never assume "the user really meant one consolidated row."

Sanity-check before returning:
1. Count product rows in the source. items.length MUST equal that count.
2. For each distinct (product, siteId) combination in items[], you should have exactly one entry per occurrence in the source. If "King Bed Frame at SITE-LON-01" appears once in the source, it appears once in items[]. If it appears twice in the source (e.g. two delivery dates or two project codes), it appears twice in items[].
3. If your count doesn't match, you've merged something — go back and split.

== HANDLING UNKNOWN SITES ==
- If the file references a site code that isn't in permitted_sites (e.g. SITE-COT-01 when Cotswolds isn't in scope), do NOT silently fold those rows into another site. Keep them as separate items with the original siteId from the file (verbatim). The review modal lets the user pick the correct site per row. Flag in agent_note: "row N references SITE-COT-01 which is not in permitted_sites — kept original siteId for user to remap; the London row(s) on the same invoice were processed normally and are independent of this issue."
- Critically: an unknown site on one row MUST NOT affect any other row. Process every row in isolation for the purpose of site resolution.

STEP 6 — CODING (per line, heuristic)
NEVER ask about coding. Always infer. Decision tree:

== CODING TRIPLE MUST BE COHERENT ==
The three fields are NOT independent. They move together: GL drives CC, CC drives Dept. If you decide a line's GL is 6310 (R&M), you MUST set CC = CC-MTC and Dept = Eng. You may NOT set GL = 6310 and leave CC = CC-FDR (which was the catalogue default). The dimensions cascade: GL → CC → Dept.

Concrete check, before returning every item:
- Pick GL based on the product
- Look up the CC for that GL from cost_centres (filter where cost_centres[].allowedGLs includes the GL)
- Set Dept = CC.dept

If the cascade is ambiguous (multiple CCs accept the GL, e.g. GL 6900 G&A which 3 CCs accept), leave CC blank — the calling code reconciles or asks. Do NOT pick one arbitrarily.

== HEURISTIC DECISION TREE ==
(a) File has Department / CC / GL columns AND they map onto the linkage → use them.
(b) File has foreign codes (CC-RMS, GL 10100, "Capex Direct Asset") → translate:
    · Treatment: "Capex Direct Asset" / "Capex WIP" → "CapEx". "P&L" / "Expense" → "Direct to P&L".
    · CC by treatment: CapEx → CC-GEN.
(c) File blank → PRODUCT-NAME HEURISTIC:
    · Food/produce/meat/seafood/salmon/dairy/bakery/sourdough/bread/chef/knife/kitchen → CC-FDR (F&B), GL 6010
    · Beverage/wine/whisky/spirits/beer/coffee/tea/soft drinks/tonic → CC-BAR (F&B), GL 6020
    · Linen/towels/sheets/toiletries/amenities/cleaning/soap/shampoo/chocolate/turndown/robe/blinds/curtain → CC-HSK (Rooms), GL 6110
    · Maintenance/repair/lift/elevator/HVAC/electrical/plumbing/paint/tool/lock/battery → CC-MTC (Eng), GL 6310
    · Furniture/FF&E/bed/mattress/sofa/chair/table/lamp/mirror/rug/safe/TV with CapEx treatment → CC-GEN, GL 1010
    · Insurance/license/annual subscription → CC-GEN (G&A), GL 5200, treatment Prepayment
    · Training/certification/stationery/uniforms → CC-GEN (G&A), GL 6900
    · No signal → site's default outlet coding
(d) Outlet from resolved CC: CC-FDR→REST · CC-BAR→BAR · CC-HSK→HSK · CC-MTC→MTC · CC-GEN→GEN. If missing at site, use site default.
(e) Validate. Fail → fall back to site default coding, surface in agent_note.

== OUTPUT MODES ==

MODE A — confirmations (only when at least one field is genuinely missing):
{
  "confirmations": [
    {
      "field": "supplier",
      "question": "No supplier in the file. Use Premier Produce Co. for all 10 lines?",
      "proposed": "Premier Produce Co.",
      "alternatives": ["Linen & Laundry", "Brakes"],
      "reasoning": "F&B dominates the product mix; Premier is the strongest single-supplier fit."
    }
  ],
  "items": [],
  "agent_note": "All other fields resolved from the file. Holding extraction until supplier confirmed."
}

MODE B — extraction complete (use whenever the file gives you enough to proceed):
{
  "confirmations": [],
  "items": [
    {
      "name": "product name verbatim from file",
      "qty": <number — default 1 if blank>,
      "uom": "kg | ea | cs | box | l | ml | ...",
      "supplier": "supplier name or null",
      "estPrice": <number or null>,
      "siteId": "SITE-... from permitted_sites",
      "legalEntity": "LE code",
      "issuesAs": "REQ | RFQ",
      "coding": {
        "outlet": "outletId",
        "dept": "F&B | Rooms | Eng | G&A",
        "costCentre": "CC-... code",
        "glAccount": "GL code as string"
      },
      "treatment": "Direct to P&L | Prepayment | Inventory | CapEx",
      "agent_note": "per-line note if needed, else null"
    }
  ],
  "agent_note": "N lines extracted. LE/Site/Project from file. Supplier from user confirmation. Coding inferred via heuristic for blank rows."
}

Respond with ONLY a single JSON object. No prose, no code fences. Default to MODE B whenever possible.`;

/* ---------- Initial state ---------- */
const initialOrder = {
  id: 'ORD-2026-0046',
  status: 'draft',
  description: '',
  requester: 'Flo Brunner',
  requiredBy: '',
  defaultBusinessArea: 'multi-site',
  // routing = "where the next manual add lands". Cascade LE → Site (outlet auto-resolves).
  // Multi-target orders flip between routings as the user builds them.
  // History remembers prior targets in this order so the user can jump back.
  routing: { legalEntity: '', siteId: '', outletId: '' },
  routingHistory: [],
  // routingUserConfirmed — Sovereign-AI gate. False until the human explicitly
  // picks LE AND Site via the RoutingStrip dropdowns (action.userInitiated = true).
  // Auto-resolutions (singleton LEs, agent populates, restore) do not flip it.
  // Validation blocks submit when sites exist but this is false.
  routingUserConfirmed: false,
  // pendingAdd = product the user clicked Add on while routing was incomplete.
  // Stays queued until the strip resolves, then auto-fires.
  pendingAdd: null,
  activeSiteId: null,  // site selected in the catalogue dropdown — lines go here directly
  sites: []  // sites are added as the user adds lines to a site
};

/* ---------- Seed ledger ----------
   Wireframe demo data so the Invoice tabs aren't empty on first load.
   Generates a small but representative slice of the procurement chain:
     · 4 POs in various ack/received states, across 2 sites and 3 suppliers
     · 3 GRN events recording physical receipts against those POs
     · 6 invoices covering every status in the lifecycle:
       - INV-2026-0001  pending_match       (Premier Produce, no matches yet)
       - INV-2026-0002  partially_matched   (Brakes, 2 of 4 lines matched)
       - INV-2026-0003  matched             (Linen, all lines in tolerance)
       - INV-2026-0004  disputed            (Brakes, price variance flags)
       - INV-2026-0005  approved_for_post   (historical, already approved)
       - INV-2026-0006  partially_matched   (sent back from approver — has reason)
   Ids are deterministic so the demo replays consistently. Real session events
   coexist with these seeds in the same ledger.
*/

const initialState = {
  order: initialOrder,
  catalogue: CATALOGUE,
  suppliers: SUPPLIERS,
  sites: SITES,
  user: {
    name: 'Flo Brunner',
    role: 'Property Director',
    permittedLEs: ['LE-UK-OPS', 'LE-SCO-OPS'],                     // multi-LE — must resolve via Site
    assignedSites: ['SITE-LON-01', 'SITE-EDI-01'],
    permittedSuppliers: ['SUP-001', 'SUP-002', 'SUP-003', 'SUP-005', 'SUP-006', 'SUP-007', 'SUP-008', 'SUP-009', 'SUP-010', 'SUP-011'],  // SUP-004 (Bayle) excluded -> triggers onboarding gate
    // Permission flags. canEditCoding gates the post-submission coding-override
    // affordance on Reqs / POs / Invoices. In production this comes from the
    // org's role/permission system; default TRUE in the wireframe so the
    // capability is demonstrable. Toggle to false to test the locked-down view.
    permissions: { canEditCoding: true }
  },
  ledger: [],  // populated via lazy init in useReducer; seed depends on classifyMatchVariance defined later in the module
  agent: { open: false, messages: [], pendingSuggestions: [], typing: false },
  recentlyAdded: [],  // for quick-reorder strip
  flowRequests: []    // supplier requests created via the Flow wizard
};

/* ---------- Helpers ---------- */
const uid = (prefix) => `${prefix}-${Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 8).toUpperCase()}`;
const gbp = (n) => `£${(Number(n) || 0).toLocaleString('en-GB', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 })}`;
const nowIso = () => new Date().toISOString().replace('T', ' ').slice(0, 16);

/* ---------- Event-shape helpers (Phase 1 ledger refactor) ----------
   Ledger events follow a common shape:
     { eventId, eventType, parentEventId, timestamp, status, ...payload }
   eventType   — 'ORDER' | 'RFQ' | 'REQUISITION' | 'PO'
   parentEventId — lineage link (null for ORDER root events)
   status      — lifecycle state, type-specific (see per-type comments at emission)
   On submit, one ORDER event fans out into N REQUISITION events (one per
   LE | Site | Supplier partition of REQ-routed lines) and M RFQ events
   (one per RFQ-routed line). PO events emit later, after the Req approval
   workflow clears. Existing ledger rows persisted before this refactor have
   no eventType — consumers treat missing eventType as ORDER for backward
   compatibility. */
const EVENT_TYPE = {
  ORDER: 'ORDER', RFQ: 'RFQ', REQUISITION: 'REQUISITION', PO: 'PO', GRN: 'GRN', INVOICE: 'INVOICE',
  // Incoming document events — pre-commit state. The agent (or upload) has extracted
  // data from a PDF/email/portal and parked it here for human verification. On
  // commit, an INVOICE or QUOTE event is emitted and the document event marks
  // status 'committed' (kept for audit lineage; not deleted).
  INCOMING_INVOICE_DOC: 'INCOMING_INVOICE_DOC',
  INCOMING_QUOTE_DOC:   'INCOMING_QUOTE_DOC',
  QUOTE: 'QUOTE'
};

const newReqId = (n) => `REQ-2026-${String(n).padStart(4, '0')}`;
const newRfqId = (n) => `RFQ-2026-${String(n).padStart(4, '0')}`;
const newGrnId = (n) => `GRN-2026-${String(n).padStart(4, '0')}`;
const newInvoiceId = (n) => `INV-2026-${String(n).padStart(4, '0')}`;
const newQuoteId   = (n) => `QTE-2026-${String(n).padStart(4, '0')}`;
const newDocId     = (kind, n) => `${kind}-DOC-${String(n).padStart(4, '0')}`;

/* Budget flag — wireframe stub. Production reads from budgets-admin.
   The demo derives a deterministic chip from partition net so the same
   submission shows the same flag on replay; no backing store required. */
const deriveBudgetStatus = (net) => {
  if (net > 5000) return 'breach';
  if (net > 2500) return 'flag';
  return 'within';
};

/* Ledger selectors — used by RFQ / Requisition / PO views (built in later passes).
   Pre-refactor ledger rows used eventType: 'Order' (title case); the new shape uses
   'ORDER' (enum). Selectors normalise so persisted state from older sessions still
   renders in the Orders tab. */
const isOrderEvent = (e) => String(e.eventType || '').toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.ORDER;
// Deduplicate by orderId — a double-click on the routing modal confirm button
// could have emitted two ORDER events with the same orderId before the guard
// was in place. Keep only the first occurrence (earliest in the prepended ledger).
const selectOrderEvents = (ledger) => {
  const seen = new Set();
  return ledger.filter(e => {
    if (!isOrderEvent(e)) return false;
    if (seen.has(e.orderId)) return false;
    seen.add(e.orderId);
    return true;
  });
};
const selectRfqEvents = (ledger) => ledger.filter(e => String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.RFQ);
const selectRequisitionEvents = (ledger) => ledger.filter(e => String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.REQUISITION);
const selectPOEvents = (ledger) => ledger.filter(e => String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.PO);
const selectGRNEvents = (ledger) => ledger.filter(e => String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.GRN);
const selectInvoiceEvents = (ledger) => ledger.filter(e => String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE);
const selectIncomingInvoiceDocs = (ledger) =>
  ledger.filter(e => String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.INCOMING_INVOICE_DOC && e.status !== 'committed' && e.status !== 'rejected');
const selectIncomingQuoteDocs = (ledger) =>
  ledger.filter(e => String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.INCOMING_QUOTE_DOC && e.status !== 'committed' && e.status !== 'rejected');
const selectQuoteEvents = (ledger) => ledger.filter(e => String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.QUOTE);
/* Aggregate received qty per PO line across one or more GRNs against that PO.
   Returns an object: { [poLineIdx]: totalReceived }. Used by PO views to show
   open vs received split and by GRN view to compute remaining-to-receive. */
const grnReceivedTotalsForPo = (ledger, poEventId) => {
  const totals = {};
  selectGRNEvents(ledger)
    .filter(g => g.parentEventId === poEventId)
    .forEach(g => g.lines.forEach(l => {
      totals[l.poLineIdx] = (totals[l.poLineIdx] || 0) + (l.receivedQty || 0);
    }));
  return totals;
};
/* Aggregate invoiced qty per PO line across confirmed invoice matches.
   Each invoice carries lines that may reference one or more PO lines via the
   `matchedTo` array. Used by the matching UI to show the remaining invoiceable
   qty against a PO line (so an operator can't accidentally over-invoice it). */
const invoicedTotalsForPo = (ledger, poEventId) => {
  const totals = {};
  selectInvoiceEvents(ledger)
    .filter(inv => inv.status === 'matched' || inv.status === 'partially_matched' || inv.status === 'approved_for_post')
    .forEach(inv => inv.lines.forEach(invLine => {
      (invLine.matchedTo || []).forEach(m => {
        if (m.poEventId === poEventId) {
          totals[m.poLineIdx] = (totals[m.poLineIdx] || 0) + (m.matchedQty || 0);
        }
      });
    }));
  return totals;
};
const selectByParent = (ledger, parentEventId) => ledger.filter(e => e.parentEventId === parentEventId);

/* ---------- Variance classifier ----------
   Used by the manual invoice-matching UI. Given an invoice line, the PO line
   it's been matched to, and the cumulative qty received against that PO line
   across all GRNs, computes deltas and emits a list of variance flags. This
   is the substrate the agent-enabled matcher will reuse — the agent batches
   match suggestions but routes them through the same classifier so manual
   and agent paths produce identical variance verdicts.

   Three-way logic:
     · invoice qty vs PO ack qty       → qty_short | qty_over     (PO leg)
     · invoice unit price vs PO price  → price_low | price_high   (PO leg)
     · invoice qty vs GRN received qty → grn_short | grn_over | no_receipt   (GRN leg)
     · description string mismatch     → desc_drift               (semantic leg)

   `receivedQty` is the cumulative across every GRN against this PO line (use
   grnReceivedTotalsForPo to compute). If omitted, the GRN leg is skipped —
   useful when invoking the classifier in a context where GRN data isn't
   relevant (e.g. preview against a not-yet-received PO).

   VAT leg — exact match, not within-tolerance. VAT rates are categorical (0%,
   5%, 20% in UK) not continuous, so any difference is structurally meaningful
   and gets flagged. The supplier-LE expected rate (per the architectural call:
   "VAT/GST is auto-resolved from the supplier-LE pair at transaction time")
   is passed in as `expectedVatPct` when available — if not provided, the leg
   compares invoice VAT against PO VAT only.

   Tolerances are wireframe defaults — production pulls them from supplier-
   level tolerance settings. */
const TOLERANCE = { qtyPct: 0.05, pricePct: 0.02, taxAbs: 0.10 };  // ±5% qty, ±2% unit price, ±£0.10 tax-amount rounding drift
const classifyMatchVariance = ({ invLine, poLine, matchedQty, receivedQty, expectedVatPct }) => {
  const flags = [];
  const baseQty = poLine.confirmedQty ?? poLine.qty;
  const basePrice = poLine.confirmedUnitPrice ?? poLine.unitPrice;
  const qtyDelta = (matchedQty - baseQty);
  const qtyPct = baseQty ? qtyDelta / baseQty : 0;
  const priceDelta = (invLine.unitPrice - basePrice);
  const pricePct = basePrice ? priceDelta / basePrice : 0;
  if (qtyPct < -TOLERANCE.qtyPct)        flags.push('qty_short');
  else if (qtyPct >  TOLERANCE.qtyPct)   flags.push('qty_over');
  if (pricePct >  TOLERANCE.pricePct)    flags.push('price_high');
  else if (pricePct < -TOLERANCE.pricePct) flags.push('price_low');
  if (invLine.product && poLine.product && invLine.product.trim().toLowerCase() !== poLine.product.trim().toLowerCase()) {
    flags.push('desc_drift');
  }

  // GRN leg — only evaluated when caller provides receivedQty
  let grn = null;
  if (typeof receivedQty === 'number') {
    const grnDelta = matchedQty - receivedQty;
    const grnPct = receivedQty ? grnDelta / receivedQty : (matchedQty > 0 ? 1 : 0);
    if (receivedQty === 0 && matchedQty > 0) {
      flags.push('no_receipt');
    } else if (grnPct > TOLERANCE.qtyPct) {
      flags.push('grn_short');  // invoice exceeds what physically arrived
    } else if (grnPct < -TOLERANCE.qtyPct) {
      flags.push('grn_over');   // less invoiced than received — possible split-invoice
    }
    grn = { receivedQty, grnDelta, grnPct };
  }

  // Tax leg — aligns with Tom's Workstream E proposal (TAX_MISMATCH conflict type).
  //
  // Rate check: categorical, no tolerance — a Standard / Reduced / Zero / Exempt
  // category change is structurally meaningful and must be flagged regardless
  // of magnitude.
  //
  // Amount check: small absolute tolerance for line-vs-header rounding drift
  // (a few pence, configured via TOLERANCE.taxAbs and overridable per-supplier
  // in the production data model). Per-line VAT computed vs per-invoice VAT
  // diverges by pennies across many lines — that drift is expected, not a flag.
  //
  // Expected-rate check: where the supplier-LE pair has a known VAT regime
  // (production: vatRegimeByLe on supplier master; wireframe: heuristic via
  // expectedVatPctForSupplierLe), an invoice rate that disagrees fires
  // `tax_unexpected_rate` — catches e.g. a UK food supplier returning 20%
  // when zero-rating was expected, or a service supplier returning 0%.
  const invVatRate = invLine.vatPct ?? 0;
  const poVatRate  = poLine.vatPct ?? 0;
  const invVatAmt  = invLine.tax ?? (((invLine.net ?? (matchedQty * invLine.unitPrice)) * invVatRate) / 100);
  const expectedPoVatAmt = (matchedQty * (poLine.confirmedUnitPrice ?? poLine.unitPrice) * poVatRate) / 100;
  let tax = {
    invVatRate, poVatRate, expectedVatPct: expectedVatPct ?? null,
    invVatAmt, expectedPoVatAmt,
    rateMismatch: false, amountDrift: false, unexpectedRate: false
  };
  if (invVatRate !== poVatRate) {
    // Categorical mismatch — Standard vs Zero vs Reduced
    flags.push('tax_rate_mismatch');
    tax.rateMismatch = true;
  } else if (Math.abs(invVatAmt - expectedPoVatAmt) > TOLERANCE.taxAbs) {
    // Same rate but the line's tax amount drifted beyond the rounding tolerance
    // — could indicate a per-line rounding policy difference or a supplier
    // computing tax on a different base (e.g. gross-of-discount vs net).
    flags.push('tax_amount_drift');
    tax.amountDrift = true;
  }
  if (expectedVatPct != null && invVatRate !== expectedVatPct) {
    // Supplier-LE expected rate doesn't match what the invoice carries.
    // E.g. food supplier returning 20% when zero-rating was expected.
    flags.push('tax_unexpected_rate');
    tax.unexpectedRate = true;
  }

  // Back-compat shim: keep the `vat` field name in the return so any
  // older render paths that read `variance.vat` still get a sensible object.
  const vat = {
    invVat: invVatRate, poVat: poVatRate, expectedVatPct: expectedVatPct ?? null,
    mismatch: tax.rateMismatch, mismatchAgainstExpected: tax.unexpectedRate
  };

  return { qtyDelta, qtyPct, priceDelta, pricePct, grn, vat, tax, flags, withinTolerance: flags.length === 0 };
};

/* ---------- Supplier × LE → expected VAT rate ----------
   Wireframe heuristic: category-driven defaults. UK food suppliers are
   zero-rated (groceries, produce, meat, fish); standard 20% applies elsewhere.
   Production replaces this with a per-supplier-per-LE VAT regime config:
   the supplier master would carry a `vatRegimeByLe` map and this resolver
   would read it. Reverse-charge (intra-EU services) and partial-exemption
   handling sit on top of this resolver and aren't modelled in the wireframe.

   Returns null when no rule applies — callers should treat null as
   "no expected rate, skip the vat_unexpected check". */
const expectedVatPctForSupplierLe = (supplier, legalEntity) => {
  if (!supplier) return null;
  const cat = String(supplier.category || '').toLowerCase();
  // UK food zero-rating applies to unprocessed and most prepared foods
  if (cat.includes('produce') || cat.includes('frozen') || cat.includes('meat')
      || cat.includes('fish') || cat.includes('dry') || cat.includes('spices')) {
    return 0;
  }
  // Insurance — exempt (no VAT)
  if (cat.includes('insurance')) return 0;
  // Business rates — outside scope of VAT
  if (cat.includes('rates')) return 0;
  // Utilities, services, equipment, linen — standard rate 20%
  return 20;
};

/* ---------- PO match confidence scoring ----------
   Given an invoice and a candidate PO, computes a 0-100 confidence score plus
   per-signal evidence used to rank eligible POs in the matching workspace.
   Six signals contribute:
     · supplier match     (binary)       — 25 pts  — same supplier ID
     · site match         (binary)       — 10 pts  — invoice billing site = PO site
     · total proximity    (continuous)   — 20 pts  — |inv net - PO net| as % of PO net
     · line count match   (continuous)   — 10 pts  — similar count of lines
     · description overlap (continuous)  — 25 pts  — Jaccard token similarity of line products
     · po-ref in doc      (binary)       — 10 pts  — invoice document body / number references PO id
   Returned shape:
     { score: 0..100, signals: [{name, weight, hit, detail}], topReason: string }
   The agent-enabled matcher will reuse this; manual UI just renders the score
   bar and the top reason next to each candidate. */
const scorePoMatchForInvoice = (invoice, po) => {
  const signals = [];
  let score = 0;

  // 1. Supplier
  const supHit = invoice.supplierId && po.supplierId && invoice.supplierId === po.supplierId;
  signals.push({ name: 'Supplier', weight: 25, hit: supHit, detail: supHit ? `${po.supplier}` : 'different supplier' });
  if (supHit) score += 25;

  // 2. Site
  const siteHit = invoice.siteId && po.siteId && invoice.siteId === po.siteId;
  signals.push({ name: 'Site', weight: 10, hit: siteHit, detail: siteHit ? `${po.siteName || po.siteId}` : 'different site' });
  if (siteHit) score += 10;

  // 3. Total proximity
  const poNet = po.netTotal || 0;
  const invNet = invoice.netTotal || 0;
  const totalPct = poNet ? Math.abs(invNet - poNet) / poNet : 1;
  const totalScore = Math.max(0, 20 * (1 - Math.min(totalPct, 1)));
  signals.push({
    name: 'Total proximity', weight: 20, hit: totalPct < 0.05,
    detail: `${gbp(invNet)} vs ${gbp(poNet)} (${(totalPct * 100).toFixed(1)}% Δ)`
  });
  score += totalScore;

  // 4. Line count match
  const invLines = invoice.lines?.length || 0;
  const poLines = po.lines?.length || 0;
  const lineCountDiff = Math.abs(invLines - poLines);
  const lineCountScore = Math.max(0, 10 * (1 - Math.min(lineCountDiff / Math.max(poLines, 1), 1)));
  signals.push({
    name: 'Line count', weight: 10, hit: lineCountDiff <= 1,
    detail: `${invLines} inv · ${poLines} PO`
  });
  score += lineCountScore;

  // 5. Description overlap (Jaccard token similarity)
  const tokenise = (s) => new Set(String(s || '').toLowerCase().split(/[\s\W]+/).filter(t => t.length > 2));
  const invTokens = new Set();
  invoice.lines?.forEach(l => tokenise(l.product).forEach(t => invTokens.add(t)));
  const poTokens = new Set();
  po.lines?.forEach(l => tokenise(l.product).forEach(t => poTokens.add(t)));
  const intersection = [...invTokens].filter(t => poTokens.has(t)).length;
  const union = new Set([...invTokens, ...poTokens]).size;
  const jaccard = union ? intersection / union : 0;
  const descScore = 25 * jaccard;
  signals.push({
    name: 'Description overlap', weight: 25, hit: jaccard > 0.5,
    detail: `${intersection}/${union} tokens shared (${(jaccard * 100).toFixed(0)}%)`
  });
  score += descScore;

  // 6. PO reference in document
  const poRefHit = invoice.poRefInDocument && po.poId && String(invoice.poRefInDocument).includes(po.poId);
  signals.push({
    name: 'PO ref in doc', weight: 10, hit: poRefHit,
    detail: poRefHit ? `"${po.poId}" found on invoice` : 'no PO reference on document'
  });
  if (poRefHit) score += 10;

  // Top reason — strongest non-binary positive signal (for the one-line "why")
  const ranked = signals.filter(s => s.hit).sort((a, b) => b.weight - a.weight);
  const topReason = ranked.length ? ranked[0].name : 'low signal across all axes';

  return { score: Math.round(score), signals, topReason };
};

const getSite = (state, siteId) => state.sites.find(s => s.siteId === siteId);

/* ---------- Readable-label helpers ----------
   The ledger stores codes (OUT-LON-01-REST-01, CC-FDR, 6010).
   These helpers translate them to user-friendly labels. */
const outletNameOf = (outletCode, sites) => {
  if (!outletCode) return '—';
  for (const s of sites || []) {
    const o = s.outlets?.find(o => o.outletId === outletCode);
    if (o) return o.name;
  }
  return outletCode;
};
const ccNameOf = (ccCode) => {
  if (!ccCode) return '—';
  const r = COST_CENTRES.find(c => c.code === ccCode);
  return r ? r.name : ccCode;
};
const glLabelOf = (glCode) => {
  if (!glCode) return '—';
  const r = CHART_OF_ACCOUNTS.find(g => g.glCode === glCode);
  return r ? `${r.glCode} · ${r.name}` : glCode;
};
const deptLabelOf = (dept) => {
  // Departments are first-class master records — labels come from DEPARTMENTS.
  // Fallback to the raw code if not found (legacy data tolerance).
  if (!dept) return '—';
  const r = DEPARTMENTS.find(d => d.code === dept);
  return r ? r.name : dept;
};

/* ====== LINKAGE HELPERS — Dept ↔ CC ↔ GL ======
   The data model declares: each CC has a Dept (many CCs per Dept), each CC has
   an allowedGLs list (many-to-many with GLs), and each GL declares allowedCCs
   (reverse for fast lookup). These helpers do the lookups and one validator
   ties them together. '*' means "any" (used for transit / capex GLs that any
   CC can carry). */

// All CCs that belong to a Dept. Returns full records.
const ccsForDept = (deptCode) => {
  if (!deptCode) return COST_CENTRES;
  return COST_CENTRES.filter(c => c.dept === deptCode);
};

// All GLs a given CC may post to. Wildcard '*' on a CC means all P&L + balance
// GLs are allowed (used sparingly — currently no CC has it).
const glsForCC = (ccCode) => {
  if (!ccCode) return CHART_OF_ACCOUNTS;
  const cc = COST_CENTRES.find(c => c.code === ccCode);
  if (!cc) return CHART_OF_ACCOUNTS;
  if (cc.allowedGLs?.includes('*')) return CHART_OF_ACCOUNTS;
  return CHART_OF_ACCOUNTS.filter(g => cc.allowedGLs?.includes(g.glCode));
};

// All CCs that may post to a given GL. Used when the user picks a GL first
// (less common, but the inline cells support it). Wildcard '*' on a GL means
// any CC can carry it (e.g. transit accounts).
const ccsForGL = (glCode) => {
  if (!glCode) return COST_CENTRES;
  const gl = CHART_OF_ACCOUNTS.find(g => g.glCode === glCode);
  if (!gl) return COST_CENTRES;
  if (gl.allowedCCs?.includes('*')) return COST_CENTRES;
  return COST_CENTRES.filter(c => gl.allowedCCs?.includes(c.code));
};

// Single source of truth for "is this line's coding valid?". Drives the green
// check / red warning marker on each line. Returns { ok, reason }.
//   ok=true  → all three dimensions agree
//   ok=false → reason names the first broken linkage (Dept↔CC, then CC↔GL)
const validateCoding = ({ department, costCentre, glAccount }) => {
  if (!department || !costCentre || !glAccount) {
    return { ok: false, reason: 'incomplete', detail: 'One or more of Dept / CC / GL is empty.' };
  }
  const cc = COST_CENTRES.find(c => c.code === costCentre);
  if (!cc) return { ok: false, reason: 'unknown_cc', detail: `CC ${costCentre} is not in the registry.` };
  if (cc.dept !== department) {
    return { ok: false, reason: 'dept_cc_mismatch', detail: `${cc.name} (${cc.code}) belongs to ${deptLabelOf(cc.dept)}, not ${deptLabelOf(department)}.` };
  }
  const gl = CHART_OF_ACCOUNTS.find(g => g.glCode === glAccount);
  if (!gl) return { ok: false, reason: 'unknown_gl', detail: `GL ${glAccount} is not in the chart.` };
  const ccAllowsGL = cc.allowedGLs?.includes('*') || cc.allowedGLs?.includes(glAccount);
  const glAllowsCC = gl.allowedCCs?.includes('*') || gl.allowedCCs?.includes(costCentre);
  if (!ccAllowsGL || !glAllowsCC) {
    return { ok: false, reason: 'cc_gl_mismatch', detail: `${cc.name} cannot post to GL ${gl.glCode} (${gl.name}).` };
  }
  return { ok: true };
};

/* inferCodingFromName — name-based heuristic, mirrors the rules in the bulk agent
   prompt's STEP 6(c). Used as a BACKSTOP when:
     · The new-product agent returns weak coding (e.g. just GL, or nothing)
     · A line lands without explicit Dept/CC and we need somewhere sensible to
       start rather than the site's default outlet.

   Returns { dept, costCentre, glAccount, treatment, outletKey } or null when no
   pattern matches. outletKey is a hint ('REST' | 'BAR' | 'HSK' | 'MTC' | 'GEN')
   the caller can use to pick a matching outlet from the site's outlets.

   The function never throws on bad input — returns null on empty string. */
const inferCodingFromName = (productName) => {
  if (!productName) return null;
  const n = productName.toLowerCase();

  // Order matters — more-specific patterns first so "Espresso machine" lands
  // on CapEx (machine) not Beverage (espresso). "Olive oil bottle" lands on
  // Food (olive oil) not Beverage — "bottle" alone is no longer a trigger.

  // 1) FF&E / CapEx — equipment, furniture, large appliances
  if (/\b(machine|appliance|fridge|freezer|oven|dishwasher|washing machine|tumble dryer|tv|television|projector|printer(?! toner)|computer|laptop|server|safe|desk|chair|sofa|armchair|bed frame|bedside table|coffee table|side table|wardrobe|cabinet|cupboard|sideboard|mirror|artwork|painting|lamp(?! oil)|chandelier|rug|carpet|console)\b/.test(n)) {
    return { dept: 'G&A', costCentre: 'CC-GEN', glAccount: '1010', treatment: 'CapEx', outletKey: 'GEN' };
  }
  // 2) Insurance / subscription — Prepayment treatment
  if (/\b(insurance|licen[cs]e|subscription|annual fee|premium policy|warranty plan|service contract|rent|business rates)\b/.test(n)) {
    return { dept: 'G&A', costCentre: 'CC-GEN', glAccount: '5200', treatment: 'Prepayment', outletKey: 'GEN' };
  }
  // 3) Engineering / maintenance — repairs, building services
  if (/\b(maintenance|repair|lift|elevator|hvac|electrical|plumbing|paint(?! brush)|tool|tools|lock|locks|battery|batteries|boiler|filter|light bulb|bulb|led|valve|pipe|cable|wire|hose|gasket|fastener|screw|nail)\b/.test(n)) {
    return { dept: 'Eng', costCentre: 'CC-MTC', glAccount: '6310', treatment: 'Direct to P&L', outletKey: 'MTC' };
  }
  // 4) F&B Beverage — drinks by name (no generic "bottle" trigger)
  if (/\b(wine|whisky|whiskey|spirits?|beer|lager|ale|cider|champagne|prosecco|sparkling wine|coffee|espresso|cappuccino|latte|tea|tonic|soda|mixer|soft drinks?|drink|beverage|cocktail|liqueur|gin|vodka|rum|brandy|cognac|tequila|bourbon|sake|port|sherry|vermouth|bitters|juice|smoothie|water|mineral water|sparkling water|still water|bottled water|kombucha|milkshake)\b/.test(n)) {
    return { dept: 'F&B', costCentre: 'CC-BAR', glAccount: '6020', treatment: 'Direct to P&L', outletKey: 'BAR' };
  }
  // 5) F&B Food — everything edible that isn't a drink
  if (/\b(food|produce|meat|beef|lamb|pork|chicken|poultry|sausage|bacon|ham|duck|venison|seafood|salmon|tuna|fish|prawn|crab|lobster|oyster|scallop|mussel|dairy|cheese|butter|cream|yogurt|yoghurt|milk|egg|eggs|bakery|sourdough|bread|pastry|croissant|brioche|cake|tart|chef|kitchen(?! ware)|knife|knives|chopping board|herbs?|spice|spices|saffron|basil|thyme|rosemary|sage|oregano|garlic|ginger|chilli|cinnamon|nutmeg|paprika|cumin|cardamom|truffle|olive oil|truffle oil|vinegar|sauce|stock|broth|rice|pasta|noodle|flour|sugar|salt|pepper|honey|jam|preserve|condiment|vegetable|veg|fruit|berry|berries|tomato|tomatoes|avocado|asparagus|carrot|carrots|mushroom|mushrooms|onion|potato|lettuce|salad|spinach|kale|cucumber|pepper|broccoli|cauliflower|courgette|aubergine|squash|pumpkin|leek|celery|apple|pear|banana|orange|lemon|lime|grape|peach|plum|pineapple|melon|mango|chocolate(?! turndown)|cocoa|nuts?|almond|walnut|cashew|pistachio|hazelnut)\b/.test(n)) {
    return { dept: 'F&B', costCentre: 'CC-FDR', glAccount: '6010', treatment: 'Direct to P&L', outletKey: 'REST' };
  }
  // 6) Rooms / Housekeeping — linen, amenities, cleaning, soft furnishings
  if (/\b(linen|towels?|sheets?|bedding|toiletr|amenit|cleaning|soap|shampoo|conditioner|lotion|bath salt|turndown chocolate|robe|slipper|slippers|blinds?|curtains?|toilet roll|tissue|tissues|pillow|duvet|cushion|throw|hanger|coat hanger|bin liner|laundry bag|do not disturb|guest stationery|notepad|pencil)\b/.test(n)) {
    return { dept: 'Rooms', costCentre: 'CC-HSK', glAccount: '6110', treatment: 'Direct to P&L', outletKey: 'HSK' };
  }
  // 7) G&A operations — admin, office, training
  if (/\b(training|certification|stationery|uniform|office suppl|printer toner|paper|envelope|file|folder|binder|pen|marker|software|consult|legal fee|audit fee|professional fee)\b/.test(n)) {
    return { dept: 'G&A', costCentre: 'CC-GEN', glAccount: '6900', treatment: 'Direct to P&L', outletKey: 'GEN' };
  }

  // No signal — let the caller fall back to site defaults
  return null;
};

/* pickOutletForCC — given a site and a target cost centre, find the outlet at
   that site whose defaultCC matches. Used in tandem with inferCodingFromName
   to translate the heuristic's outletKey hint into an actual outletId at the
   user's chosen site. Falls back to site's default outlet if no match exists. */
const pickOutletForCC = (site, costCentre) => {
  if (!site?.outlets) return null;
  const match = site.outlets.find(o => o.cc === costCentre);
  if (match) return match.outletId;
  return (site.outlets.find(o => o.isDefault) || site.outlets[0])?.outletId || null;
};

/* SPEND_CATEGORIES — the user-facing product taxonomy.

   When a user creates a product, they pick ONE category. That single choice
   drives everything downstream: GL account, cost centre, department, and
   accounting treatment. Operations users never see GL/CC/Dept directly during
   creation — Finance owns those fields, and the category-to-coding map below
   is the contract between the two layers.

   Adding a new category here is the only place this mapping lives. If you
   want to introduce "F&B · Wine cellar inventory" you add one row; no other
   code changes. */
const SPEND_CATEGORIES = [
  { code: 'FB_FOOD',    label: 'F&B · Food',                       dept: 'F&B',   costCentre: 'CC-FDR', glAccount: '6010', treatment: 'Direct to P&L', uomDefault: 'KG'   },
  { code: 'FB_BEV',     label: 'F&B · Beverage',                   dept: 'F&B',   costCentre: 'CC-BAR', glAccount: '6020', treatment: 'Direct to P&L', uomDefault: 'BTL'  },
  { code: 'ROOMS_HSK',  label: 'Rooms · Housekeeping consumables', dept: 'Rooms', costCentre: 'CC-HSK', glAccount: '6110', treatment: 'Direct to P&L', uomDefault: 'EACH' },
  { code: 'ENG_MTC',    label: 'Engineering · Maintenance',        dept: 'Eng',   costCentre: 'CC-MTC', glAccount: '6310', treatment: 'Direct to P&L', uomDefault: 'EACH' },
  { code: 'GNA_OPS',    label: 'G&A · Operations',                 dept: 'G&A',   costCentre: 'CC-GEN', glAccount: '6900', treatment: 'Direct to P&L', uomDefault: 'EACH' },
  { code: 'GNA_PREPAY', label: 'G&A · Insurance / subscriptions',  dept: 'G&A',   costCentre: 'CC-GEN', glAccount: '5200', treatment: 'Prepayment',    uomDefault: 'EACH' },
  { code: 'FFE_CAPEX',  label: 'FF&E · CapEx',                     dept: 'G&A',   costCentre: 'CC-GEN', glAccount: '1010', treatment: 'CapEx',         uomDefault: 'EACH' }
];

/* suggestCategoryFromName — bridge from the existing keyword heuristic to the
   spend-category enum. Used by the "Suggest from name" button in the Create
   Product modal: user types a name, agent maps it to one of the categories
   above. Falls back to null when no pattern matches. */
const suggestCategoryFromName = (productName) => {
  const hint = inferCodingFromName(productName);
  if (!hint) return null;
  // Treatment-aware special cases come first
  if (hint.treatment === 'Prepayment') return 'GNA_PREPAY';
  if (hint.treatment === 'CapEx') return 'FFE_CAPEX';
  // Outlet-key → category code lookup
  switch (hint.outletKey) {
    case 'REST': return 'FB_FOOD';
    case 'BAR':  return 'FB_BEV';
    case 'HSK':  return 'ROOMS_HSK';
    case 'MTC':  return 'ENG_MTC';
    case 'GEN':  return 'GNA_OPS';
    default:     return null;
  }
};

/* getProductCategoryCode — returns the product's primary SPEND_CATEGORIES code.
   Legacy products in the seed CATALOGUE don't carry categoryCode explicitly;
   we derive it from gl + treatment using the same mapping the modal uses on
   creation. Once products are recreated through the new modal they'll carry
   categoryCode directly, but the derivation keeps the seed working without a
   migration. */
const getProductCategoryCode = (product) => {
  if (!product) return null;
  if (product.categoryCode) return product.categoryCode;
  if (product.treatment === 'Prepayment') return 'GNA_PREPAY';
  if (product.treatment === 'CapEx') return 'FFE_CAPEX';
  if (product.gl === '6010') return 'FB_FOOD';
  if (product.gl === '6020') return 'FB_BEV';
  if (product.gl === '6110') return 'ROOMS_HSK';
  if (product.gl === '6310') return 'ENG_MTC';
  if (product.gl === '6900') return 'GNA_OPS';
  if (product.gl === '5200') return 'GNA_PREPAY';
  if (product.gl === '1010') return 'FFE_CAPEX';
  return null;
};

/* getProductAllowedCategories — every product has a default category; some
   products are legitimately multi-use (wine: kitchen + bar; cleaning supplies:
   housekeeping + maintenance). Those carry an explicit allowedCategories list
   on the catalogue record. For everything else, the allowed list is just the
   primary category. The catalogue card uses this to decide whether to show
   the "Use as" picker.

   Result is always a non-empty array where allowedCategories[0] === primary. */
const getProductAllowedCategories = (product) => {
  const primary = getProductCategoryCode(product);
  if (!primary) return [];
  const explicit = product?.allowedCategories || [];
  // Ensure primary is first and dedupe
  const list = [primary, ...explicit.filter(c => c !== primary)];
  return list;
};

/* reconcileCodingPatch — every inline coding edit goes through this. Given the
   current coding and a partial patch (one field the user just changed), figure
   out what the OTHER fields should be. Rules:

   1. CC always determines Dept (CC.dept is 1:1). Setting CC silently sets Dept.
   2. If user changes a field and the rest of the triple still validates → no
      further changes.
   3. If a field becomes invalid AND there's exactly one valid candidate → fill
      it automatically (this is the "optimisation" — single answers don't need
      to bother the user).
   4. If there are multiple candidates → blank the invalid field so the user
      picks intentionally.
   5. Outlet never auto-changes from accounting edits — it's physical. The line
      can carry an outlet whose defaultCC differs from the line CC; we surface
      that as a "cross-charge" indicator elsewhere, not by overwriting outlet. */
const reconcileCodingPatch = (currentCoding, patch) => {
  const next = { ...currentCoding, ...patch };

  // The patch tells us which dimension the user explicitly touched. That dimension
  // is the user's intent — we never overwrite it. The other two dimensions follow.
  for (let pass = 0; pass < 3; pass++) {
    let mutated = false;

    // (a) CC → Dept (1:1). Skip if user just changed Dept — their intent wins.
    if (next.costCentre && !('dept' in patch)) {
      const cc = COST_CENTRES.find(c => c.code === next.costCentre);
      if (cc && cc.dept !== next.dept) { next.dept = cc.dept; mutated = true; }
    }

    // (b) User changed Dept → if existing CC is from another Dept, blank CC + GL.
    //     The user moved business areas; coding should follow.
    if ('dept' in patch && next.costCentre) {
      const cc = COST_CENTRES.find(c => c.code === next.costCentre);
      if (cc && cc.dept !== next.dept) {
        next.costCentre = '';
        next.glAccount = '';
        mutated = true;
      }
    }

    // (c) GL ↔ CC clash. Most-recently-edited wins: if patch changed GL, blank CC;
    //     if patch changed CC, blank GL.
    if (next.glAccount && next.costCentre) {
      const cc = COST_CENTRES.find(c => c.code === next.costCentre);
      const ccAllowsGL = cc && (cc.allowedGLs?.includes('*') || cc.allowedGLs?.includes(next.glAccount));
      if (!ccAllowsGL) {
        if ('glAccount' in patch) { next.costCentre = ''; mutated = true; }
        else if ('costCentre' in patch) { next.glAccount = ''; mutated = true; }
      }
    }

    // (d) GL → Dept/CC inference. Only when CC is blank.
    //     If current Dept has no CC that can post to this GL, adopt the GL's
    //     natural Dept (if unanimous across CCs). Then auto-fill CC if single candidate.
    if (next.glAccount && !next.costCentre) {
      let candidates = ccsForGL(next.glAccount);
      if (next.dept && !('dept' in patch)) {
        // Try keeping user's Dept first
        const inDept = candidates.filter(c => c.dept === next.dept);
        if (inDept.length > 0) {
          candidates = inDept;
        } else {
          // Adopt GL's natural Dept if all candidates agree, else blank Dept
          const depts = [...new Set(candidates.map(c => c.dept))];
          if (depts.length === 1) { next.dept = depts[0]; mutated = true; }
          else { next.dept = ''; mutated = true; }
        }
      } else if (!next.dept) {
        const depts = [...new Set(candidates.map(c => c.dept))];
        if (depts.length === 1) { next.dept = depts[0]; mutated = true; }
      }
      if (candidates.length === 1) {
        next.costCentre = candidates[0].code;
        next.dept = candidates[0].dept;
        mutated = true;
      }
    }

    // (e) Dept → CC inference. Only when CC is blank. Filter by current GL too —
    //     prevents the oscillation bug where (e) refills CC ignoring GL compatibility.
    if (next.dept && !next.costCentre) {
      let candidates = ccsForDept(next.dept);
      if (next.glAccount) {
        candidates = candidates.filter(c =>
          c.allowedGLs?.includes('*') || c.allowedGLs?.includes(next.glAccount)
        );
      }
      if (candidates.length === 1) { next.costCentre = candidates[0].code; mutated = true; }
    }

    // (f) CC → GL inference. Only when GL is blank. CC's single non-transit GL fills.
    if (next.costCentre && !next.glAccount) {
      const candidates = glsForCC(next.costCentre)
        .filter(g => !['2100', '2090', '1700', '1020'].includes(g.glCode));
      if (candidates.length === 1) { next.glAccount = candidates[0].glCode; mutated = true; }
    }

    if (!mutated) break;
  }

  // Return only the diff so dispatch stays surgical
  const diff = {};
  for (const k of Object.keys(next)) {
    if (next[k] !== currentCoding[k]) diff[k] = next[k];
  }
  return diff;
};

const buildLineFromProduct = (product, site, areaMaster, qty = 1, codingExplicit = false) => {
  /* Coding resolution — product drives accounting; routing strip drives outlet.

     Outlet rule (Flo's spec): "outlet should revert to a default unless
     otherwise specified". The default = whatever the routing strip points at,
     which itself defaults to the site's placeholder default outlet (typically
     General/shared). We never override the routing strip's outlet from the
     product — that's a delivery-location decision the user owns.

     Coding rule, two modes:
       · codingExplicit=true  — areaMaster already carries the user's explicit
         Dept/CC/GL choice (set by addCatalogueItem when a category or coding
         override is present). We trust it verbatim — no cascade, no heuristic.
         A Bath sheet added with category override to Food lands with F&B/
         CC-FDR/GL 6010 regardless of the product's GL 6110 default.
       · codingExplicit=false — default. Drive from product.gl via the
         linkage cascade. Ambiguous GLs fall back to the name heuristic, then
         to ccsForGL[0]. */
  let dept, costCentre, glAccount;
  const outlet = areaMaster.outlet;   // never overridden

  if (codingExplicit) {
    // Start from areaMaster (user's chip filter / category override).
    dept = areaMaster.departments[0] || '';
    costCentre = areaMaster.costCentre || '';
    glAccount = areaMaster.glAccount || '';

    // Fill any missing dimensions from product.gl, respecting what's already set.
    //   · Missing GL with a CC: pick the first compatible GL from glsForCC.
    //   · Missing GL, no CC: use product.gl if present.
    //   · Missing CC: derive from GL, filtered by current Dept if any.
    //   · Missing Dept: derive from CC.
    if (!glAccount && costCentre) {
      const candidates = glsForCC(costCentre);
      if (candidates.length > 0) glAccount = candidates[0].glCode;
    }
    if (!glAccount && product.gl) {
      // Use product GL only if it's compatible with the user's CC (when set)
      if (!costCentre || glsForCC(costCentre).some(g => g.glCode === product.gl)) {
        glAccount = product.gl;
      }
    }
    if (!costCentre && glAccount) {
      const candidates = ccsForGL(glAccount);
      const inDept = dept ? candidates.filter(c => c.dept === dept) : candidates;
      if (inDept.length > 0) {
        costCentre = inDept[0].code;
        if (!dept) dept = inDept[0].dept;
      } else if (candidates.length > 0) {
        costCentre = candidates[0].code;
        if (!dept) dept = candidates[0].dept;
      }
    }
    if (!dept && costCentre) {
      const cc = COST_CENTRES.find(c => c.code === costCentre);
      if (cc) dept = cc.dept;
    }
  } else if (product.gl) {
    // Cascade: GL → CC → Dept. Start fresh — don't carry stale CC/Dept forward.
    glAccount = product.gl;
    const reconciled = reconcileCodingPatch(
      { dept: '', costCentre: '', glAccount: '' },
      { glAccount: product.gl }
    );
    costCentre = reconciled.costCentre || '';
    dept = reconciled.dept || '';

    // GL ambiguous on CC (e.g. 6020 accepts both CC-FDR and CC-BAR) → name heuristic tiebreaker
    if (!costCentre) {
      const hint = inferCodingFromName(product.name);
      if (hint && validateCoding({ department: hint.dept, costCentre: hint.costCentre, glAccount }).ok) {
        dept = hint.dept;
        costCentre = hint.costCentre;
      }
    }

    // Last resort — pick the first CC that accepts this GL
    if (!costCentre) {
      const candidates = ccsForGL(glAccount);
      if (candidates.length > 0) {
        costCentre = candidates[0].code;
        dept = candidates[0].dept;
      }
    }
  } else {
    // No product GL — fall through to area master entirely
    dept = areaMaster.departments[0];
    costCentre = areaMaster.costCentre;
    glAccount = areaMaster.glAccount;
  }

  return {
    lineId: uid('LN'),
    productId: product.id,
    sku: product.sku,
    name: product.name,
    supplier: product.supplier,
    qty,
    uom: product.uom,
    price: product.price,
    vat: product.vat,
    coding: {
      legalEntity: areaMaster.legalEntity || site.legalEntity,
      outlet,
      dept,
      costCentre,
      glAccount
    },
    treatment: product.treatment,
    issuesAs: 'REQ',
    notes: '',
    agentSuggestion: null,
    agentSuggestionStatus: 'accepted',
    isCustom: false
  };
};

/* ---------- Reducer ---------- */
/* Lock all unlocked comments at a given stage on a given event. Called by
   transition reducers (REQ_APPROVE, PO_SEND_TO_SUPPLIER, INVOICE_APPROVE)
   to snapshot the comment thread once a stage closes. */
function lockCommentsAtStage(ev, stage) {
  if (!ev || !ev.comments?.length) return ev;
  return {
    ...ev,
    comments: ev.comments.map(c => c.stage === stage && !c.locked ? { ...c, locked: true, lockedAt: nowIso() } : c)
  };
}

function reducer(state, action) {
  switch (action.type) {
    /* ---------- RESET (DEV-ONLY) ----------
       Wipes all transactional ledger events and resets the order canvas to a
       blank draft so flows can be built against a clean sheet without legacy
       demo data in the way. Master data (catalogue, suppliers, sites) is kept.
       This whole case — plus resetDb and the sidebar button — is development
       scaffolding and should be removed before production. */
    case 'RESET_LEDGER': {
      return {
        ...initialState,
        ledger: [],
        catalogue: state.catalogue,
        suppliers: state.suppliers,
      };
    }

    /* ---------- COMMENTS ----------
       Stage-tagged comments on any event. They lock automatically when the
       stage transitions (req approval, PO send-to-supplier, invoice approval,
       etc.) so the audit trail stays intact. Both requester and approver see
       all comments — visibility is not role-filtered. */
    case 'COMMENT_ADD': {
      const newComment = {
        id: uid('CMT'),
        by: action.byName || 'Unknown',
        byRole: action.byRole || 'requester',
        at: nowIso(),
        text: action.text || '',
        stage: action.stage || 'general',
        locked: false,
      };
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId) return e;
        return { ...e, comments: [...(e.comments || []), newComment] };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'FLOW_REQUEST_CREATE': {
      const req = {
        id: uid('FRQ'),
        createdAt: nowIso(),
        createdBy: action.createdBy || 'You',
        status: 'draft', // draft | sent | supplier_responded | accepted | rejected
        supplierId: null,
        supplierName: null,
        supplierNote: '',
        buyerNote: action.buyerNote || '',
        lines: action.lines || [], // { id, name, qty, uom, estPrice, note }
        supplierLines: null, // supplier's priced response
        thread: []
      };
      return { ...state, flowRequests: [...state.flowRequests, req] };
    }
    case 'FLOW_REQUEST_UPDATE': {
      return {
        ...state,
        flowRequests: state.flowRequests.map(r =>
          r.id === action.id ? { ...r, ...action.patch } : r
        )
      };
    }
    case 'FLOW_REQUEST_SEND': {
      const fr = state.flowRequests.find(r => r.id === action.id);
      if (!fr) return state;
      const updated = {
        ...fr,
        status: 'sent',
        supplierId: action.supplierId,
        supplierName: action.supplierName,
        sentAt: nowIso(),
        thread: [...fr.thread, { at: nowIso(), by: 'You', text: `Request sent to ${action.supplierName}.` }]
      };
      // Simulate supplier response after a short delay (demo only)
      return { ...state, flowRequests: state.flowRequests.map(r => r.id === action.id ? updated : r) };
    }
    case 'FLOW_REQUEST_SUPPLIER_RESPOND': {
      const fr = state.flowRequests.find(r => r.id === action.id);
      if (!fr) return state;
      const supplierLines = fr.lines.map(l => ({
        ...l,
        supplierPrice: action.prices?.[l.id] ?? l.estPrice ?? 0,
        supplierNote: action.lineNotes?.[l.id] ?? '',
        available: action.availability?.[l.id] ?? true,
      }));
      const updated = {
        ...fr,
        status: 'supplier_responded',
        supplierLines,
        supplierNote: action.supplierNote || '',
        respondedAt: nowIso(),
        thread: [...fr.thread, { at: nowIso(), by: fr.supplierName, text: action.supplierNote || 'Supplier has responded with pricing.' }]
      };
      return { ...state, flowRequests: state.flowRequests.map(r => r.id === action.id ? updated : r) };
    }
    case 'FLOW_REQUEST_ACCEPT': {
      // Convert supplier-priced lines into a new draft order
      const fr = state.flowRequests.find(r => r.id === action.id);
      if (!fr || !fr.supplierLines) return state;
      const updatedFR = { ...fr, status: 'accepted', acceptedAt: nowIso() };
      return { ...state, flowRequests: state.flowRequests.map(r => r.id === action.id ? updatedFR : r) };
    }
    case 'FLOW_REQUEST_REJECT': {
      return {
        ...state,
        flowRequests: state.flowRequests.map(r =>
          r.id === action.id ? { ...r, status: 'rejected', rejectedAt: nowIso() } : r
        )
      };
    }
    case 'RESTORE': {
      const payload = { ...action.payload };
      // Forward-compat: orders persisted before the routing wizard existed lack these
      // fields. Patch in the empty defaults so the RoutingStrip and pendingAdd flow
      // don't have to special-case undefined throughout.
      if (payload.order) {
        payload.order = {
          ...payload.order,
          routing: payload.order.routing || { legalEntity: '', siteId: '', outletId: '' },
          routingHistory: payload.order.routingHistory || [],
          pendingAdd: payload.order.pendingAdd || null
        };
      }
      return { ...state, ...payload };
    }
    case 'MOVE_LINE_TO_SITE': {
      const { lineId, fromSiteId, toSiteId } = action;
      const fromGroup = state.order.sites.find(s => s.siteId === fromSiteId);
      if (!fromGroup) return state;
      const line = fromGroup.lines.find(l => (l.lineId || l.id) === lineId) || fromGroup.lines[lineId];
      if (!line) return state;
      let sites = state.order.sites.map(sg => {
        if (sg.siteId === fromSiteId) return { ...sg, lines: sg.lines.filter(l => (l.lineId || l.id) !== lineId && sg.lines.indexOf(l) !== lineId) };
        if (sg.siteId === toSiteId) return { ...sg, lines: [...sg.lines, { ...line, siteId: toSiteId }] };
        return sg;
      });
      // Add toSite group if it doesn't exist yet
      if (!sites.find(s => s.siteId === toSiteId)) {
        const toSite = state.sites.find(s => s.siteId === toSiteId);
        sites = [...sites, { siteId: toSiteId, collapsed: false, areaMasterCollapsed: false, areaMaster: { ...toSite?.defaults }, lines: [{ ...line, siteId: toSiteId }] }];
      }
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites } };
    }

    case 'SET_ACTIVE_SITE':
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, activeSiteId: action.siteId } };

    case 'SET_ORDER_FIELD': {
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, [action.field]: action.value } };
    }
    case 'ADD_SITE_GROUP': {
      const site = getSite(state, action.siteId);
      if (!site) return state;
      if (state.order.sites.find(s => s.siteId === action.siteId)) return state;
      const newSite = {
        siteId: site.siteId,
        collapsed: false,
        areaMasterCollapsed: false,
        areaMaster: { ...site.defaults, legalEntity: site.legalEntity },
        lines: []
      };
      // Adding a site group is also a routing signal — seed the strip so the user
      // doesn't have to pick the same site again when clicking Add on the catalogue.
      const newRouting = {
        legalEntity: site.legalEntity,
        siteId: site.siteId,
        outletId: site.defaults?.outlet || site.outlets?.[0]?.outletId || ''
      };
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites: [...state.order.sites, newSite], routing: newRouting } };
    }
    case 'REMOVE_SITE_GROUP': {
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites: state.order.sites.filter(s => s.siteId !== action.siteId) } };
    }
    case 'SET_PENDING_ADD': {
      // Latest-wins: clicking Add on a different product replaces the queue.
      // codingOverride carries the Dept/CC picked in the catalogue panel filters,
      // categoryOverride carries the multi-use product's "Use as" picker choice;
      // both survive the routing wizard and apply when the line finally fires.
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, pendingAdd: {
        productId: action.productId,
        qty: action.qty || 1,
        codingOverride: action.codingOverride || null,
        categoryOverride: action.categoryOverride || null
      } } };
    }
    case 'CLEAR_PENDING_ADD': {
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, pendingAdd: null } };
    }
    case 'SET_ROUTING': {
      // Patch the routing target. Cascading reset: changing an upstream field clears
      // downstream fields (LE change clears site+outlet, site change clears outlet).
      // When a complete routing resolves, push to routingHistory (dedup, max 6).
      //
      // action.userInitiated — true when the change came from the human clicking
      // a dropdown in the RoutingStrip. Flips routingUserConfirmed so the order
      // can pass the submit gate. Auto-resolutions (singletons, agent populates)
      // do NOT pass userInitiated, so the gate stays closed until the human acts.
      const cur = state.order.routing || { legalEntity: '', siteId: '', outletId: '' };
      let next = { ...cur, ...action.patch };
      if ('legalEntity' in action.patch && action.patch.legalEntity !== cur.legalEntity) {
        next.siteId = '';
        next.outletId = '';
      }
      if ('siteId' in action.patch && action.patch.siteId !== cur.siteId) {
        next.outletId = '';
      }
      // Update history when fully resolved
      let history = state.order.routingHistory || [];
      if (next.legalEntity && next.siteId && next.outletId) {
        const key = `${next.legalEntity}|${next.siteId}|${next.outletId}`;
        history = [next, ...history.filter(r => `${r.legalEntity}|${r.siteId}|${r.outletId}` !== key)].slice(0, 6);
      }
      const routingUserConfirmed = action.userInitiated
        ? Boolean(next.legalEntity && next.siteId)
        : state.order.routingUserConfirmed;
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, routing: next, routingHistory: history, routingUserConfirmed } };
    }
    case 'ADD_LINE': {
      const { siteId, line } = action;
      let sites = [...state.order.sites];
      let idx = sites.findIndex(s => s.siteId === siteId);
      if (idx < 0) {
        // New site group. If the order already has site groups, default-collapse
        // them so the canvas stays compact and the focus stays on the new group.
        if (sites.length >= 1) {
          sites = sites.map(s => ({ ...s, collapsed: true }));
        }
        const site = getSite(state, siteId);
        sites.push({
          siteId, collapsed: false, areaMasterCollapsed: false,
          areaMaster: { ...site.defaults, legalEntity: site.legalEntity },
          lines: [line]
        });
      } else {
        sites[idx] = { ...sites[idx], lines: [...sites[idx].lines, line] };
      }
      // recently added
      const recent = [{ productId: line.productId, name: line.name, qty: line.qty, siteId }, ...state.recentlyAdded].slice(0, 8);
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites }, recentlyAdded: recent };
    }
    case 'ADD_LINES_BULK': {
      // Bulk-upload outcome — many lines drop in one dispatch. The agent already
      // ran the linkage (supplier resolution, coding) for each so the reducer
      // doesn't reconcile; it just appends.
      const { siteId, lines } = action;
      let sites = [...state.order.sites];
      let idx = sites.findIndex(s => s.siteId === siteId);
      if (idx < 0) {
        if (sites.length >= 1) {
          sites = sites.map(s => ({ ...s, collapsed: true }));
        }
        const site = getSite(state, siteId);
        sites.push({
          siteId, collapsed: false, areaMasterCollapsed: false,
          areaMaster: { ...site.defaults, legalEntity: site.legalEntity },
          lines: [...lines]
        });
      } else {
        sites[idx] = { ...sites[idx], lines: [...sites[idx].lines, ...lines] };
      }
      const newRecent = lines.map(l => ({ productId: l.productId, name: l.name, qty: l.qty, siteId }));
      const recent = [...newRecent, ...state.recentlyAdded].slice(0, 8);
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites }, recentlyAdded: recent };
    }
    case 'ADD_TO_CATALOGUE': {
      // Promote a one-off ad-hoc product into the persistent catalogue so future
      // searches find it. SKU is freshly minted. Treatment / GL / category set by
      // the caller (modal manual path) or by the agent (RFQ-receipt write-back).
      // De-dupe by name + supplier — if it already exists, no-op.
      const { product } = action;
      const exists = state.catalogue.some(p =>
        p.name.toLowerCase() === product.name.toLowerCase() &&
        p.supplier === product.supplier
      );
      if (exists) return state;
      const newProduct = {
        id: uid('PRD'),
        sku: product.sku || `SKU-${Math.floor(Math.random() * 9000 + 1000)}`,
        ...product
      };
      return { ...state, catalogue: [...state.catalogue, newProduct] };
    }
    case 'ADD_SUPPLIER_PENDING': {
      // Inline supplier-onboarding shortcut from the New Product / Bulk Upload modals.
      // The supplier is created with status 'pending_onboarding' so it appears in
      // permitted_suppliers (the agent rule still treats it specially), can be
      // selected on lines, but cannot ship POs until Finance completes onboarding.
      // Optional fields can be passed for utility/rates/insurance-style suppliers
      // — poRequired:false plus defaultCoding/defaultAllocation seed the recurring-
      // invoice intake path. Inline-onboard from a product flow leaves these at
      // sensible defaults (poRequired:true) and Finance fills them in later via
      // the Suppliers screen.
      const { name, category, paymentTerms, poRequired, recurringInvoice, defaultCoding, defaultAllocation } = action;
      const exists = state.suppliers.some(s => s.name.toLowerCase() === name.toLowerCase());
      if (exists) return state;
      const newSupplier = {
        id: uid('SUP'),
        name,
        category: category || 'Custom',
        status: 'pending_onboarding',
        paymentTerms: paymentTerms || 'Net 30',
        poRequired: poRequired !== false,           // default true unless explicitly disabled
        recurringInvoice: recurringInvoice === true, // default false
        defaultCoding: defaultCoding || null,
        defaultAllocation: defaultAllocation || [],
        addedBy: state.user.name,
        addedAt: nowIso()
      };
      return { ...state, suppliers: [...state.suppliers, newSupplier] };
    }
    case 'ADD_SUPPLIER_ACTIVE': {
      // Suppliers screen — Finance creates a supplier with all fields populated.
      // Marked 'active' immediately (Finance owns the screen, so onboarding is
      // synonymous with creation here).
      const { name, category, paymentTerms, poRequired, recurringInvoice, defaultCoding, defaultAllocation } = action;
      const exists = state.suppliers.some(s => s.name.toLowerCase() === name.toLowerCase());
      if (exists) return state;
      const newSupplier = {
        id: uid('SUP'),
        name,
        category: category || 'Custom',
        status: 'active',
        paymentTerms: paymentTerms || 'Net 30',
        poRequired: poRequired !== false,
        recurringInvoice: recurringInvoice === true,
        defaultCoding: defaultCoding || null,
        defaultAllocation: defaultAllocation || [],
        addedBy: state.user.name,
        addedAt: nowIso()
      };
      return {
        ...state,
        suppliers: [...state.suppliers, newSupplier],
        // Auto-grant the user permission to use the new supplier
        user: { ...state.user, permittedSuppliers: [...(state.user.permittedSuppliers || []), newSupplier.id] }
      };
    }
    case 'UPDATE_SUPPLIER': {
      // Edit any field on a supplier. Used by the Suppliers screen to flip
      // poRequired, set defaultCoding, edit allocation splits, etc. Also used
      // to promote pending → active once Finance has done onboarding.
      const { id, patch } = action;
      return { ...state, suppliers: state.suppliers.map(s => s.id === id ? { ...s, ...patch } : s) };
    }
    case 'UPDATE_LINE': {
      const { siteId, lineId, patch } = action;
      const sites = state.order.sites.map(s => {
        if (s.siteId !== siteId) return s;
        return { ...s, lines: s.lines.map(l => l.lineId === lineId ? { ...l, ...patch } : l) };
      });
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites } };
    }
    case 'UPDATE_LINE_CODING': {
      const { siteId, lineId, codingPatch } = action;
      const sites = state.order.sites.map(s => {
        if (s.siteId !== siteId) return s;
        return { ...s, lines: s.lines.map(l => l.lineId === lineId ? { ...l, coding: { ...l.coding, ...codingPatch } } : l) };
      });
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites } };
    }
    case 'REMOVE_LINE': {
      const { siteId, lineId } = action;
      const sites = state.order.sites
        .map(s => s.siteId === siteId ? { ...s, lines: s.lines.filter(l => l.lineId !== lineId) } : s)
        .filter(s => s.lines.length > 0);
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites } };
    }
    case 'DUPLICATE_LINE': {
      const { siteId, lineId } = action;
      const sites = state.order.sites.map(s => {
        if (s.siteId !== siteId) return s;
        const idx = s.lines.findIndex(l => l.lineId === lineId);
        if (idx < 0) return s;
        const dup = { ...s.lines[idx], lineId: uid('LN') };
        const lines = [...s.lines.slice(0, idx + 1), dup, ...s.lines.slice(idx + 1)];
        return { ...s, lines };
      });
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites } };
    }
    case 'TOGGLE_SITE_COLLAPSE': {
      const sites = state.order.sites.map(s => s.siteId === action.siteId ? { ...s, collapsed: !s.collapsed } : s);
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites } };
    }
    case 'SET_ALL_SITES_COLLAPSED': {
      // Master collapse/expand. action.collapsed: boolean.
      const sites = state.order.sites.map(s => ({ ...s, collapsed: action.collapsed }));
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites } };
    }
    case 'MOVE_LINE_TO_SITE': {
      // Move a line between site groups when the user changes its Site column.
      // Removes from the source group (drops group if it becomes empty), creates
      // the target group if needed, updates line.coding to match the new site:
      //   · legalEntity → target site's LE
      //   · outlet      → target site's default outlet
      //   · dept/CC/GL  → derived from the default outlet (so the line stays valid)
      // The user can override outlet/dept/CC/GL afterwards via the coding columns.
      const { sourceSiteId, lineId, targetSiteId } = action;
      if (sourceSiteId === targetSiteId) return state;
      const sourceIdx = state.order.sites.findIndex(s => s.siteId === sourceSiteId);
      if (sourceIdx < 0) return state;
      const sourceEntry = state.order.sites[sourceIdx];
      const line = sourceEntry.lines.find(l => l.lineId === lineId);
      if (!line) return state;
      const targetMaster = state.sites.find(s => s.siteId === targetSiteId);
      if (!targetMaster) return state;
      const defaultOutlet = targetMaster.outlets?.find(o => o.isDefault) || targetMaster.outlets?.[0];
      // Rewrite the line's coding for the new site
      const newLine = {
        ...line,
        coding: {
          legalEntity: targetMaster.legalEntity,
          outlet:      defaultOutlet?.outletId || '',
          dept:        defaultOutlet?.dept || '',
          costCentre:  defaultOutlet?.cc || '',
          glAccount:   defaultOutlet?.defaultGL || ''
        }
      };
      // Remove from source
      let sites = state.order.sites.map(s =>
        s.siteId === sourceSiteId
          ? { ...s, lines: s.lines.filter(l => l.lineId !== lineId) }
          : s
      );
      // Drop empty source group
      sites = sites.filter(s => s.lines.length > 0 || s.siteId === targetSiteId);
      // Add to target group (create if missing)
      const targetIdx = sites.findIndex(s => s.siteId === targetSiteId);
      if (targetIdx >= 0) {
        sites = sites.map(s => s.siteId === targetSiteId ? { ...s, lines: [...s.lines, newLine] } : s);
      } else {
        sites.push({
          siteId: targetSiteId,
          collapsed: false,
          areaMasterCollapsed: false,
          areaMaster: { ...targetMaster.defaults, legalEntity: targetMaster.legalEntity },
          lines: [newLine]
        });
      }
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites } };
    }
    case 'TOGGLE_AM_COLLAPSE': {
      const sites = state.order.sites.map(s => s.siteId === action.siteId ? { ...s, areaMasterCollapsed: !s.areaMasterCollapsed } : s);
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites } };
    }
    case 'UPDATE_AREA_MASTER': {
      const { siteId, patch } = action;
      const sites = state.order.sites.map(s => s.siteId === siteId ? { ...s, areaMaster: { ...s.areaMaster, ...patch } } : s);
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites } };
    }
    case 'TOGGLE_AGENT': {
      return { ...state, agent: { ...state.agent, open: action.open ?? !state.agent.open } };
    }
    case 'AGENT_MESSAGE_ADD': {
      return { ...state, agent: { ...state.agent, messages: [...state.agent.messages, action.message] } };
    }
    case 'AGENT_TYPING': {
      return { ...state, agent: { ...state.agent, typing: !!action.typing } };
    }
    case 'AGENT_SUGGESTION_ADD': {
      return { ...state, agent: { ...state.agent, pendingSuggestions: [...state.agent.pendingSuggestions, action.suggestion] } };
    }
    case 'AGENT_SUGGESTION_RESOLVE': {
      const filtered = state.agent.pendingSuggestions.filter(s => s.id !== action.id);
      return { ...state, agent: { ...state.agent, pendingSuggestions: filtered } };
    }
    case 'ACCEPT_LINE_SUGGESTION': {
      // Apply agent's suggested coding to the line and mark accepted
      const sites = state.order.sites.map(s => {
        if (s.siteId !== action.siteId) return s;
        const lines = s.lines.map(l => {
          if (l.lineId !== action.lineId) return l;
          if (!l.agentSuggestion) return l;
          const { confidence, reasoning, ...codingOnly } = l.agentSuggestion;
          return { ...l, coding: { ...l.coding, ...codingOnly }, agentSuggestionStatus: 'accepted' };
        });
        return { ...s, lines };
      });
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites } };
    }
    case 'DISMISS_LINE_SUGGESTION': {
      const sites = state.order.sites.map(s => {
        if (s.siteId !== action.siteId) return s;
        const lines = s.lines.map(l => {
          if (l.lineId !== action.lineId) return l;
          return { ...l, agentSuggestionStatus: 'dismissed' };
        });
        return { ...s, lines };
      });
      return { ...state, order: { ...state.order, sites } };
    }
    case 'SUBMIT_ORDER': {
      const order = { ...state.order, status: 'submitted', submittedAt: nowIso() };
      // events: array emitted at submit — one ORDER + N RFQ + M REQUISITION.
      // Append-only ledger; prepend so newest events show first.
      // ledgerRow fallback kept for backward compat with any caller still
      // dispatching the pre-refactor single-row payload.
      const events = action.events || (action.ledgerRow ? [action.ledgerRow] : []);
      const ledger = [...events, ...state.ledger];
      return { ...state, order, ledger };
    }

    /* ---------- RFQ lifecycle (Phase 2) ----------
       Per spec frame 2 (RFQ): pending → quoted → accepted (creates Requisition)
       / rejected / timed_out. Each transition updates the existing event in place
       except RFQ_ACCEPT which also emits a new REQUISITION event with the RFQ as
       parent (◂ RFQ in the lineage). The ledger remains append-only at the event
       level — status updates mutate the row, never overwrite history; a full audit
       trail layer can be added later if forensics is needed. */
    case 'SUPPLIER_ONBOARD_MINIMUM': {
      // Captures the minimum supplier contact info needed to send an RFQ to them.
      // Status transitions: pending_onboarding → minimal_onboarded.
      // Full vendor onboarding (bank, contract, payment terms) happens in the next
      // sprint — this lets the operator unblock RFQs without finishing every field.
      const { supplierId, email, name } = action;
      const suppliers = state.suppliers.map(s =>
        s.id === supplierId
          ? { ...s, email: email || s.email, name: name || s.name, status: 'minimal_onboarded' }
          : s
      );
      return { ...state, suppliers };
    }
    case 'RFQ_SEND': {
      // Marks a batch of RFQ events as sent. action.eventIds is an array — the
      // batch is collapsed by (LE, Site, Supplier) and dispatched together via
      // the RFQ-out preview modal. Each event gets sentAt + validityBy.
      // The rfqOutDocument snapshot stores the aggregated supplier-facing doc.
      const { eventIds, validityBy, rfqOutDocument } = action;
      const sentAt = nowIso();
      const idSet = new Set(eventIds);
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (!idSet.has(e.eventId)) return e;
        if (String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.RFQ) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'pending') return e;
        return { ...e, status: 'sent', sentAt, validityBy, rfqOutDocument };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'RFQ_RECORD_QUOTE': {
      // action.eventId, action.quote: { unitPrice, currency, validUntil, supplierResponse, notes, receivedAt }
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId) return e;
        if (String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.RFQ) return e;
        return { ...e, status: 'quoted', quote: action.quote };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'RFQ_ACCEPT': {
      // Accept the quote on an RFQ → create a new single-line REQUISITION event
      // with the RFQ as parent. The Req inherits coding, supplier, site, LE from
      // the RFQ; unit price comes from the accepted quote.
      const rfqEvent = state.ledger.find(e => e.eventId === action.eventId);
      if (!rfqEvent || !rfqEvent.quote) return state;
      const quotedPrice = rfqEvent.quote.unitPrice;
      const lineNet = rfqEvent.line.qty * quotedPrice;
      const lineTax = lineNet * ((rfqEvent.line.vatPct || 0) / 100);
      const existingReqCount = selectRequisitionEvents(state.ledger).length;
      const reqEvent = {
        eventId: uid('EVT'),
        eventType: EVENT_TYPE.REQUISITION,
        parentEventId: action.eventId,  // ◂ RFQ (not the order — accepted-quote path)
        timestamp: nowIso(),
        status: 'draft',
        requisitionId: newReqId(existingReqCount + 1),
        legalEntity: rfqEvent.legalEntity,
        siteId: rfqEvent.siteId,
        siteName: rfqEvent.siteName,
        supplier: rfqEvent.supplier,
        partitionKey: `${rfqEvent.legalEntity}__${rfqEvent.siteId}__${rfqEvent.supplier}`,
        lines: [{
          product: rfqEvent.line.product,
          sku: rfqEvent.line.sku,
          qty: rfqEvent.line.qty,
          uom: rfqEvent.line.uom,
          unitPrice: quotedPrice,
          vatPct: rfqEvent.line.vatPct,
          net: lineNet,
          tax: lineTax,
          gross: lineNet + lineTax,
          supplier: rfqEvent.supplier,
          coding: rfqEvent.line.coding,
          codingString: rfqEvent.line.codingString,
          projectCode: rfqEvent.line.projectCode,
          serviceTerm: rfqEvent.line.serviceTerm,
          treatment: rfqEvent.line.treatment,
          catalogueStatus: 'Quote-Accepted'  // marker — line originated from accepted RFQ
        }],
        netTotal: lineNet,
        taxTotal: lineTax,
        grossTotal: lineNet + lineTax,
        budgetStatus: deriveBudgetStatus(lineNet),
        approvalFlow: null,
        poEventId: null,
        requester: rfqEvent.requester
      };
      const updated = state.ledger.map(e =>
        e.eventId === action.eventId
          ? { ...e, status: 'accepted', acceptedAt: nowIso(), linkedRequisitionEventId: reqEvent.eventId, linkedRequisitionId: reqEvent.requisitionId }
          : e
      );
      return { ...state, ledger: [reqEvent, ...updated] };
    }
    case 'RFQ_REJECT': {
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e =>
        e.eventId === action.eventId && String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.RFQ
          ? { ...e, status: 'rejected', rejectedAt: nowIso(), rejectionReason: action.reason || '' }
          : e
      );
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'RFQ_TIMEOUT': {
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e =>
        e.eventId === action.eventId && String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.RFQ
          ? { ...e, status: 'timed_out', timedOutAt: nowIso() }
          : e
      );
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }

    /* ---------- REQUISITION lifecycle ----------
       Operator path: draft → (edit lines) → pending_approval → approved | rejected | sent_back
       Approved Requisition spawns a PO event with parentEventId = reqEvent.eventId.
       The PO inherits coding/supplier/site/lines from the Req and starts in 'draft'
       state ready to dispatch. PO_SEND_TO_SUPPLIER flips it to 'sent'.

       Edits are line-level: qty, unitPrice, coding patch. Each edit triggers a
       recompute of net/tax/gross at the line AND at the requisition totals. The
       original orderLine (pre-edit) is kept on the line so the detail panel can
       surface "changed from X" annotations.
    */
    case 'REQ_EDIT_LINE': {
      const { eventId, lineIdx, patch } = action;
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.REQUISITION) return e;
        // Editable by the requester in draft/sent_back, AND by the approver
        // while pending_approval (an approver adjustment). Approved/rejected
        // are locked.
        const requesterEdit = e.status === 'draft' || e.status === 'sent_back';
        const approverEdit  = e.status === 'pending_approval';
        if (!requesterEdit && !approverEdit) return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== lineIdx) return l;
          // Snapshot the original values once, then preserve them across subsequent edits
          const original = l.originalLine || { qty: l.qty, unitPrice: l.unitPrice, coding: { ...l.coding } };
          const merged = { ...l, ...patch, originalLine: original };
          if (patch.coding) {
            merged.coding = { ...l.coding, ...patch.coding };
            merged.codingString = `${merged.coding.legalEntity} · ${e.siteId} · ${merged.coding.outlet} · ${merged.coding.dept} · ${merged.coding.costCentre} · ${merged.coding.glAccount}`;
          }
          // Recompute monetary fields
          merged.net   = merged.qty * merged.unitPrice;
          merged.tax   = merged.net * ((merged.vatPct || 0) / 100);
          merged.gross = merged.net + merged.tax;
          return merged;
        });
        const netTotal   = lines.reduce((s, l) => s + l.net, 0);
        const taxTotal   = lines.reduce((s, l) => s + l.tax, 0);
        const grossTotal = netTotal + taxTotal;
        // Flag approver adjustments so REQ_APPROVE knows not to auto-send.
        const approverEdited = e.approverEdited || approverEdit;
        return { ...e, lines, netTotal, taxTotal, grossTotal, approverEdited, budgetStatus: deriveBudgetStatus(netTotal) };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'REQ_OVERRIDE_LINE_CODING': {
      // Coding-only override that's allowed up to (but not including) approval.
      // Permission-gated at the UI layer via state.user.permissions.canEditCoding.
      // Unlike REQ_EDIT_LINE this works in `pending_approval` status too — a
      // designated coder can fix a category without unwinding the approval.
      const { eventId, lineIdx, coding } = action;
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.REQUISITION) return e;
        if (e.status === 'approved' || e.status === 'rejected') return e;  // locked once approved
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== lineIdx) return l;
          const merged = { ...l };
          merged.coding = { ...l.coding, ...coding };
          merged.codingString = `${merged.coding.legalEntity} · ${e.siteId} · ${merged.coding.outlet || '—'} · ${merged.coding.dept} · ${merged.coding.costCentre} · ${merged.coding.glAccount}`;
          merged.codingOverridden = true;
          merged.codingOverriddenAt = nowIso();
          return merged;
        });
        return { ...e, lines };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'REQ_SUBMIT_FOR_APPROVAL': {
      // Operator submits the Requisition for internal approval. Status: draft → pending_approval.
      // Approval rules system lands next sprint — for now any approver can act.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.REQUISITION) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'draft' && e.status !== 'sent_back') return e;
        return {
          ...e,
          status: 'pending_approval',
          submittedForApprovalAt: nowIso(),
          approvalFlow: { stages: [{ name: 'Approver', state: 'pending' }], currentStage: 0 }
        };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'REQ_SEND_BACK': {
      // Approver returns the Req to the operator for revision. Status: pending_approval → sent_back.
      // Operator edits and re-submits.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.REQUISITION) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'pending_approval') return e;
        return { ...e, status: 'sent_back', sentBackAt: nowIso(), sentBackReason: action.reason || '', approverEdited: false };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'REQ_REJECT_BY_APPROVER': {
      // Approver fully rejects (Req closed, no PO emitted). Status: pending_approval → rejected.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.REQUISITION) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'pending_approval') return e;
        return { ...e, status: 'rejected', rejectedAt: nowIso(), rejectionReason: action.reason || '' };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'REQ_APPROVE': {
      // Approver approves → status flips to 'approved' AND a PO event is emitted.
      // PO inherits lines/coding/supplier/site/LE from the Req. parentEventId on
      // the PO points back to the Req for lineage. The Req's poEventId is set so
      // the detail panel can show the linked PO.
      const reqEvent = state.ledger.find(e => e.eventId === action.eventId);
      if (!reqEvent || String(reqEvent.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.REQUISITION) return state;
      if (reqEvent.status !== 'pending_approval') return state;

      const existingPoCount = selectPOEvents(state.ledger).length;
      const poId = `PO-2026-${String(existingPoCount + 1).padStart(4, '0')}`;
      const approverName = action.approverName || 'Approver';
      const nowTs = nowIso();
      // Clean approval = approver made no edits during review. Clean → auto-send
      // to supplier; edited → hold for the requester to review and send.
      const cleanApproval = !reqEvent.approverEdited;
      const poEvent = {
        eventId: uid('EVT'),
        eventType: EVENT_TYPE.PO,
        parentEventId: reqEvent.eventId,
        timestamp: nowTs,
        // Option A: PO is created already approved. The req approval is the
        // commit decision — re-approving the PO that mirrors the req lines is
        // redundant.
        //
        // Auto-send on clean approval: if the approver did NOT change anything,
        // the PO goes straight to the supplier (status 'sent'). If the approver
        // adjusted the requisition, we hold the PO at 'po_approved' so the
        // requester (Flo) can review the changes and send it manually.
        status: cleanApproval ? 'sent' : 'po_approved',
        poApprovedAt: nowTs,
        poApprovedBy: approverName,
        poApprovalNote: cleanApproval ? 'Auto-approved & sent (clean approval)' : 'Approved with approver edits — held for requester to send',
        poId,
        legalEntity: reqEvent.legalEntity,
        siteId: reqEvent.siteId,
        siteName: reqEvent.siteName,
        supplier: reqEvent.supplier,
        supplierId: reqEvent.supplierId,
        partitionKey: reqEvent.partitionKey,
        lines: reqEvent.lines.map(l => ({
          ...l,
          confirmedQty: null,            // populated on supplier confirmation
          confirmedUnitPrice: null,      // populated if supplier confirms a different unit price
          confirmationStatus: 'line_pending'     // line_pending | line_confirmed | line_partial | line_rejected
        })),
        netTotal: reqEvent.netTotal,
        taxTotal: reqEvent.taxTotal,
        grossTotal: reqEvent.grossTotal,
        requisitionEventId: reqEvent.eventId,
        requisitionId: reqEvent.requisitionId,
        requester: reqEvent.requester,
        sentAt: cleanApproval ? nowTs : null,
        sentBy: cleanApproval ? 'Auto-sent on clean approval' : null,
        confirmedAt: null
      };
      const updated = state.ledger.map(e =>
        e.eventId === action.eventId
          ? lockCommentsAtStage({ ...e, status: 'approved', approvedAt: nowIso(), approvedBy: action.approverName || 'Approver', poEventId: poEvent.eventId, poId }, 'requisition')
          : e
      );
      return { ...state, ledger: [poEvent, ...updated] };
    }

    /* ---------- PO lifecycle ----------
       Approved Req → PO event (status: draft) → operator can edit → submit for
       PO approval → approver acts (approve / send back / reject) → operator
       sends approved PO to supplier (status: sent) → supplier confirms full,
       partial, or rejects.

       PO approval mirrors Requisition approval but acts as a second control
       point — useful when PO value is amended after Req approval, or when a
       different role signs off on the supplier-facing commit. */
    case 'PO_EDIT_LINE': {
      const { eventId, lineIdx, patch } = action;
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'draft' && e.status !== 'po_sent_back') return e;  // approved/sent/acked are locked
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== lineIdx) return l;
          // Snapshot original values once for the diff display
          const original = l.originalLine || { qty: l.qty, unitPrice: l.unitPrice, coding: { ...l.coding } };
          const merged = { ...l, ...patch, originalLine: original };
          if (patch.coding) {
            merged.coding = { ...l.coding, ...patch.coding };
            merged.codingString = `${merged.coding.legalEntity} · ${e.siteId} · ${merged.coding.outlet} · ${merged.coding.dept} · ${merged.coding.costCentre} · ${merged.coding.glAccount}`;
          }
          merged.net   = merged.qty * merged.unitPrice;
          merged.tax   = merged.net * ((merged.vatPct || 0) / 100);
          merged.gross = merged.net + merged.tax;
          return merged;
        });
        const netTotal   = lines.reduce((s, l) => s + l.net, 0);
        const taxTotal   = lines.reduce((s, l) => s + l.tax, 0);
        const grossTotal = netTotal + taxTotal;
        return { ...e, lines, netTotal, taxTotal, grossTotal };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'PO_OVERRIDE_LINE_CODING': {
      // Coding-only override that's allowed up to (but not including) PO approval.
      // Permission-gated at the UI layer via state.user.permissions.canEditCoding.
      // Works in `po_pending_approval` too — useful when an approver spots a
      // coding error and wants to fix without bouncing the PO back to the buyer.
      const { eventId, lineIdx, coding } = action;
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        if (e.status === 'po_approved' || e.status === 'sent' ||
            e.status === 'confirmation_full' || e.status === 'confirmation_partial' ||
            e.status === 'received_partial' || e.status === 'received_full' ||
            e.status === 'po_rejected' || e.status === 'rejected_by_supplier') return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== lineIdx) return l;
          const merged = { ...l };
          merged.coding = { ...l.coding, ...coding };
          merged.codingString = `${merged.coding.legalEntity} · ${e.siteId} · ${merged.coding.outlet || '—'} · ${merged.coding.dept} · ${merged.coding.costCentre} · ${merged.coding.glAccount}`;
          merged.codingOverridden = true;
          merged.codingOverriddenAt = nowIso();
          return merged;
        });
        return { ...e, lines };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'PO_SUBMIT_FOR_APPROVAL': {
      // Operator submits the PO for internal approval. Status: draft / po_sent_back → po_pending_approval.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'draft' && e.status !== 'po_sent_back') return e;
        return {
          ...e,
          status: 'po_pending_approval',
          poSubmittedForApprovalAt: nowIso(),
          poApprovalFlow: { stages: [{ name: 'PO Approver', state: 'pending' }], currentStage: 0 }
        };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'PO_APPROVAL_RECODE_LINE': {
      // Approver overrides the coding on a single PO line before approving.
      // The coding stays on the line; audit trail captures the override.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== action.lineIdx) return l;
          const merged = { ...l, coding: { ...l.coding, ...action.patch } };
          merged.codingOverridden = true;
          merged.codingOverriddenAt = nowIso();
          merged.codingOverriddenBy = 'approver';
          return merged;
        });
        return { ...e, lines };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }

    case 'PO_LINE_SET_SPLITS': {
      // Approver defines cost-allocation splits for a line. Each split has:
      //   { id, label, pct, coding: { dept, costCentre, glAccount, outlet } }
      // Percentages must sum to 100. The journal generator expands one line
      // into N Dr legs — one per split — weighted by pct.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== action.lineIdx) return l;
          return { ...l, splits: action.splits, splitMode: action.splits && action.splits.length > 1 };
        });
        return { ...e, lines };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }

    case 'INVOICE_APPROVAL_RECODE_LINE': {
      // Approver overrides coding on a single invoice line before approving.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE) return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== action.lineIdx) return l;
          return { ...l, coding: { ...l.coding, ...action.patch },
            codingOverridden: true, codingOverriddenAt: nowIso(), codingOverriddenBy: 'approver' };
        });
        return { ...e, lines };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }

    case 'INVOICE_LINE_SET_SPLITS': {
      // Same split-allocation logic as PO, applied at invoice approval.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE) return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== action.lineIdx) return l;
          return { ...l, splits: action.splits, splitMode: action.splits && action.splits.length > 1 };
        });
        return { ...e, lines };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }

    case 'PO_APPROVE': {
      // Approver clears the PO for dispatch. Status: po_pending_approval → po_approved.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'po_pending_approval') return e;
        return { ...e, status: 'po_approved', poApprovedAt: nowIso(), poApprovedBy: action.approverName || 'Approver' };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'PO_SEND_BACK': {
      // Approver returns the PO to the operator for revision. Status: po_pending_approval → po_sent_back.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'po_pending_approval') return e;
        return { ...e, status: 'po_sent_back', poSentBackAt: nowIso(), poSentBackReason: action.reason || '' };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'PO_REJECT_BY_APPROVER': {
      // Approver fully rejects (PO closed, never sent to supplier). Status: po_pending_approval → po_rejected.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'po_pending_approval') return e;
        return { ...e, status: 'po_rejected', poRejectedAt: nowIso(), poRejectionReason: action.reason || '' };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'PO_SEND_TO_SUPPLIER': {
      // A PO may only reach a supplier after it has passed PO approval.
      // Status must be po_approved — the previous draft→sent express path is
      // closed so dispatch can't skip the approval gate.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'po_approved') return e;
        return lockCommentsAtStage({ ...e, status: 'sent', sentAt: nowIso(), sentBy: action.sentBy || 'Requester' }, 'po');
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'SUPPLIER_ISSUE_INVOICE': {
      // Supplier issues an invoice from the supplier portal for a confirmed
      // PO. We mirror the PO lines into an INVOICE event with status
      // 'pending_match' so the customer's matching queue picks it up. The
      // invoice carries supplierIdentity stamped to the supplier user.
      const po = state.ledger.find(e => e.eventId === action.poEventId);
      if (!po || String(po.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return state;
      const alreadyHasInvoice = state.ledger.some(e =>
        String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE &&
        (e.poEventId === po.eventId || e.poId === po.poId)
      );
      if (alreadyHasInvoice) return state;
      const invoiceCount = state.ledger.filter(e => String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE).length;
      const invoiceId = `INV-2026-${String(invoiceCount + 1).padStart(4, '0')}`;
      const invLines = (po.lines || []).map(l => {
        // Use confirmedQty if partial; else qty
        const q = (l.confirmedQty != null) ? l.confirmedQty : l.qty;
        const unit = l.confirmedUnitPrice ?? l.unitPrice ?? l.price ?? 0;
        const net = q * unit;
        const tax = net * ((l.vatPct ?? l.vat ?? 0) / 100);
        return {
          product: l.name || l.product,
          sku: l.sku,
          qty: q,
          uom: l.uom,
          unitPrice: unit,
          vatPct: l.vatPct ?? l.vat ?? 0,
          net,
          tax,
          gross: net + tax,
          matchedTo: null,  // populated downstream during matching
        };
      });
      const net = invLines.reduce((s, l) => s + l.net, 0);
      const tax = invLines.reduce((s, l) => s + l.tax, 0);
      const inv = {
        eventId: uid('EVT'),
        eventType: EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE,
        parentEventId: po.eventId,
        timestamp: nowIso(),
        status: 'pending_match',
        invoiceId,
        invoiceNumber: invoiceId,
        supplier: po.supplier,
        supplierId: po.supplierId,
        poEventId: po.eventId,
        poId: po.poId,
        siteId: po.siteId,
        siteName: po.siteName,
        legalEntity: po.legalEntity,
        lines: invLines,
        netTotal: net,
        taxTotal: tax,
        grossTotal: net + tax,
        issuedBy: action.issuedBy || 'Supplier',
        comments: [],
      };
      return { ...state, ledger: [inv, ...state.ledger] };
    }

    case 'PO_CONFIRM_FULL': {
      // Supplier confirms every line at the asked qty and price.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'sent') return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map(l => ({
          ...l, confirmedQty: l.qty, confirmedUnitPrice: l.unitPrice, confirmationStatus: 'line_confirmed'
        }));
        return { ...e, lines, status: 'confirmation_full', confirmedAt: nowIso(), confirmedBy: action.confirmedBy || e.confirmedBy || null };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'PO_CONFIRM_PARTIAL': {
      // Supplier confirms reduced quantities. action.lineAcks: array of
      // { lineIdx, confirmedQty } — lines not in the array default to qty 0 (declined).
      const ackMap = new Map((action.lineAcks || []).map(a => [a.lineIdx, a]));
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'sent') return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          const ack = ackMap.get(i);
          const confirmedQty = ack ? Math.max(0, Math.min(l.qty, ack.confirmedQty)) : 0;
          const confirmedUnitPrice = ack?.confirmedUnitPrice ?? l.unitPrice;
          let confirmationStatus = 'line_rejected';
          if (confirmedQty === l.qty) confirmationStatus = 'line_confirmed';
          else if (confirmedQty > 0) confirmationStatus = 'line_partial';
          return { ...l, confirmedQty, confirmedUnitPrice, confirmationStatus };
        });
        return { ...e, lines, status: 'confirmation_partial', confirmedAt: nowIso(), confirmedBy: action.confirmedBy || e.confirmedBy || null };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'PO_REJECT_BY_SUPPLIER': {
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'sent') return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map(l => ({ ...l, confirmedQty: 0, confirmationStatus: 'line_rejected' }));
        return { ...e, lines, status: 'rejected_by_supplier', confirmedAt: nowIso(), rejectionReason: action.reason || '' };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }

    /* ---------- Gap-decision cases ----------
       After a partial ack, each gap line needs an operator decision.
       action.lineIdx targets a specific line; action.reason is optional.
       When every gap line on a PO has a decision, the PO auto-transitions
       to confirmation_resolved — the GRN module only reads that status. */

    case 'PO_LINE_GAP_ACCEPT': {
      // Gap accepted: committed qty becomes confirmedQty. Budget commitment releases
      // the delta. GRN and invoice match both use confirmedQty as the new baseline.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== action.lineIdx) return l;
          return { ...l, gapDecision: 'accept', gapDecidedAt: nowIso(),
            gapDecisionReason: action.reason || null,
            agentProposal: l.agentProposal || null };
        });
        const allResolved = lines.every(l =>
          l.confirmationStatus === 'line_confirmed' || l.gapDecision !== null
        );
        return { ...e, lines, status: allResolved ? 'confirmation_resolved' : e.status };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }

    case 'PO_LINE_GAP_BACKORDER': {
      // Gap backordered: line splits into delivered (confirmedQty) + pending (gap qty).
      // Both portions share the same original line — the pending portion is
      // tracked as a `backorderPending` field rather than a new line event,
      // keeping PO lineage intact. GRN will expect confirmedQty for the initial
      // delivery; a second GRN event covers the backorder arrival.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== action.lineIdx) return l;
          const gap = (l.qty || 0) - (l.confirmedQty || 0);
          return { ...l, gapDecision: 'backorder', gapDecidedAt: nowIso(),
            gapDecisionReason: action.reason || null,
            backorderQty: gap,
            backorderExpectedDate: action.expectedDeliveryDate || null };
        });
        const allResolved = lines.every(l =>
          l.confirmationStatus === 'line_confirmed' || l.gapDecision !== null
        );
        return { ...e, lines, status: allResolved ? 'confirmation_resolved' : e.status };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }

    case 'PO_LINE_GAP_RETENDER': {
      // Re-tender: this line closes at confirmedQty (same as accept). A new RFQ event
      // is spawned for the gap qty, linked back to this PO via gapSourceEventId.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        const targetLine = e.lines[action.lineIdx];
        if (!targetLine) return e;
        const gap = (targetLine.qty || 0) - (targetLine.confirmedQty || 0);
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== action.lineIdx) return l;
          return { ...l, gapDecision: 'retender', gapDecidedAt: nowIso(),
            gapDecisionReason: action.reason || null };
        });
        const allResolved = lines.every(l =>
          l.confirmationStatus === 'line_confirmed' || l.gapDecision !== null
        );
        const updatedPo = { ...e, lines, status: allResolved ? 'confirmation_resolved' : e.status };
        // Spawn re-tender RFQ event for the gap qty
        const retenderRfq = {
          eventId: `EVT-RETENDER-${e.eventId}-${action.lineIdx}`,
          eventType: EVENT_TYPE.RFQ,
          parentEventId: e.parentEventId || e.eventId,
          gapSourceEventId: e.eventId,
          gapSourceLineIdx: action.lineIdx,
          timestamp: nowIso(),
          rfqId: `RFQ-RETENDER-${e.poId}-L${action.lineIdx + 1}`,
          status: 'pending',
          siteId: e.siteId, siteName: e.siteName, legalEntity: e.legalEntity,
          supplier: null,
          line: {
            product: targetLine.product, sku: targetLine.sku,
            qty: gap, uom: targetLine.uom,
            targetPrice: targetLine.unitPrice,
            catalogueStatus: 'Catalogue',
            coding: targetLine.coding, codingString: targetLine.codingString
          },
          isGapRetender: true,
          note: `Re-tender: gap from ${e.poId} line ${action.lineIdx + 1} — ${targetLine.product} (${gap} ${targetLine.uom} short)`
        };
        return [...state.ledger.filter(ev => ev.eventId !== e.eventId), updatedPo, retenderRfq];
      });
      // ledger map returns nested arrays when retender fires — flatten
      const flatLedger = ledger.flat ? ledger.flat() : [].concat(...ledger);
      return { ...state, ledger: flatLedger };
    }

    case 'PO_LINE_GAP_REJECT': {
      // Reject entire line: cancelled from this PO. New RFQ spawned at
      // original full qty (not just the gap) so the whole need is re-sourced.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        const targetLine = e.lines[action.lineIdx];
        if (!targetLine) return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== action.lineIdx) return l;
          return { ...l, gapDecision: 'reject', gapDecidedAt: nowIso(),
            gapDecisionReason: action.reason || null };
        });
        const allResolved = lines.every(l =>
          l.confirmationStatus === 'line_confirmed' || l.gapDecision !== null
        );
        const updatedPo = { ...e, lines, status: allResolved ? 'confirmation_resolved' : e.status };
        const rejectRfq = {
          eventId: `EVT-REJECT-${e.eventId}-${action.lineIdx}`,
          eventType: EVENT_TYPE.RFQ,
          parentEventId: e.parentEventId || e.eventId,
          gapSourceEventId: e.eventId,
          gapSourceLineIdx: action.lineIdx,
          timestamp: nowIso(),
          rfqId: `RFQ-REJECT-${e.poId}-L${action.lineIdx + 1}`,
          status: 'pending',
          siteId: e.siteId, siteName: e.siteName, legalEntity: e.legalEntity,
          supplier: null,
          line: {
            product: targetLine.product, sku: targetLine.sku,
            qty: targetLine.qty, uom: targetLine.uom,
            targetPrice: targetLine.unitPrice,
            catalogueStatus: 'Catalogue',
            coding: targetLine.coding, codingString: targetLine.codingString
          },
          isGapRetender: true,
          note: `Re-tender (full): line rejected from ${e.poId} — ${targetLine.product}`
        };
        return [...state.ledger.filter(ev => ev.eventId !== e.eventId), updatedPo, rejectRfq];
      });
      const flatLedger = ledger.flat ? ledger.flat() : [].concat(...ledger);
      return { ...state, ledger: flatLedger };
    }

    case 'PO_REJECTED_RETENDER': {
      // Whole PO rejected — spawn a new RFQ for every line at full original qty.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        return { ...e, status: 'cancelled', cancellationReason: 'rejected_by_supplier_retendered', resolvedAt: nowIso() };
      });
      const po = state.ledger.find(e => e.eventId === action.eventId);
      const newRfqs = (po?.lines || []).map((l, i) => ({
        eventId: `EVT-REJRET-${action.eventId}-${i}`,
        eventType: EVENT_TYPE.RFQ,
        parentEventId: po.parentEventId || po.eventId,
        gapSourceEventId: po.eventId,
        timestamp: nowIso(),
        rfqId: `RFQ-REJRET-${po.poId}-L${i + 1}`,
        status: 'pending',
        siteId: po.siteId, siteName: po.siteName, legalEntity: po.legalEntity,
        supplier: null,
        line: { product: l.product, sku: l.sku, qty: l.qty, uom: l.uom,
          targetPrice: l.unitPrice, catalogueStatus: 'Catalogue',
          coding: l.coding, codingString: l.codingString },
        isGapRetender: true,
        note: `Re-tender: full PO ${po.poId} rejected by ${po.supplier}`
      }));
      return { ...state, ledger: [...ledger, ...newRfqs] };
    }

    case 'PO_REJECTED_CANCEL': {
      // Whole PO rejected — cancel demand, no re-sourcing.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.eventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return e;
        return { ...e, status: 'cancelled', cancellationReason: 'rejected_by_supplier_cancelled', resolvedAt: nowIso() };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }

    /* ---------- GRN lifecycle ----------
       A PO becomes eligible for goods receipt once the supplier confirms
       (full or partial). One PO can have multiple GRN events — partial
       deliveries against the same PO are common in hospitality (e.g. produce
       short-shipped, balance arrives next day).

       Each GRN event references the parent PO. Line shape on the GRN snapshots:
         · orderedQty   — PO line qty at receipt time (immutable on the GRN)
         · confirmedQty       — supplier-confirmed cap (the receivable max)
         · receivedQty  — what physically arrived in this delivery
         · condition    — 'good' | 'damaged' | 'short' (qualitative)
         · notes        — free-text per line
       Cumulative receipts across all GRNs against a PO determine PO status:
         · received_partial — some lines have outstanding qty
         · received_full    — every line's cumulative received >= ack qty
       Once GRN flow connects to invoice match, the GRN events feed the
       three-way reconciliation and the period-end accruals run. */
    case 'GRN_RECORD': {
      const po = state.ledger.find(e => e.eventId === action.poEventId);
      if (!po || String(po.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return state;
      if (po.status !== 'confirmation_full' && po.status !== 'confirmation_partial' && po.status !== 'received_partial') return state;

      // Build the GRN event from the supplied per-line receipts.
      // action.lineReceipts: array of { poLineIdx, receivedQty, condition?, notes? }
      const existingGrnCount = selectGRNEvents(state.ledger).length;
      const grnId = newGrnId(existingGrnCount + 1);
      const grnLines = (action.lineReceipts || [])
        .filter(r => (r.receivedQty || 0) > 0)
        .map(r => {
          const poLine = po.lines[r.poLineIdx];
          return {
            poLineIdx: r.poLineIdx,
            product: poLine.product,
            sku: poLine.sku,
            uom: poLine.uom,
            orderedQty: poLine.qty,
            confirmedQty: poLine.confirmedQty ?? poLine.qty,
            unitPrice: poLine.confirmedUnitPrice ?? poLine.unitPrice,
            receivedQty: Math.max(0, r.receivedQty || 0),
            condition: r.condition || 'good',
            notes: r.notes || '',
            coding: poLine.coding,
            codingString: poLine.codingString
          };
        });
      if (grnLines.length === 0) return state;  // nothing actually received

      const grnEvent = {
        eventId: uid('EVT'),
        eventType: EVENT_TYPE.GRN,
        parentEventId: po.eventId,
        timestamp: nowIso(),
        grnId,
        poId: po.poId,
        poEventId: po.eventId,
        legalEntity: po.legalEntity,
        siteId: po.siteId,
        siteName: po.siteName,
        supplier: po.supplier,
        partitionKey: po.partitionKey,
        lines: grnLines,
        netTotal: grnLines.reduce((s, l) => s + l.receivedQty * l.unitPrice, 0),
        receivedBy: action.receivedBy || 'Operator',
        notes: action.notes || ''
      };

      // Compute cumulative received against PO lines (this GRN plus prior GRNs)
      const priorReceived = grnReceivedTotalsForPo(state.ledger, po.eventId);
      const cumulative = { ...priorReceived };
      grnLines.forEach(l => {
        cumulative[l.poLineIdx] = (cumulative[l.poLineIdx] || 0) + l.receivedQty;
      });
      const fullyReceived = po.lines.every((pl, idx) => {
        const targetQty = pl.confirmedQty ?? pl.qty;
        if (targetQty === 0) return true;  // line was rejected on ack — nothing to receive
        return (cumulative[idx] || 0) >= targetQty;
      });
      const updatedPo = {
        ...po,
        status: fullyReceived ? 'received_full' : 'received_partial',
        lastReceivedAt: nowIso()
      };

      const ledger = [grnEvent, ...state.ledger.map(e => e.eventId === po.eventId ? updatedPo : e)];
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }

    /* ---------- Invoice lifecycle ----------
       Invoices arrive against POs once goods have been received. The match
       workflow walks the operator through:
         · invoice header check (supplier, totals)
         · line-by-line match to PO lines (manual in this pass; agent-assisted next)
         · variance review (qty short/over, price high/low, desc drift)
         · confirm match → status reflects line-level state
         · approve for ERP post once matched cleanly

       Statuses:
         pending_match       — newly received, no matching yet
         partially_matched   — some lines matched, some left
         matched             — every line has a match decision (incl. disputed)
         disputed            — at least one line outside tolerance, operator flagged
         approved_for_post   — ready for journal generation / ERP push
         rejected            — invoice fully rejected (e.g. wrong supplier, duplicate)
    */
    /* ---------- Document ingestion lifecycle ----------
       Incoming invoice / quote docs arrive with agent-extracted data (or
       upload-parsed data) and field-level confidence. The operator verifies,
       optionally corrects, then commits — at which point the doc is converted
       into a first-class INVOICE or QUOTE event in the ledger.

       The document event is preserved (not deleted) with status: 'committed'
       so the lineage (and any original extraction-vs-edit diff) is auditable.

       Doc status lifecycle:
         pending_review        — just arrived, untouched
         in_review             — operator has opened the doc and edited fields
         committed             — operator confirmed, INVOICE/QUOTE event emitted
         rejected              — operator discarded (e.g. duplicate, spam) */
    case 'DOC_EDIT_FIELD': {
      // Edit one field on an incoming doc. Marks it as 'edited' for the diff view.
      // action: { docEventId, path: string e.g. 'header.invoiceDate' or 'lines.0.qty', value }
      const { docEventId, path, value } = action;
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== docEventId) return e;
        if (e.status === 'committed' || e.status === 'rejected') return e;
        // Deep-clone shallowly along the path
        const next = { ...e, extractedData: JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(e.extractedData || {})) };
        // Path resolution: split on '.' and array indices
        const parts = path.split('.');
        let cursor = next.extractedData;
        for (let i = 0; i < parts.length - 1; i++) {
          const k = parts[i];
          if (!(k in cursor)) cursor[k] = {};
          cursor = cursor[k];
        }
        cursor[parts[parts.length - 1]] = value;
        // Mark edited
        const editedFields = new Set(next.editedFields || []);
        editedFields.add(path);
        next.editedFields = [...editedFields];
        next.status = 'in_review';
        // Recompute line nets / header totals if relevant
        if (path.startsWith('lines.')) {
          const lineIdxStr = parts[1];
          const li = parseInt(lineIdxStr, 10);
          const line = next.extractedData.lines?.[li];
          if (line) {
            line.net = (line.qty || 0) * (line.unitPrice || 0);
            line.tax = line.net * ((line.vatPct || 0) / 100);
            line.gross = line.net + line.tax;
          }
          const lines = next.extractedData.lines || [];
          next.extractedData.header = next.extractedData.header || {};
          next.extractedData.header.netTotal = lines.reduce((s, l) => s + (l.net || 0), 0);
          next.extractedData.header.taxTotal = lines.reduce((s, l) => s + (l.tax || 0), 0);
          next.extractedData.header.grossTotal = next.extractedData.header.netTotal + next.extractedData.header.taxTotal;
        }
        return next;
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'DOC_RESET_FIELD': {
      // Revert one field back to the agent's original extraction.
      const { docEventId, path } = action;
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== docEventId) return e;
        if (e.status === 'committed' || e.status === 'rejected') return e;
        const next = { ...e, extractedData: JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(e.extractedData || {})) };
        // Read the original value from agentExtractedRaw
        const parts = path.split('.');
        let raw = e.agentExtractedRaw;
        for (const k of parts) {
          if (raw == null) break;
          raw = raw[k];
        }
        // Re-apply
        let cursor = next.extractedData;
        for (let i = 0; i < parts.length - 1; i++) cursor = cursor[parts[i]];
        cursor[parts[parts.length - 1]] = raw;
        // Remove from edited set
        next.editedFields = (next.editedFields || []).filter(p => p !== path);
        return next;
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'DOC_COMMIT_INVOICE': {
      // Commit an incoming invoice doc → emit a real INVOICE event.
      const doc = state.ledger.find(e => e.eventId === action.docEventId);
      if (!doc || String(doc.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.INCOMING_INVOICE_DOC) return state;
      if (doc.status === 'committed' || doc.status === 'rejected') return state;

      const header = doc.extractedData?.header || {};
      const lines = (doc.extractedData?.lines || []).map((l) => ({
        product: l.product || '',
        sku: l.sku || '',
        qty: l.qty || 0,
        uom: l.uom || 'EA',
        unitPrice: l.unitPrice || 0,
        vatPct: l.vatPct || 0,
        net: l.net || 0,
        tax: l.tax || 0,
        gross: l.gross || 0,
        // Matching — operator fills in via INVOICE_MATCH_LINE
        matchedTo: [],
        matchStatus: 'unmatched',
        coding: l.coding || null
      }));

      const existingInvCount = selectInvoiceEvents(state.ledger).length;
      const invoiceId = newInvoiceId(existingInvCount + 1);

      const invoiceEvent = {
        eventId: uid('EVT'),
        eventType: EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE,
        parentEventId: doc.eventId,  // lineage to the source document
        timestamp: nowIso(),
        receivedAt: doc.receivedAt || doc.timestamp,
        invoiceId,
        supplierInvoiceNumber: header.supplierInvoiceNumber || '—',
        poId: header.poRefInDocument || null,
        poEventId: null,  // assigned during matching, not at intake
        status: 'pending_match',
        legalEntity: header.legalEntity || null,
        siteId: header.siteId || null,
        siteName: header.siteName || null,
        supplierId: doc.supplierId,
        supplier: doc.supplier,
        invoiceDate: header.invoiceDate || nowIso().slice(0, 10),
        dueDate: header.dueDate || null,
        poRefInDocument: header.poRefInDocument || null,
        lines,
        netTotal: header.netTotal || lines.reduce((s, l) => s + l.net, 0),
        taxTotal: header.taxTotal || lines.reduce((s, l) => s + l.tax, 0),
        grossTotal: header.grossTotal || lines.reduce((s, l) => s + l.gross, 0),
        // Audit
        ingestedFrom: { docEventId: doc.eventId, channel: doc.intakeChannel, editedFields: doc.editedFields || [] }
      };

      const ledger = [invoiceEvent, ...state.ledger.map(e =>
        e.eventId === doc.eventId ? { ...e, status: 'committed', committedAt: nowIso(), committedInvoiceEventId: invoiceEvent.eventId } : e
      )];
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'DOC_COMMIT_QUOTE': {
      // Commit an incoming quote doc → emit a real QUOTE event linked to the parent RFQ.
      const doc = state.ledger.find(e => e.eventId === action.docEventId);
      if (!doc || String(doc.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.INCOMING_QUOTE_DOC) return state;
      if (doc.status === 'committed' || doc.status === 'rejected') return state;

      const header = doc.extractedData?.header || {};
      const lines = (doc.extractedData?.lines || []).map((l) => ({
        rfqLineRef: l.rfqLineRef || null,
        product: l.product || '',
        sku: l.sku || '',
        qty: l.qty || 0,
        uom: l.uom || 'EA',
        unitPrice: l.unitPrice || 0,
        leadTimeDays: l.leadTimeDays || null,
        packSize: l.packSize || null,
        moq: l.moq || null,
        net: (l.qty || 0) * (l.unitPrice || 0)
      }));

      const existingQuoteCount = selectQuoteEvents(state.ledger).length;
      const quoteId = newQuoteId(existingQuoteCount + 1);

      const quoteEvent = {
        eventId: uid('EVT'),
        eventType: EVENT_TYPE.QUOTE,
        parentEventId: doc.parentEventId || doc.eventId,  // link to RFQ event
        timestamp: nowIso(),
        receivedAt: doc.receivedAt || doc.timestamp,
        quoteId,
        rfqId: doc.rfqId || header.rfqId || null,
        rfqEventId: doc.parentEventId || null,
        status: 'received',
        supplierId: doc.supplierId,
        supplier: doc.supplier,
        validUntil: header.validUntil || null,
        paymentTerms: header.paymentTerms || null,
        deliveryTerms: header.deliveryTerms || null,
        lines,
        netTotal: lines.reduce((s, l) => s + l.net, 0),
        ingestedFrom: { docEventId: doc.eventId, channel: doc.intakeChannel, editedFields: doc.editedFields || [] }
      };

      const ledger = [quoteEvent, ...state.ledger.map(e =>
        e.eventId === doc.eventId ? { ...e, status: 'committed', committedAt: nowIso(), committedQuoteEventId: quoteEvent.eventId } : e
      )];
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'DOC_REJECT': {
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.docEventId) return e;
        if (e.status === 'committed') return e;
        return { ...e, status: 'rejected', rejectedAt: nowIso(), rejectionReason: action.reason || '' };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'DOC_INGEST_NEW_QUOTE': {
      // Simulate the post-OCR-extraction state after a fresh upload. In
      // production this action would be dispatched by the inbox/upload
      // worker once the OCR pass returned structured extraction. In the
      // wireframe the user drag-drops a file and we synthesise a draft
      // with low confidence + placeholder values to be edited inline.
      //
      // action: { filename, sizeBytes, supplierGuess?, rfqIdGuess? }
      const { filename, sizeBytes, supplierGuess, rfqIdGuess } = action;
      const existingCount = selectIncomingQuoteDocs(state.ledger).length;
      const newDoc = {
        eventId: uid('EVT'),
        eventType: EVENT_TYPE.INCOMING_QUOTE_DOC,
        parentEventId: null,
        timestamp: nowIso(), receivedAt: nowIso(),
        docId: newDocId('QTE', existingCount + 1),
        documentName: filename || 'uploaded-quote.pdf',
        sizeBytes: sizeBytes || null,
        intakeChannel: 'manual_upload',
        intakeEmail: null,
        rfqId: rfqIdGuess || null,
        status: 'pending_review',
        supplierId: supplierGuess?.id || null,
        supplier: supplierGuess?.name || '(unresolved — confirm supplier)',
        extractedData: {
          header: {
            rfqId: rfqIdGuess || '',
            validUntil: '',
            paymentTerms: '',
            deliveryTerms: ''
          },
          lines: []  // empty — operator types in lines or agent fills them post-OCR
        },
        agentExtractedRaw: null,
        editedFields: [],
        // All-low confidence — flags every field for operator review since
        // there's no real OCR running in the wireframe
        confidenceMap: {
          'header.rfqId': 30,
          'header.validUntil': 30,
          'header.paymentTerms': 30,
          'header.deliveryTerms': 30
        },
        agentExtractedAt: null,
        agentNotes: 'Manually uploaded — OCR extraction pending. Confirm supplier, link to an RFQ, and add line items below.',
        wasUploaded: true   // flag to render an "uploaded" badge in the UI
      };
      return { ...state, ledger: [newDoc, ...state.ledger] };
    }
    case 'DOC_INGEST_NEW_INVOICE': {
      // Same simulation pattern as DOC_INGEST_NEW_QUOTE but for invoice docs.
      // Produces an INCOMING_INVOICE_DOC with empty extractedData that the
      // operator fills (or that a production OCR call would populate).
      //
      // action: { filename, sizeBytes, supplierGuess?, poRefGuess? }
      const { filename, sizeBytes, supplierGuess, poRefGuess } = action;
      const existingCount = selectIncomingInvoiceDocs(state.ledger).length;
      const newDoc = {
        eventId: uid('EVT'),
        eventType: EVENT_TYPE.INCOMING_INVOICE_DOC,
        timestamp: nowIso(), receivedAt: nowIso(),
        docId: newDocId('INV', existingCount + 1),
        documentName: filename || 'uploaded-invoice.pdf',
        sizeBytes: sizeBytes || null,
        intakeChannel: 'manual_upload',
        intakeEmail: null,
        status: 'pending_review',
        supplierId: supplierGuess?.id || null,
        supplier: supplierGuess?.name || '(unresolved — confirm supplier)',
        extractedData: {
          header: {
            supplierInvoiceNumber: '',
            invoiceDate: '',
            dueDate: '',
            legalEntity: '',
            siteId: '',
            siteName: '',
            poRefInDocument: poRefGuess || null,
            netTotal: 0, taxTotal: 0, grossTotal: 0
          },
          lines: []
        },
        agentExtractedRaw: null,
        editedFields: [],
        confidenceMap: {
          'header.supplierInvoiceNumber': 30,
          'header.invoiceDate': 30,
          'header.dueDate': 30,
          'header.poRefInDocument': poRefGuess ? 60 : 30,
          'header.netTotal': 30
        },
        agentExtractedAt: null,
        agentNotes: 'Manually uploaded — OCR extraction pending. Confirm supplier, link to a PO, and add line items below.',
        wasUploaded: true
      };
      return { ...state, ledger: [newDoc, ...state.ledger] };
    }

    case 'INVOICE_CREATE_FROM_PO': {
      // Demo intake — generates an invoice that mirrors what the supplier
      // would have sent against a received PO. Builds in small qty/price
      // variances on selected lines so the matching UI has something interesting
      // to surface. The variancePattern argument controls which lines drift.
      // action: { poEventId, variancePattern?: 'clean'|'mixed'|'messy' }
      const po = state.ledger.find(e => e.eventId === action.poEventId);
      if (!po || String(po.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.PO) return state;
      if (po.status !== 'received_full' && po.status !== 'received_partial' &&
          po.status !== 'confirmation_full' && po.status !== 'confirmation_partial') return state;

      const pattern = action.variancePattern || 'mixed';

      // Receipt context — what was actually delivered
      const received = grnReceivedTotalsForPo(state.ledger, po.eventId);

      // Generate invoice lines from the PO ack qty (or received qty if any).
      // Apply variance per pattern.
      const invoiceLines = po.lines.map((poLine, idx) => {
        const confirmedQty = poLine.confirmedQty ?? poLine.qty;
        if (confirmedQty === 0) return null;  // line was rejected on ack — no invoice line
        const recQty = received[idx] ?? confirmedQty;
        let invoiceQty = recQty;
        let invoicePrice = poLine.confirmedUnitPrice ?? poLine.unitPrice;
        if (pattern === 'mixed') {
          // First line: clean. Second: 5% qty short. Third: 3% price high. Others clean.
          if (idx === 1)      invoiceQty = +(recQty * 0.95).toFixed(2);
          else if (idx === 2) invoicePrice = +(invoicePrice * 1.03).toFixed(4);
        } else if (pattern === 'messy') {
          // Every other line gets a variance, alternating qty / price
          if (idx % 2 === 0 && idx > 0) invoiceQty = +(recQty * 0.92).toFixed(2);
          else if (idx % 2 === 1)       invoicePrice = +(invoicePrice * 1.05).toFixed(4);
        }
        // pattern === 'clean': everything matches exactly
        const net = +(invoiceQty * invoicePrice).toFixed(2);
        const vatPct = poLine.vatPct || 0;
        const tax = +(net * vatPct / 100).toFixed(2);
        return {
          invLineIdx: idx,
          product: poLine.product,
          sku: poLine.sku,
          uom: poLine.uom,
          qty: invoiceQty,
          unitPrice: invoicePrice,
          vatPct,
          net,
          tax,
          gross: +(net + tax).toFixed(2),
          // Matching — operator fills in via INVOICE_MATCH_LINE
          matchedTo: [],          // [{ poEventId, poLineIdx, matchedQty, matchedUnitPrice }]
          matchStatus: 'unmatched' // unmatched | matched | variance | disputed
        };
      }).filter(Boolean);

      const netTotal = invoiceLines.reduce((s, l) => s + l.net, 0);
      const taxTotal = invoiceLines.reduce((s, l) => s + l.tax, 0);
      const grossTotal = netTotal + taxTotal;

      const existingInvCount = selectInvoiceEvents(state.ledger).length;
      const invoiceId = newInvoiceId(existingInvCount + 1);
      // Synthetic supplier-side invoice number — what would appear on the PDF
      const supplierInvoiceNumber = `${po.supplier.split(' ').map(w => w[0]).join('').toUpperCase()}-${String(Math.floor(Math.random() * 90000) + 10000)}`;

      const invoiceEvent = {
        eventId: uid('EVT'),
        eventType: EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE,
        parentEventId: po.eventId,
        timestamp: nowIso(),
        invoiceId,
        supplierInvoiceNumber,
        poId: po.poId,
        poEventId: po.eventId,
        legalEntity: po.legalEntity,
        siteId: po.siteId,
        siteName: po.siteName,
        supplier: po.supplier,
        partitionKey: po.partitionKey,
        invoiceDate: nowIso().slice(0, 10),
        dueDate: new Date(Date.now() + 30 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000).toISOString().slice(0, 10),
        receivedAt: nowIso(),
        lines: invoiceLines,
        netTotal: +netTotal.toFixed(2),
        taxTotal: +taxTotal.toFixed(2),
        grossTotal: +grossTotal.toFixed(2),
        currency: 'GBP',
        status: 'pending_match',
        matchedAt: null,
        approvedAt: null,
        approvedBy: null,
        disputeReason: null
      };

      return { ...state, ledger: [invoiceEvent, ...state.ledger] };
    }
    case 'INVOICE_MATCH_LINE': {
      // Operator picks a PO line for one invoice line. matchedQty defaults to
      // the invoice line qty (so Many:1 aggregation works — multiple invoice
      // lines pointing to the same PO line; the PO line's invoiced total then
      // sums across them). One invoice line → one PO line in this pass; 1:Many
      // splits (one invoice line spread across multiple PO lines) come with
      // the agent-assisted match.
      // The variance classifier also receives the cumulative qty received
      // against this PO line from all GRN events — that's the third leg of
      // the three-way match (invoice / PO / GRN).
      // action: { invoiceEventId, invLineIdx, poEventId, poLineIdx }
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.invoiceEventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE) return e;
        if (e.status === 'approved_for_post' || e.status === 'rejected') return e;
        const po = state.ledger.find(p => p.eventId === action.poEventId && String(p.eventType).toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.PO);
        if (!po) return e;
        const grnTotals = grnReceivedTotalsForPo(state.ledger, action.poEventId);
        const receivedQty = grnTotals[action.poLineIdx] || 0;
        // Resolve supplier-LE expected VAT rate (architectural call: VAT is
        // auto-resolved from the supplier-LE pair, not picked per transaction).
        const supplier = state.suppliers.find(s => s.id === e.supplierId);
        const expectedVatPct = expectedVatPctForSupplierLe(supplier, e.legalEntity);
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== action.invLineIdx) return l;
          const poLine = po.lines[action.poLineIdx];
          if (!poLine) return l;
          const matchedQty = l.qty;  // default: match the entire invoice-line qty against this PO line
          const variance = classifyMatchVariance({ invLine: l, poLine, matchedQty, receivedQty, expectedVatPct });
          return {
            ...l,
            matchedTo: [{
              poEventId: po.eventId,
              poId: po.poId,
              poLineIdx: action.poLineIdx,
              matchedQty,
              matchedUnitPrice: poLine.confirmedUnitPrice ?? poLine.unitPrice,
              receivedQty,  // snapshot at match time; recomputed in UI from live ledger
              variance
            }],
            matchStatus: variance.withinTolerance ? 'matched' : 'variance'
          };
        });
        return { ...e, lines };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'INVOICE_UNMATCH_LINE': {
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.invoiceEventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE) return e;
        if (e.status === 'approved_for_post' || e.status === 'rejected') return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) =>
          i === action.invLineIdx ? { ...l, matchedTo: [], matchStatus: 'unmatched' } : l
        );
        return { ...e, lines };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'INVOICE_CODE_LINE_MANUALLY': {
      // Operator codes an invoice line directly (not by matching to a PO).
      // Used for Pathway 3 invoices (utilities/rates/insurance) AND off-PO
      // additions (supplier added a line not on the PO). Sets line.coding
      // explicitly and marks the line `manually_coded` — a terminal-for-
      // matching state that the confirm-match gate treats as acceptable.
      //
      // action: { invoiceEventId, invLineIdx, coding: { dept, costCentre, glAccount, outlet, treatment? } }
      const { invoiceEventId, invLineIdx, coding } = action;
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== invoiceEventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE) return e;
        if (e.status === 'approved_for_post' || e.status === 'rejected') return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== invLineIdx) return l;
          const fullCoding = {
            legalEntity: e.legalEntity,
            outlet: coding.outlet || null,
            dept: coding.dept,
            costCentre: coding.costCentre,
            glAccount: coding.glAccount,
            treatment: coding.treatment || 'Direct to P&L'
          };
          const codingStr = `${fullCoding.legalEntity} · ${e.siteId} · ${fullCoding.outlet || '—'} · ${fullCoding.dept} · ${fullCoding.costCentre} · ${fullCoding.glAccount}`;
          return {
            ...l,
            coding: fullCoding,
            codingString: codingStr,
            matchedTo: [],          // clearing any prior PO match — manual coding supersedes
            matchStatus: 'manually_coded',
            manuallyCodedAt: nowIso()
          };
        });
        return { ...e, lines };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'INVOICE_RESET_LINE_CODING': {
      // Operator clears manual coding, returning the line to unmatched state.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.invoiceEventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE) return e;
        if (e.status === 'approved_for_post' || e.status === 'rejected') return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== action.invLineIdx) return l;
          const { manuallyCodedAt, ...rest } = l;
          return { ...rest, coding: null, codingString: null, matchedTo: [], matchStatus: 'unmatched' };
        });
        return { ...e, lines };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'INVOICE_OVERRIDE_LINE_CODING': {
      // Operator adjusts coding on an invoice line WITHOUT discarding any PO
      // match. The line keeps `matchedTo` (so lineage to the PO line is
      // preserved) but `coding` and `codingString` are explicitly set to the
      // override values. A `codingOverridden: true` flag marks the divergence
      // from the PO line's coding for audit purposes.
      //
      // This is the action used by the Invoices-tab coding editor — where the
      // operator may want to re-code a matched line (e.g. recategorise to a
      // different cost centre) without unmatching it from the PO.
      //
      // action: { invoiceEventId, invLineIdx, coding: { dept, costCentre, glAccount, outlet, treatment? } }
      const { invoiceEventId, invLineIdx, coding } = action;
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== invoiceEventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE) return e;
        if (e.status === 'approved_for_post' || e.status === 'rejected') return e;
        const lines = e.lines.map((l, i) => {
          if (i !== invLineIdx) return l;
          const fullCoding = {
            legalEntity: e.legalEntity,
            outlet: coding.outlet || null,
            dept: coding.dept,
            costCentre: coding.costCentre,
            glAccount: coding.glAccount,
            treatment: coding.treatment || (l.coding?.treatment) || 'Direct to P&L'
          };
          const codingStr = `${fullCoding.legalEntity} · ${e.siteId} · ${fullCoding.outlet || '—'} · ${fullCoding.dept} · ${fullCoding.costCentre} · ${fullCoding.glAccount}`;
          return {
            ...l,
            coding: fullCoding,
            codingString: codingStr,
            codingOverridden: true,
            codingOverriddenAt: nowIso()
          };
        });
        return { ...e, lines };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'INVOICE_CONFIRM_MATCH': {
      // Operator declares matching complete. Derives invoice status from the
      // line states. `manually_coded` lines count as resolved (no PO match
      // but coded for the journal). Status mapping:
      //   any unmatched → partially_matched
      //   any variance/disputed → disputed (flag persists; operator can still approve)
      //   else → matched
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.invoiceEventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE) return e;
        if (e.status === 'approved_for_post' || e.status === 'rejected') return e;
        const lineStatuses = e.lines.map(l => l.matchStatus);
        let status = 'matched';
        if (lineStatuses.some(s => s === 'unmatched')) status = 'partially_matched';
        else if (lineStatuses.some(s => s === 'variance' || s === 'disputed')) status = 'disputed';
        return { ...e, status, matchedAt: nowIso() };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'INVOICE_APPROVE': {
      // Final approval — moves the invoice to approved_for_post. Journal generation
      // is downstream (next module). Approver lives in the Invoice approvals tab;
      // this action fires from that queue, not from the matching workspace.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.invoiceEventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'matched' && e.status !== 'disputed') return e;
        return lockCommentsAtStage({
          ...e,
          status: 'approved_for_post',
          approvedAt: nowIso(),
          approvedBy: action.approverName || 'Approver',
          approvalReviewNote: action.reviewNote || null,
          approvalReviewFlags: action.reviewFlags || []
        }, 'invoice');
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'INVOICE_SEND_BACK_TO_MATCHING': {
      // Approver returns a matched invoice to the matching queue with a note.
      // Status: matched | disputed → partially_matched (so matcher sees it again).
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.invoiceEventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'matched' && e.status !== 'disputed') return e;
        return {
          ...e,
          status: 'partially_matched',
          sentBackAt: nowIso(),
          sentBackReason: action.reason || '',
          sentBackBy: action.approverName || 'Approver'
        };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'INVOICE_REJECT_BY_APPROVER': {
      // Approver rejects fully — invoice closed. Status: matched | disputed → rejected.
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.invoiceEventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE) return e;
        if (e.status !== 'matched' && e.status !== 'disputed') return e;
        return {
          ...e,
          status: 'rejected',
          rejectedAt: nowIso(),
          rejectionReason: action.reason || '',
          rejectedBy: action.approverName || 'Approver'
        };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }
    case 'INVOICE_DISPUTE': {
      // Operator-initiated dispute (e.g. duplicate, wrong supplier, can't reconcile).
      const ledger = state.ledger.map(e => {
        if (e.eventId !== action.invoiceEventId || String(e.eventType).toUpperCase() !== EVENT_TYPE.INVOICE) return e;
        if (e.status === 'approved_for_post' || e.status === 'rejected') return e;
        return { ...e, status: 'disputed', disputeReason: action.reason || '' };
      });
      return { ...state, ledger };
    }

    case 'NEW_ORDER': {
      // Derive next ID from the ledger — the highest committed orderId is the
      // authoritative sequence anchor. Falling back to state.order.id only when
      // the ledger is empty (first ever order on a clean sheet). This prevents
      // gaps or collisions that would arise from reading the current draft ID,
      // which can lag behind what's actually been committed.
      const committedNums = state.ledger
        .filter(e => String(e.eventType || '').toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.ORDER && e.orderId)
        .map(e => parseInt(String(e.orderId).split('-').pop(), 10) || 0);
      const draftNum = parseInt(String(state.order.id || '').split('-').pop(), 10) || 0;
      const maxNum = Math.max(0, ...committedNums, draftNum);
      const fresh = { ...initialOrder, id: `ORD-2026-${String(maxNum + 1).padStart(4, '0')}` };
      // Also reset the agent's chat history. Without this, prior-session mentions of
      // a site name (e.g. "Mayfair") leak into the new order's intake — the agent
      // sees them via priorMessages and "resolves" Site without asking.
      return { ...state, order: fresh, agent: { ...state.agent, messages: [], pendingSuggestions: [], typing: false } };
    }
    case 'POPULATE_FROM_AGENT': {
      // Agent payload: { description?, needBy?, sites: [{ siteId, lines: [{...}] }] }
      const payload = action.agentOutput || {};

      // If the user asked the agent to populate while looking at a submitted order,
      // mint a fresh draft first. Use the same ledger-anchored ID derivation as
      // NEW_ORDER so the ID is always one above the highest committed order.
      const committedOrderNums = state.ledger
        .filter(e => String(e.eventType || '').toUpperCase() === EVENT_TYPE.ORDER && e.orderId)
        .map(e => parseInt(String(e.orderId).split('-').pop(), 10) || 0);
      const currentDraftNum = parseInt(String(state.order.id || '').split('-').pop(), 10) || 0;
      const maxOrderNum = Math.max(0, ...committedOrderNums, currentDraftNum);
      const baseOrder = state.order.status === 'submitted'
        ? { ...initialOrder, id: `ORD-2026-${String(maxOrderNum + 1).padStart(4, '0')}` }
        : state.order;
      let sites = [...baseOrder.sites];

      (payload.sites || []).forEach(siteAction => {
        const masterSite = state.sites.find(s => s.siteId === siteAction.siteId);
        if (!masterSite) return;  // unknown site — agent shouldn't have produced this; skip
        if (!siteAction.lines || siteAction.lines.length === 0) return;  // phantom group — skip; the chat handler surfaces the reason

        // Find or create the site group
        let siteEntry = sites.find(s => s.siteId === siteAction.siteId);
        if (!siteEntry) {
          siteEntry = {
            siteId: masterSite.siteId,
            collapsed: false,
            areaMasterCollapsed: false,
            areaMaster: { ...masterSite.defaults, legalEntity: masterSite.legalEntity },
            lines: []
          };
          sites = [...sites, siteEntry];
        }

        (siteAction.lines || []).forEach(la => {
          // Try to resolve product from SKU (if present and in catalogue)
          const product = la.sku ? state.catalogue.find(p => p.sku === la.sku) : null;

          // Binary routing rule (overrides whatever the agent emitted):
          //   LIVE product = catalogue match with current price > 0 → REQ
          //   anything else (ad-hoc, catalogue without live price) → RFQ
          // Catalogue price is authoritative for catalogue matches — agent.price is
          // only meaningful for ad-hoc lines where there's no master anchor.
          const livePrice = product ? product.price : (la.price ?? null);
          const isLive = !!product && livePrice != null && livePrice > 0;
          const issuesAs = isLive ? 'REQ' : 'RFQ';

          // Supplier: agent's value > SKU's supplier > empty. Empty supplier is now a
          // normal state — the user fills the inline supplier dropdown to complete the line.
          // No auto-blocking; the line is otherwise fully formed.
          const resolvedSupplier = la.supplier || (product ? product.supplier : '');

          // Defensive de-duplication. The agent prompt tells it not to re-emit
          // existing lines, but if it does anyway, suppress silently rather than
          // doubling the order. Match heuristic: same site, same SKU (or same
          // ad-hoc name when SKU is absent), same supplier.
          const dupKey = (l) => `${l.sku || (l.name || '').toLowerCase()}|${(l.supplier || '').toLowerCase()}`;
          const incomingKey = `${la.sku || (la.name || '').toLowerCase()}|${(resolvedSupplier || '').toLowerCase()}`;
          const isDup = siteEntry.lines.some(l => dupKey(l) === incomingKey);
          if (isDup) return;  // skip — agent dedup leak guard

          // Coding always populates from the agent's values OR the area-master defaults.
          // Every dimension gets a non-empty value so the line never carries empty coding.
          const coding = {
            legalEntity: la.coding?.legalEntity || siteEntry.areaMaster.legalEntity,
            outlet:      la.coding?.outlet      || siteEntry.areaMaster.outlet,
            dept:        la.coding?.dept        || siteEntry.areaMaster.departments[0],
            costCentre:  la.coding?.costCentre  || siteEntry.areaMaster.costCentre,
            glAccount:   la.coding?.glAccount   || siteEntry.areaMaster.glAccount
          };

          const newLine = {
            lineId: uid('LN'),
            productId: product ? product.id : null,
            sku: la.sku || 'AD-HOC',
            name: la.name || (product ? product.name : 'Unknown item'),
            supplier: resolvedSupplier,
            qty: la.qty || 1,
            uom: la.uom || (product ? product.uom : 'ea'),
            price: isLive ? livePrice : 0,           // RFQ lines carry £0 until quote arrives
            vat: la.vat ?? (product ? product.vat : 20),
            coding,
            treatment: la.treatment || (product ? product.treatment : 'Direct to P&L'),
            issuesAs,                                  // ← enforced binary rule, not agent's choice
            notes: la.notes || '',
            agentSuggestion: null,
            agentSuggestionStatus: 'accepted',
            agentPopulated: true,                      // ← marks fields the agent set
            agentConfidence: la.confidence || null,
            blockedReason: null,                       // ← no line is blocked; supplier-missing handled inline
            isCustom: !product
          };

          // Update siteEntry with the new line, then re-merge into sites array
          const updatedSite = { ...siteEntry, lines: [...siteEntry.lines, newLine] };
          sites = sites.map(s => s.siteId === siteEntry.siteId ? updatedSite : s);
          siteEntry = updatedSite;
        });
      });

      // Order-level patches (description, requiredBy) if agent provided them
      const orderPatch = {};
      if (payload.description) orderPatch.description = payload.description;
      if (payload.needBy)      orderPatch.requiredBy  = payload.needBy;

      // Seed the routing strip from the first populated site, so the dropdowns
      // reflect the agent's choice and the user can see / change / confirm it
      // (rather than seeing empty dropdowns next to fully-coded lines). The
      // routingUserConfirmed flag stays false — agent set this, not the human.
      // Only seeds when routing was previously empty; respects an existing user pick.
      const seedRouting = (() => {
        if (baseOrder.routing?.legalEntity && baseOrder.routing?.siteId) return baseOrder.routing;
        const firstSiteEntry = sites.find(s => s.lines.length > 0);
        if (!firstSiteEntry) return baseOrder.routing;
        const masterSite = state.sites.find(s => s.siteId === firstSiteEntry.siteId);
        if (!masterSite) return baseOrder.routing;
        return {
          legalEntity: masterSite.legalEntity,
          siteId: masterSite.siteId,
          outletId: masterSite.defaults?.outlet || masterSite.outlets?.[0]?.outletId || ''
        };
      })();

      // Recently added: surface for the quick-reorder strip
      const newLinesFlat = (payload.sites || []).flatMap(sa => (sa.lines || []).map(la => ({
        productId: la.sku, name: la.name, qty: la.qty || 1, siteId: sa.siteId
      })));
      const recent = [...newLinesFlat, ...state.recentlyAdded].slice(0, 8);

      return { ...state, order: { ...baseOrder, ...orderPatch, sites, routing: seedRouting }, recentlyAdded: recent };
    }
    default:
      return state;
  }
}

/* ---------- Build rich agent context (the fix to the 42%-confidence problem) ----------
   The agent over-asked because it had nothing to anchor to. This helper packages
   the full master-data scope the agent needs to resolve dimensions silently. */
function buildAgentContext(state, extras = {}) {
  const permittedLEs = (state.user.permittedLEs || [])
    .map(code => LEGAL_ENTITIES.find(le => le.code === code))
    .filter(Boolean);

  const permittedSites = (state.user.assignedSites || [])
    .map(siteId => {
      const s = state.sites.find(x => x.siteId === siteId);
      if (!s) return null;
      return {
        siteId: s.siteId,
        name: s.name,
        parent_LE: s.parent_LE,
        outlets: s.outlets,
        default_outlet_code: s.defaultOutletCode
      };
    })
    .filter(Boolean);

  const permittedSuppliers = (state.user.permittedSuppliers || [])
    .map(id => state.suppliers.find(s => s.id === id))
    .filter(Boolean);

  return {
    today: new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10),  // anchor for need-by date interpretation
    user_profile: {
      name: state.user.name,
      role: state.user.role,
      permitted_LEs: permittedLEs,
      permitted_sites: permittedSites,
      permitted_suppliers: permittedSuppliers
    },
    chart_of_accounts: CHART_OF_ACCOUNTS,
    // Linkage tables — the agent uses these to produce coding that passes
    // validateCoding(). Without them every agent populate triggered CODING flags.
    departments: DEPARTMENTS,
    cost_centres: COST_CENTRES,
    master_products: MASTER_PRODUCTS,
    catalogue_skus: state.catalogue.map(p => ({
      sku: p.sku, name: p.name, masterProductId: p.masterProductId,
      supplier: p.supplier, supplierId: p.supplierId,
      uom: p.uom, packSize: p.packSize,  // pack size lets the agent convert user units → SKU units
      price: p.price, gl: p.gl, treatment: p.treatment
    })),
    recent_orders_for_cluster_inference: HISTORICAL_ORDERS,
    all_suppliers_including_pending: state.suppliers,  // so agent can see SUP-004 exists but is gated
    current_order: {
      order_id: state.order.id,
      // routing_user_confirmed: false when the agent populated routing but the
      // human hasn't approved it — agent must still avoid re-asking about LE/Site.
      routing: state.order.routing,
      routing_user_confirmed: state.order.routingUserConfirmed,
      // FULL existing-line list so the agent can avoid emitting duplicates.
      // Without this the agent only saw line_count per site and could
      // re-emit lines from prior turns mentioned in priorMessages — the
      // "agent added another order for saffron" leak.
      existing_lines: state.order.sites.flatMap(s =>
        s.lines.map(l => ({
          siteId: s.siteId,
          product: l.name,
          sku: l.sku || null,
          supplier: l.supplier || null,
          qty: l.qty,
          uom: l.uom
        }))
      )
    },
    ...extras
  };
}

/* ---------- Claude API call ---------- */
async function callAgent(userMessage, contextObj, responseSchemaInstruction = null, priorMessages = [], attachments = [], systemPromptOverride = null) {
  const defaultSchema = `Respond with ONLY a single JSON object. Do not wrap in code fences. Schema:
{
  "coding": { "legal_entity": "...", "outlet": "...", "department": "...", "cost_centre": "...", "gl_account": "..." },
  "treatment": "Direct to P&L | Prepayment | Inventory | CapEx",
  "confidence": 0-100,
  "reasoning": "one short sentence",
  "questions": ["..."],
  "closest_analogue": "product name from catalogue or null"
}`;
  const schemaInstr = responseSchemaInstruction || defaultSchema;

  // Text-based files (CSV, TXT) get inlined into the user message; binary files
  // (PDF, image) become document/image content blocks the model can read natively.
  const textAttachments = (attachments || []).filter(a => a.kind === 'text');
  const binaryAttachments = (attachments || []).filter(a => a.kind === 'pdf' || a.kind === 'image');

  let textPart = userMessage;
  if (textAttachments.length > 0) {
    const inlined = textAttachments
      .map(a => `\n\n=== Uploaded file: ${a.name} (${a.type || 'text'}) ===\n${a.data}\n=== End of ${a.name} ===`)
      .join('');
    textPart = `${userMessage}${inlined}`;
  }
  if (binaryAttachments.length > 0) {
    const fileList = binaryAttachments.map(a => `- ${a.name} (${a.type})`).join('\n');
    textPart = `${textPart}\n\nThe user also attached the following file(s) above this message — read them as part of the order intake:\n${fileList}`;
  }

  const userText = contextObj
    ? `${textPart}\n\nContext (JSON):\n${JSON.stringify(contextObj, null, 2)}\n\n${schemaInstr}`
    : textPart;

  // Build the user content. If no binary attachments, send plain text (cheaper).
  // Otherwise send a content array with documents/images first, then the text block.
  let userContent;
  if (binaryAttachments.length === 0) {
    userContent = userText;
  } else {
    userContent = [
      ...binaryAttachments.map(a => {
        if (a.kind === 'pdf') {
          return { type: 'document', source: { type: 'base64', media_type: 'application/pdf', data: a.data } };
        }
        // image
        return { type: 'image', source: { type: 'base64', media_type: a.type || 'image/png', data: a.data } };
      }),
      { type: 'text', text: userText }
    ];
  }

  // Prior turns give the agent the conversation it asked questions in — without them
  // a follow-up reply like "Mayfair" has no anchor and the order can never complete.
  // The Anthropic Messages API requires strictly alternating user/assistant turns
  // starting with user. Coalesce same-role neighbours into one merged turn.
  const merged = [];
  for (const m of priorMessages) {
    if (m.role !== 'user' && m.role !== 'assistant') continue;
    const last = merged[merged.length - 1];
    if (last && last.role === m.role) {
      last.content = `${last.content}\n\n${m.content}`;
    } else {
      merged.push({ ...m });
    }
  }
  while (merged.length && merged[0].role !== 'user') merged.shift();
  while (merged.length && merged[merged.length - 1].role === 'user') merged.pop();

  const messages = [
    ...merged,
    { role: "user", content: userContent }
  ];

  const res = await fetch("https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages", {
    method: "POST",
    headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      model: "claude-sonnet-4-20250514",
      // Bulk extract responses are large JSON arrays — bump max_tokens so a
      // 30-row spreadsheet doesn't get truncated mid-array.
      // Bulk extract responses are large JSON arrays — 16k gives headroom for
      // 30+ line invoices/orders with full per-line coding without truncation.
      // (Truncated mid-array was a silent dropped-row failure mode.)
      max_tokens: systemPromptOverride ? 16000 : 2000,
      system: systemPromptOverride || AGENT_SYSTEM,
      messages
    })
  });
  if (!res.ok) {
    const body = await res.text().catch(() => '');
    throw new Error(`API error ${res.status}: ${body.slice(0, 200)}`);
  }
  const data = await res.json();
  const text = (data.content || []).filter(c => c.type === "text").map(c => c.text).join("\n");
  return text;
}

const tryParseJson = (txt) => {
  if (!txt) return null;
  const cleaned = txt.replace(/```json|```/g, "").trim();
  // find first { ... last }
  const first = cleaned.indexOf("{");
  const last = cleaned.lastIndexOf("}");
  if (first < 0 || last < 0) return null;
  try { return JSON.parse(cleaned.slice(first, last + 1)); } catch { return null; }
};

/* =====================================================
/* =====================================================
   ERROR BOUNDARY — surfaces runtime errors inline instead of a white screen
   ===================================================== */
class ProFlowErrorBoundary extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) { super(props); this.state = { error: null, info: null }; }
  static getDerivedStateFromError(error) { return { error }; }
  componentDidCatch(error, info) {
    this.setState({ info });
    if (typeof console !== 'undefined') console.error('[ProFlow caught render error]', error, info);
  }
  render() {
    if (this.state.error) {
      const msg = String(this.state.error?.message || this.state.error || 'Unknown error');
      const stack = this.state.error?.stack || '';
      const componentStack = this.state.info?.componentStack || '';
      return (
        <div style={{ padding: '24px', background: '#FEF2F2', minHeight: '100vh', fontFamily: 'Inter, sans-serif', color: '#0D1424' }}>
          <div style={{ maxWidth: '900px', margin: '0 auto', background: '#FFFFFF', border: '1px solid #FCA5A5', borderRadius: '8px', overflow: 'hidden' }}>
            <div style={{ padding: '14px 18px', background: '#FEE2E2', borderBottom: '1px solid #FCA5A5' }}>
              <div style={{ fontWeight: 700, fontSize: '15px', color: '#991B1B' }}>Render error — caught by boundary</div>
              <div style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#7F1D1D', marginTop: '2px' }}>The app crashed during render. The error is shown below so we can fix it instead of seeing a blank screen.</div>
            </div>
            <div style={{ padding: '14px 18px' }}>
              <div style={{ fontFamily: '"JetBrains Mono", monospace', fontSize: '12px', color: '#B91C1C', fontWeight: 600 }}>{msg}</div>
              {componentStack && (
                <details style={{ marginTop: '10px' }}>
                  <summary style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#586278', cursor: 'pointer' }}>Component stack</summary>
                  <pre style={{ fontFamily: '"JetBrains Mono", monospace', fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#586278', whiteSpace: 'pre-wrap', marginTop: '6px', maxHeight: '320px', overflow: 'auto' }}>{componentStack}</pre>
                </details>
              )}
              {stack && (
                <details style={{ marginTop: '10px' }}>
                  <summary style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#586278', cursor: 'pointer' }}>JS stack</summary>
                  <pre style={{ fontFamily: '"JetBrains Mono", monospace', fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#586278', whiteSpace: 'pre-wrap', marginTop: '6px', maxHeight: '320px', overflow: 'auto' }}>{stack}</pre>
                </details>
              )}
              <button
                onClick={() => this.setState({ error: null, info: null })}
                style={{ marginTop: '14px', padding: '6px 12px', background: '#0F7AD8', color: '#FFFFFF', border: 'none', borderRadius: '4px', fontSize: '12px', cursor: 'pointer' }}
              >Try again</button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      );
    }
    return this.props.children;
  }
}

/* =====================================================
   APP
   ===================================================== */
function AppInner() {
  const [state, dispatch] = useReducer(reducer, initialState, (s) => ({
    ...s,
    ledger: []
  }));
  const [view, setView] = useState('order'); // 'order' | 'submitted' | 'orders' | 'suppliers' | 'rfqs'
  const [trackerOrigin, setTrackerOrigin] = useState(null); // which document opened the tracker
  const [approvalFocus, setApprovalFocus] = useState(null); // eventId to auto-open in an approval queue
  const [routingModalOpen, setRoutingModalOpen] = useState(false);
  const [newProductOpen, setNewProductOpen] = useState(false);
  const [newProductSeed, setNewProductSeed] = useState({ name: '', supplier: '', siteId: 'SITE-LON-01' });
  // Bulk upload modal — runs through a multi-stage flow (file → agent parse → review → confirm).
  const [bulkUploadOpen, setBulkUploadOpen] = useState(false);
  const [bulkUploadSiteId, setBulkUploadSiteId] = useState(null);
  const [activeCategory, setActiveCategory] = useState('All');
  const [activeSupplier, setActiveSupplier] = useState('All');
  // Coding-aware catalogue filters — Dept narrows visible CCs, CC narrows visible
  // products. Optimises coding by giving the user a way to browse by accounting
  // dimension. The picked Dept/CC also propagate to the next add as a coding
  // override, so the line lands with the user's intent rather than just the
  // outlet's default. 'All' means no filter at that level.
  const [activeDept, setActiveDept] = useState('All');
  const [activeCC, setActiveCC] = useState('All');
  const [searchTerm, setSearchTerm] = useState('');
  const [showCodingCols, setShowCodingCols] = useState(false);
  const [showClusters, setShowClusters] = useState(false);
  // Left (catalogue) and right (order summary) panel collapse state. When true,
  // the panel renders as a thin icon rail and the canvas claims the freed space.
  const [leftCollapsed, setLeftCollapsed] = useState(false);
  const [rightCollapsed, setRightCollapsed] = useState(false);
  const [cartExpanded, setCartExpanded] = useState(false);
  const [activeNav, setActiveNav] = useState('new-order');
  const lastNavRef = useRef('new-order');
  // DEV-ONLY reset guard. The mount-time storage restore is async; if the user
  // clicks Reset while that restore is still in flight, the restore can resolve
  // afterwards and re-dispatch the stale (pre-reset) ledger. This ref lets the
  // restore effect detect a reset that happened during its await and abort the
  // RESTORE dispatch. Remove together with the reset feature for production.
  const resetRequestedRef = useRef(false);
  // Gates the persist effects — flipped true once the initial storage restore
  // has run, so we don't save empty state over good data during the load race.
  const restoredRef = useRef(false);

  // Two-user demo: Flo (Requester) raises orders; Marcus (Approver) signs them off.
  // Approval dispatches stamp currentUser.name into the approverName field so the
  // ledger records who acted. Toggle in the sidebar footer.
  // Three-user demo: Flo (Requester), Marcus (Approver), Sarah (Supplier).
  // Sarah is tied to Premier Produce Co. (SUP-001). The supplier user sees a
  // different sidebar and gets a Supplier Portal view filtered to their own
  // documents. Confirm/issue-invoice/respond-to-query dispatches stamp the
  // supplier user's name onto the relevant ledger event.
  const [currentUser, setCurrentUser] = useState({ name: 'Flo Brunner', role: 'requester', title: 'Property Director' });
  const USERS = [
    { name: 'Flo Brunner',  role: 'requester', title: 'Property Director' },
    { name: 'Marcus Webb',  role: 'approver',  title: 'Operations Manager' },
    { name: 'Sarah Chen',   role: 'supplier',  title: 'Account Manager · All Suppliers (demo)', supplierId: 'SUP-001', supplierName: 'Premier Produce Co.', masterSupplier: true },
  ];
  const switchUser = () => {
    setCurrentUser(u => {
      const idx = USERS.findIndex(x => x.name === u.name);
      const next = USERS[(idx + 1) % USERS.length];
      // When changing role, land on a sensible home for the new persona.
      if (next.role === 'supplier' && !String(activeNav || '').startsWith('sup-')) {
        setActiveNav('sup-home');
      } else if (next.role !== 'supplier' && String(activeNav || '').startsWith('sup-')) {
        setActiveNav('new-order');
      }
      return next;
    });
  };

  // Wipes all ledger events + order canvas and clears persisted storage.
  // Intended for testing — resets the app to a clean state without refreshing.
  // DEV-ONLY. Wipes all ledger events + order canvas and clears persisted
  // storage so a fresh set of transactions can be built without legacy data.
  // Remove this function and its sidebar button before production.
  const resetDb = async () => {
    // Cancel any in-flight mount restore so a late-resolving restore can't
    // re-populate the ledger with the pre-reset snapshot, and block the persist
    // effects from re-saving the empty state before the storage deletes land.
    resetRequestedRef.current = true;
    restoredRef.current = false;
    dispatch({ type: 'RESET_LEDGER' });
    setView('order');
    setActiveNav('new-order');
    setTrackerOrigin(null);
    setApprovalFocus(null);
    if (typeof window !== 'undefined' && window.storage) {
      await Promise.allSettled([
        window.storage.delete('proflow.ledger'),
        window.storage.delete('proflow.order'),
        window.storage.delete('proflow.agent_messages'),
        window.storage.delete('proflow.recently_added'),
      ]);
    }
    // Re-enable persistence so newly-built transactions save normally.
    restoredRef.current = true;
  };

  // Sidebar navigation handler. Currently only 'new-order' is fully wired.
  //   'new-order' click while looking at a submitted order → mint a fresh draft.
  //   'new-order' click on an empty draft → no-op (already on the right view).
  //   'new-order' click on a draft with lines → flip to canvas view; do NOT auto-clear
  //     (user explicitly confirms via the New Order button on the canvas if they
  //     want to discard work).
  // Without this effect, clicking 'new-order' just highlighted the sidebar item
  // without changing the rendered content — making the tab look broken when the
  // canvas was still showing a prior bulk-uploaded order.
  useEffect(() => {
    if (activeNav === lastNavRef.current) return;
    lastNavRef.current = activeNav;
    if (activeNav === 'new-order') {
      if (state.order.status === 'submitted') {
        dispatch({ type: 'NEW_ORDER' });
      }
      setView('order');
    } else if (activeNav === 'flow-requests') {
      setView('flow-requests');
    } else if (activeNav === 'new-flow-request') {
      setView('new-flow-request');
    } else if (activeNav === 'invoicing') {
      setView('invoicing');
    } else if (activeNav === 'orders') {
      // Orders list — every submitted order, newest first, with expandable detail.
      setView('orders');
    } else if (activeNav === 'tracker') {
      // Order tracker — show list view; clear any previously drilled-in origin
      setTrackerOrigin(null);
      setView('tracker');
    } else if (activeNav === 'rfqs') {
      // RFQ list — every RFQ event from the ledger, status-filterable, expandable.
      setView('rfqs');
    } else if (activeNav === 'requisitions') {
      // Requisition list — operator review → approval workflow → PO emission.
      setView('requisitions');
    } else if (activeNav === 'po') {
      // PO list — every PO in the ledger across statuses.
      setView('po');
    } else if (activeNav === 'po-approvals') {
      // PO approvals queue — POs needing my approval before dispatch.
      setView('po-approvals');
    } else if (activeNav === 'confirmations') {
      // Supplier Confirmations queue — POs sent to suppliers awaiting their confirmation.
      setView('confirmations');
    } else if (activeNav === 'grn') {
      // Goods receipts — record physical receipt against confirmed POs.
      setView('grn');
    } else if (activeNav === 'invoices') {
      // Invoices — data table of every invoice across all statuses.
      setView('invoices');
    } else if (activeNav === 'invoice-matching') {
      // Invoice matching — queue + workspace for active matching work.
      setView('invoice-matching');
    } else if (activeNav === 'invoice-ingestion') {
      // Invoice ingestion — verify agent-extracted data from incoming invoice docs.
      setView('invoice-ingestion');
    } else if (activeNav === 'rfq-ingestion') {
      // RFQ ingestion — verify agent-extracted data from incoming quote docs.
      setView('rfq-ingestion');
    } else if (activeNav === 'invoice-approvals') {
      // Invoice approvals — approver queue for matched invoices.
      setView('invoice-approvals');
    } else if (activeNav === 'sup-dir') {
      setView('suppliers');
    } else if (activeNav === 'sup-home' || activeNav === 'sup-pos' || activeNav === 'sup-invoices' || activeNav === 'sup-queries') {
      // Supplier portal — combined view, internal tab inferred from activeNav.
      setView('sup-portal');
    }
  }, [activeNav, state.order.status]);

  /* Persist + restore via window.storage. A schema version key guards against
     stale ledger data from sessions before the seed-removal — if the persisted
     version doesn't match, we wipe storage on load and start with a clean
     ledger rather than restoring transactions the new build doesn't know how
     to handle. */
  useEffect(() => {
    (async () => {
      try {
        if (typeof window !== 'undefined' && window.storage) {
          const SCHEMA_VERSION = 'v04-noseed-2026-05';
          const versionRec = await window.storage.get('proflow.schema_version').catch(() => null);
          const liveVersion = versionRec ? JSON.parse(versionRec.value) : null;
          if (liveVersion !== SCHEMA_VERSION) {
            // Stale or missing schema marker → purge persisted state and stamp the new version.
            await Promise.allSettled([
              window.storage.delete('proflow.ledger'),
              window.storage.delete('proflow.order'),
              window.storage.delete('proflow.agent_messages'),
              window.storage.delete('proflow.recently_added'),
            ]);
            await window.storage.set('proflow.schema_version', JSON.stringify(SCHEMA_VERSION)).catch(() => {});
            restoredRef.current = true;
            return;
          }
          const order   = await window.storage.get('proflow.order').catch(() => null);
          const ledger  = await window.storage.get('proflow.ledger').catch(() => null);
          const msgs    = await window.storage.get('proflow.agent_messages').catch(() => null);
          const recent  = await window.storage.get('proflow.recently_added').catch(() => null);
          const payload = {};
          if (order)   payload.order = JSON.parse(order.value);
          if (ledger) {
            payload.ledger = JSON.parse(ledger.value);
          }
          if (recent)  payload.recentlyAdded = JSON.parse(recent.value);
          if (msgs)    payload.agent = { ...initialState.agent, messages: JSON.parse(msgs.value) };
          // If a reset was requested while these awaits were in flight, abort —
          // restoring here would clobber the clean sheet with stale data.
          if (resetRequestedRef.current) { restoredRef.current = true; return; }
          if (Object.keys(payload).length) dispatch({ type: 'RESTORE', payload });
          if (payload.order && payload.order.status === 'submitted') setView('submitted');
        }
      } catch (e) {
        // swallow — start fresh
      } finally {
        restoredRef.current = true;
      }
    })();
  }, []);

  /* Mirror order.status to the canvas view — when the agent or NEW_ORDER mints a
     fresh draft after a submitted order, flip the user back to the canvas. */
  useEffect(() => {
    if (state.order.status === 'draft' && view === 'submitted') setView('order');
  }, [state.order.status, state.order.id]);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!restoredRef.current) return;
    if (typeof window === 'undefined' || !window.storage) return;
    window.storage.set('proflow.order', JSON.stringify(state.order)).catch(() => {});
  }, [state.order]);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!restoredRef.current) return;
    if (typeof window === 'undefined' || !window.storage) return;
    window.storage.set('proflow.ledger', JSON.stringify(state.ledger)).catch(() => {});
  }, [state.ledger]);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!restoredRef.current) return;
    if (typeof window === 'undefined' || !window.storage) return;
    window.storage.set('proflow.agent_messages', JSON.stringify(state.agent.messages)).catch(() => {});
  }, [state.agent.messages]);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!restoredRef.current) return;
    if (typeof window === 'undefined' || !window.storage) return;
    window.storage.set('proflow.recently_added', JSON.stringify(state.recentlyAdded)).catch(() => {});
  }, [state.recentlyAdded]);

  /* ---------- derived totals ---------- */
  const totals = useMemo(() => {
    let net = 0, tax = 0, gross = 0, lines = 0, units = 0, rfq = 0;
    const suppliers = new Set();
    state.order.sites.forEach(s => {
      s.lines.forEach(l => {
        const lineNet = l.qty * l.price;
        const lineTax = lineNet * (l.vat / 100);
        if (l.issuesAs !== 'RFQ') {
          net += lineNet; tax += lineTax; gross += lineNet + lineTax;
        } else {
          rfq += 1;
        }
        lines += 1; units += l.qty;
        if (l.supplier) suppliers.add(l.supplier);
      });
    });
    return { net, tax, gross, lines, units, rfq, suppliers: suppliers.size, sites: state.order.sites.length };
  }, [state.order]);

  /* ---------- routing summary for preview ---------- */
  const routingPlan = useMemo(() => {
    const reqGroups = {};
    const rfqLines = [];
    state.order.sites.forEach(s => {
      s.lines.forEach(l => {
        if (l.issuesAs === 'RFQ') {
          rfqLines.push({ ...l, siteId: s.siteId });
        } else {
          const key = `${l.coding.legalEntity}__${s.siteId}__${l.supplier}`;
          if (!reqGroups[key]) reqGroups[key] = { legalEntity: l.coding.legalEntity, siteId: s.siteId, supplier: l.supplier, lines: [] };
          reqGroups[key].lines.push(l);
        }
      });
    });
    return { reqs: Object.values(reqGroups), rfqs: rfqLines };
  }, [state.order]);

  /* ---------- handlers ---------- */
  const addCatalogueItem = (productId, siteId, qty = 1, outletOverride = null, codingOverride = null, categoryOverride = null) => {
    const baseProduct = state.catalogue.find(p => p.id === productId);
    if (!baseProduct) return;
    const site = getSite(state, siteId);
    if (!site) return;

    /* Category override — the catalogue card's "Use as" picker emits one of
       the product's allowedCategories when the user wants to charge this
       line to a non-default category. e.g. picking red wine and selecting
       "Food" (the kitchen-cooking use) instead of the default "Beverage"
       (bar service).

       Implementation: wrap the product with the category's GL + treatment,
       AND synthesize a codingOverride forcing the category's Dept/CC/GL.
       The synthesized override flows through the same path as Dept/CC chip
       overrides — addCatalogueItem applies it to areaMaster, then
       buildLineFromProduct trusts areaMaster verbatim (codingExplicit=true).
       This avoids the name-heuristic kicking in and picking a CC
       inconsistent with the user's explicit choice. */
    let product = baseProduct;
    let derivedCodingOverride = codingOverride;
    if (categoryOverride) {
      const cat = SPEND_CATEGORIES.find(c => c.code === categoryOverride);
      const allowed = getProductAllowedCategories(baseProduct);
      if (cat && allowed.includes(categoryOverride)) {
        product = { ...baseProduct, gl: cat.glAccount, treatment: cat.treatment };
        // Merge: any explicit field from codingOverride (Dept/CC chip filter)
        // still wins over the category's derived value
        derivedCodingOverride = {
          dept: cat.dept,
          costCentre: cat.costCentre,
          glAccount: cat.glAccount,
          ...(codingOverride || {})
        };
      }
    }

    // Resolve coding source. If the caller passed an outletOverride (e.g. the picker's
    // "Add to outlet" selector), build a coding chain from THAT outlet's master record
    // — so the line lands in the right business-area cluster. Otherwise fall back to
    // the site group's live area master (or site defaults if the site isn't on the order yet).
    const existing = state.order.sites.find(s => s.siteId === siteId);
    let am;
    if (outletOverride) {
      const o = site.outlets?.find(x => x.outletId === outletOverride);
      if (o) {
        am = {
          legalEntity: site.legalEntity,
          outlet: o.outletId,
          departments: [o.dept],
          costCentre: o.cc,
          glAccount: o.defaultGL
        };
      }
    }
    if (!am) {
      am = existing ? existing.areaMaster : { ...site.defaults, legalEntity: site.legalEntity };
    }
    // derivedCodingOverride covers both the chip-filter case and the
    // multi-use category override case. Either way, the user has explicitly
    // picked one or more of Dept/CC/GL — we pass those as the *patch* to
    // reconcileCodingPatch so the reconciler treats them as user intent and
    // doesn't overwrite them. Previously this passed an empty patch, which
    // caused rule (a) "CC pins Dept" to overwrite a user's Dept selection
    // when the site's default CC was from a different Dept.
    if (derivedCodingOverride) {
      const current = {
        dept:       am.departments?.[0] || '',
        costCentre: am.costCentre || '',
        glAccount:  am.glAccount || '',
      };
      const patch = {};
      if (derivedCodingOverride.dept)       patch.dept = derivedCodingOverride.dept;
      if (derivedCodingOverride.costCentre) patch.costCentre = derivedCodingOverride.costCentre;
      if (derivedCodingOverride.glAccount)  patch.glAccount = derivedCodingOverride.glAccount;
      const reconciled = reconcileCodingPatch(current, patch);
      if (reconciled.dept)       am.departments = [reconciled.dept];
      else                       am.departments = [];
      am.costCentre = reconciled.costCentre || '';
      am.glAccount  = reconciled.glAccount || '';
    }
    const codingExplicit = !!derivedCodingOverride;
    const line = buildLineFromProduct(product, site, am, qty, codingExplicit);
    dispatch({ type: 'ADD_LINE', siteId, line });
  };

  // Routing-aware entry point used by the left Catalogue Panel + Quick Reorder.
  // If routing is set, fires the add immediately; otherwise queues the product
  // and lets the RoutingStrip's focus-jumping wizard collect Entity then Site.
  // codingOverride flows from the panel's Dept/CC filter chips when active.
  // categoryOverride flows from a multi-use product's "Use as" picker.
  // Pending catalogue-add held while the user resolves a site via SitePickerModal.
  // When set, the modal opens; on pick, we fire addCatalogueItem with the resolved site.
  const [sitePickerModal, setSitePickerModal] = useState(null); // { productId, qty, codingOverride, categoryOverride } | null

  const requestAddFromCatalogue = (productId, qty = 1, codingOverride = null, categoryOverride = null) => {
    // If a site is pre-selected in the catalogue dropdown, add directly — no modal.
    if (state.order.activeSiteId) {
      const siteId = state.order.activeSiteId;
      if (!state.order.sites.find(g => g.siteId === siteId)) {
        dispatch({ type: 'ADD_SITE_GROUP', siteId });
      }
      const site = state.sites.find(s => s.siteId === siteId);
      const outletId = site?.defaults?.outlet || site?.outlets?.[0]?.outletId || null;
      setTimeout(() => addCatalogueItem(productId, siteId, qty, outletId, codingOverride, categoryOverride), 0);
      return;
    }
    setSitePickerModal({ productId, qty, codingOverride, categoryOverride });
  };

  // Resolution path from the SitePickerModal. Ensures the site group exists, then
  // fires the pending add. The reducer's ADD_SITE_GROUP creates the group if new;
  // ADD_LINE inside addCatalogueItem will find it.
  const onSitePickerResolved = (siteId) => {
    if (!siteId) { setSitePickerModal(null); return; }
    const groups = state.order.sites;
    if (!groups.find(g => g.siteId === siteId)) {
      dispatch({ type: 'ADD_SITE_GROUP', siteId });
    }
    if (sitePickerModal) {
      const { productId, qty, codingOverride, categoryOverride } = sitePickerModal;
      const site = state.sites.find(s => s.siteId === siteId);
      const outletId = site?.defaults?.outlet || site?.outlets?.[0]?.outletId || null;
      // Add on the next tick so the reducer has applied ADD_SITE_GROUP first
      setTimeout(() => addCatalogueItem(productId, siteId, qty, outletId, codingOverride, categoryOverride), 0);
    }
    setSitePickerModal(null);
  };

  // When routing completes with a pending product queued, fire the add automatically.
  // codingOverride + categoryOverride were stored on pendingAdd so they survive the wizard.
  useEffect(() => {
    const r = state.order.routing;
    const p = state.order.pendingAdd;
    if (!p || !r?.legalEntity || !r?.siteId) return;
    const site = state.sites.find(s => s.siteId === r.siteId);
    const outletId = r.outletId || site?.defaults?.outlet || site?.outlets?.[0]?.outletId || null;
    addCatalogueItem(p.productId, r.siteId, p.qty, outletId, p.codingOverride || null, p.categoryOverride || null);
    dispatch({ type: 'CLEAR_PENDING_ADD' });
    // eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps
  }, [state.order.routing?.legalEntity, state.order.routing?.siteId, state.order.pendingAdd]);

  /* handleCreateProduct — single submit path for the rebuilt two-stage
     NewProductModal. The modal's payload carries:
       · name, categoryCode, categoryLabel
       · coding {dept, costCentre, glAccount} derived from the chosen category
       · treatment derived from the category
       · supplier (required — modal blocks submit when empty), supplierIsPending
       · uom, packSize, estPrice (optional — empty triggers RFQ), qty
       · siteId, addToCatalogue

     Outlet is NOT in the payload — that's the four-step selection model's job:
     outlet defaults to the site's placeholder default outlet here, and the
     user can override on the line after the fact. */
  const handleCreateProduct = (payload) => {
    const { name, supplier, supplierIsPending, siteId, uom, packSize, estPrice, qty, coding, treatment, addToCatalogue, categoryCode, categoryLabel, allowedCategories } = payload;
    setNewProductOpen(false);
    if (supplierIsPending) {
      dispatch({ type: 'ADD_SUPPLIER_PENDING', name: supplier });
    }
    // Build the product record. categoryCode + allowedCategories are stored
    // explicitly so the catalogue card's "Use as" picker has the data it
    // needs without re-deriving from gl/treatment.
    const product = {
      name,
      supplier,
      supplierId: state.suppliers.find(s => s.name === supplier)?.id || null,
      category: categoryLabel || 'Custom',
      categoryCode,
      allowedCategories: allowedCategories && allowedCategories.length > 1 ? allowedCategories : undefined,
      uom,
      packSize: packSize || null,
      price: estPrice,
      gl: coding.glAccount,
      treatment,
      isCustom: true
    };
    // Write to catalogue immediately if the user has a price (otherwise we wait
    // for the RFQ to come back, then write).
    if (addToCatalogue && estPrice && estPrice > 0) {
      dispatch({ type: 'ADD_TO_CATALOGUE', product });
    }
    // Build the line. Outlet defaults to the site's placeholder default
    // (typically GEN/General) — the user can change it on the line if they
    // know the goods are headed to a specific outlet.
    const site = state.sites.find(s => s.siteId === siteId);
    const defaultOutlet = site?.outlets?.find(o => o.isDefault) || site?.outlets?.[0];
    const line = {
      lineId: uid('LN'),
      productId: null,
      sku: null,
      name,
      supplier,
      qty,
      uom,
      packSize,
      price: estPrice || 0,
      vat: 20,
      coding: {
        legalEntity: site?.legalEntity,
        outlet: defaultOutlet?.outletId || '',
        dept: coding.dept,
        costCentre: coding.costCentre,
        glAccount: coding.glAccount
      },
      treatment,
      // No price → RFQ to discover one; price given → REQ direct to supplier
      issuesAs: (estPrice && estPrice > 0) ? 'REQ' : 'RFQ',
      notes: '',
      agentSuggestion: null,
      agentSuggestionStatus: 'accepted',
      isCustom: true,
      // When we couldn't write the product to catalogue yet (no price), this
      // flag tells the post-RFQ pipeline to write it after the quote lands.
      writeToCatalogueOnRfq: addToCatalogue && (!estPrice || estPrice <= 0)
    };
    dispatch({ type: 'ADD_LINE', siteId, line });
    // Anchor routing if not already set so the routing strip reflects where
    // this line lives. userInitiated: true because the user clicked Add in
    // the catalogue — this is an explicit human action.
    if (!state.order.routing?.siteId) {
      dispatch({ type: 'SET_ROUTING', patch: { legalEntity: site?.legalEntity, siteId, outletId: defaultOutlet?.outletId || '' }, userInitiated: true });
    }
  };

  // Bulk upload: agent has parsed the file and proposed an array of products;
  // user has reviewed/edited in the modal; now we materialise them as lines
  // and (optionally per row) write to catalogue. Each item carries a siteId —
  // a multi-site upload (Edinburgh + Mayfair in one file) groups by site and
  // dispatches one ADD_LINES_BULK per target site.
  const handleBulkConfirm = (defaultSiteId, items, addCatalogueByDefault, source = 'order_list') => {
    setBulkUploadOpen(false);
    if (items.length === 0) return;

    // Quotation uploads carry authoritative prices and bypass RFQ entirely.
    // Force catalogue write-back on (the supplier has given us a quoted price;
    // future orders of the same SKU should find it without re-quoting).
    const isQuotation = source === 'quotation';
    const writeCatalogueGlobal = isQuotation ? true : addCatalogueByDefault;

    // Onboard new suppliers (dedup). Rule: any supplier name not already on the
    // registry gets onboarded as pending. We don't rely solely on the
    // supplierIsPending flag — the review-stage row updates that flag as the user
    // edits, but defensive matching against state.suppliers catches edge cases
    // (e.g. user typed an unknown supplier without triggering the flag).
    const knownSupplierNames = new Set(state.suppliers.map(s => s.name.toLowerCase()));
    const newSuppliers = new Set();
    items.forEach(it => {
      if (!it.supplier) return;
      if (knownSupplierNames.has(it.supplier.toLowerCase())) return;
      newSuppliers.add(it.supplier);
    });
    newSuppliers.forEach(name => dispatch({ type: 'ADD_SUPPLIER_PENDING', name }));

    // Catalogue write-back for priced items
    items.forEach(it => {
      const writeIt = isQuotation || (it.addToCatalogue ?? addCatalogueByDefault);
      if (writeIt && it.estPrice > 0) {
        dispatch({ type: 'ADD_TO_CATALOGUE', product: {
          name: it.name,
          supplier: it.supplier,
          supplierId: state.suppliers.find(s => s.name === it.supplier)?.id || null,
          category: it.category || 'Custom',
          uom: it.uom || 'EACH',
          packSize: it.packSize || null,
          price: it.estPrice,
          gl: it.coding?.glAccount,
          treatment: it.treatment || 'Direct to P&L',
          isCustom: true
        }});
      }
    });

    // Group items by site — each row's siteId (set by the agent from the file)
    // wins; if missing or unknown, fall back to the modal's default site.
    const bySite = {};
    items.forEach(it => {
      let targetSiteId = it.siteId || defaultSiteId;
      if (!state.sites.some(s => s.siteId === targetSiteId)) targetSiteId = defaultSiteId;
      (bySite[targetSiteId] = bySite[targetSiteId] || []).push(it);
    });

    let firstSite = null;
    Object.entries(bySite).forEach(([siteId, siteItems]) => {
      const site = state.sites.find(s => s.siteId === siteId);
      if (!site) return;
      const defaultOutlet = site.outlets?.find(o => o.isDefault) || site.outlets?.[0];
      if (!firstSite) firstSite = { siteId, legalEntity: site.legalEntity, outletId: defaultOutlet?.outletId };

      const lines = siteItems.map(it => {
        const cd = it.coding || {};
        const estPriceNum = (typeof it.estPrice === 'number' && it.estPrice > 0) ? it.estPrice : 0;

        // Coding reconciliation — the agent may return:
        //   (a) a complete valid triple — use as-is
        //   (b) a partial triple (e.g. only GL, or GL + Dept) — derive the rest from
        //       the linkage tables via reconcileCodingPatch
        //   (c) an invalid triple — reconcile what we can, fall back to site default
        //       only where reconciliation fails
        //
        // Previously we used all-or-nothing: validation fail → drop the agent's GL
        // entirely and use site defaults. That meant if the agent inferred a
        // sensible GL but didn't fill Dept/CC, all three dimensions got overwritten
        // with the site default instead of letting the GL drive the cascade.
        const seed = {
          dept: cd.dept || '',
          costCentre: cd.costCentre || '',
          glAccount: cd.glAccount || ''
        };
        // Run reconcile from a blank slate with the agent's values as the patch.
        // This applies the linkage rules: GL → CC (when unambiguous), CC → Dept.
        const reconciledCoding = reconcileCodingPatch(
          { dept: '', costCentre: '', glAccount: '' },
          seed
        );
        const merged = { ...seed, ...reconciledCoding };
        const v = validateCoding({ department: merged.dept, costCentre: merged.costCentre, glAccount: merged.glAccount });
        const codingOk = v.ok;
        // Per-field fallback — only fields that didn't reconcile fall back to defaults.
        // Don't wipe a valid GL just because the CC was blank.
        const finalCoding = {
          legalEntity: site.legalEntity,
          outlet: it.outlet || defaultOutlet?.outletId,
          dept: merged.dept || defaultOutlet?.dept,
          costCentre: merged.costCentre || defaultOutlet?.cc,
          glAccount: merged.glAccount || defaultOutlet?.defaultGL
        };
        // Re-validate the final triple; if STILL invalid, fall back fully to site defaults
        // (this catches contradictory agent input that survived reconcile).
        const finalV = validateCoding({ department: finalCoding.dept, costCentre: finalCoding.costCentre, glAccount: finalCoding.glAccount });
        if (!finalV.ok) {
          finalCoding.dept = defaultOutlet?.dept;
          finalCoding.costCentre = defaultOutlet?.cc;
          finalCoding.glAccount = defaultOutlet?.defaultGL;
        }

        const issuesAs = isQuotation ? 'REQ' : (estPriceNum > 0 ? 'REQ' : 'RFQ');
        return {
          lineId: uid('LN'),
          productId: null,
          sku: null,
          name: it.name,
          supplier: it.supplier || '',
          qty: it.qty || 1,
          uom: it.uom || 'EACH',
          packSize: it.packSize || null,
          price: estPriceNum,
          vat: 20,
          coding: finalCoding,
          treatment: it.treatment || 'Direct to P&L',
          issuesAs,
          notes: finalV.ok && (!codingOk || !cd.dept || !cd.costCentre)
            ? `Coding derived: agent provided [${seed.dept || '?'}/${seed.costCentre || '?'}/${seed.glAccount || '?'}] → reconciled to [${finalCoding.dept}/${finalCoding.costCentre}/${finalCoding.glAccount}]`
            : (finalV.ok ? '' : `Coding fallback — agent input [${seed.dept || '?'}/${seed.costCentre || '?'}/${seed.glAccount || '?'}] couldn't reconcile.`),
          agentSuggestion: null,
          agentSuggestionStatus: 'accepted',
          isCustom: true,
          writeToCatalogueOnRfq: isQuotation ? false : ((it.addToCatalogue ?? addCatalogueByDefault) && estPriceNum <= 0),
          uploadSource: source
        };
      });

      console.log('[BulkUpload] dispatching ADD_LINES_BULK', { siteId, source, lineCount: lines.length });
      dispatch({ type: 'ADD_LINES_BULK', siteId, lines });
    });

    // Auto-reveal coding columns after a bulk upload. Bulk-uploaded lines always
    // carry agent-derived coding, and hiding it by default makes it look like
    // the lines are "uncategorised" when they aren't — the columns are just
    // collapsed. User can collapse again via the canvas toggle.
    setShowCodingCols(true);

    if (firstSite && !state.order.routing?.siteId) {
      dispatch({ type: 'SET_ROUTING', patch: { legalEntity: firstSite.legalEntity, siteId: firstSite.siteId, outletId: firstSite.outletId || '' }, userInitiated: false });
    }
  };

  const acceptAgentProposal = (proposal) => {
    const site = getSite(state, proposal.siteId);
    if (!site) return;
    const cd = proposal.coding || {};

    // Name-based heuristic backstop. If the agent didn't return Dept/CC/GL (or
    // returned weak coding), use product-name keywords to infer where the line
    // SHOULD land — instead of defaulting to the site's first outlet, which
    // for Mayfair is the General/shared outlet and would yield generic G&A
    // coding for a clearly-categorised product.
    //
    // Priority order per field:
    //   1. Agent's explicit value
    //   2. Heuristic from product name
    //   3. Site default (last resort — wrong-ish but never crashes)
    const hint = inferCodingFromName(proposal.productName);
    const hintedOutletId = hint ? pickOutletForCC(site, hint.costCentre) : null;

    const resolvedDept = cd.department || hint?.dept || site.defaults.departments[0];
    const resolvedCC   = cd.cost_centre || hint?.costCentre || site.defaults.costCentre;
    const resolvedGL   = cd.gl_account || hint?.glAccount || site.defaults.glAccount;
    const resolvedOutlet = cd.outlet || hintedOutletId || site.defaults.outlet;
    const resolvedTreatment = proposal.treatment || hint?.treatment || 'Direct to P&L';

    // Run the result through reconcileCodingPatch — if the agent supplied a GL
    // that doesn't match the (hinted) CC, reconcile will catch it.
    const reconciled = reconcileCodingPatch(
      { dept: '', costCentre: '', glAccount: '' },
      { dept: resolvedDept, costCentre: resolvedCC, glAccount: resolvedGL }
    );
    const finalDept = reconciled.dept || resolvedDept;
    const finalCC   = reconciled.costCentre || resolvedCC;
    const finalGL   = reconciled.glAccount || resolvedGL;

    const line = {
      lineId: uid('LN'),
      productId: null,
      sku: 'AD-HOC',
      name: proposal.productName,
      supplier: proposal.supplier,
      qty: 1,
      uom: 'EA',
      price: 0,
      vat: 20,
      coding: {
        legalEntity: cd.legal_entity || site.legalEntity,
        outlet: resolvedOutlet,
        dept: finalDept,
        costCentre: finalCC,
        glAccount: finalGL
      },
      treatment: resolvedTreatment,
      issuesAs: 'RFQ',  // no live price → RFQ
      notes: hint && !cd.department
        ? `Coding inferred from product name (heuristic): ${finalDept}/${finalCC}/${finalGL}. Closest analogue: ${proposal.closest_analogue || '—'}`
        : `Closest analogue: ${proposal.closest_analogue || '—'}`,
      agentSuggestion: { ...cd, confidence: proposal.confidence, reasoning: proposal.reasoning },
      agentSuggestionStatus: 'accepted',
      isCustom: true
    };
    dispatch({ type: 'ADD_LINE', siteId: proposal.siteId, line });
    dispatch({ type: 'AGENT_MESSAGE_ADD', message: {
      id: uid('MSG'), role: 'system', t: nowIso(),
      text: `Added "${proposal.productName}" as RFQ on ${proposal.siteId}.`
    }});
  };

  const submitOrder = () => {
    setRoutingModalOpen(true);
  };

  const confirmSubmit = () => {
    const orderEventId = uid('EVT');
    const submittedAt = nowIso();

    /* ---------- ORDER event (root) ----------
       Existing flat payload preserved so OrdersListView / OrderListRow / the
       Submitted view continue to read the same fields. eventType / parentEventId /
       status added for the event-shape contract. */
    const orderEvent = {
      eventId: orderEventId,
      eventType: EVENT_TYPE.ORDER,
      parentEventId: null,
      timestamp: submittedAt,
      status: 'submitted',
      orderId: state.order.id,
      orderDescription: state.order.description || '',
      requester: state.order.requester,
      requesterRole: state.order.requesterRole || 'Operations',
      businessArea: state.order.sites.length > 1 ? 'multi-site' : (state.order.sites[0]?.siteId || '—'),
      siteIds: state.order.sites.map(s => s.siteId),
      legalEntities: [...new Set(state.order.sites.map(s => {
        const masterSite = state.sites.find(x => x.siteId === s.siteId);
        return masterSite?.legalEntity;
      }).filter(Boolean))],
      netTotal: totals.net,
      taxTotal: totals.tax,
      grossTotal: totals.gross,
      reqCount: routingPlan.reqs.length,
      rfqCount: routingPlan.rfqs.length,
      lineCount: state.order.sites.reduce((n, s) => n + s.lines.length, 0),
      // carried forward data points (per Order frame, Part B)
      lines: state.order.sites.flatMap(s => s.lines.map(l => {
        const lineNet = l.qty * l.price;
        const lineTax = lineNet * (l.vat / 100);
        return {
          siteId: s.siteId,
          product: l.name,
          sku: l.sku,
          qty: l.qty,
          uom: l.uom,
          unitPrice: l.price,
          vatPct: l.vat,
          net: lineNet,
          tax: lineTax,
          gross: lineNet + lineTax,
          supplier: l.supplier,
          codingString: `${l.coding.legalEntity} · ${s.siteId} · ${l.coding.outlet} · ${l.coding.dept} · ${l.coding.costCentre} · ${l.coding.glAccount}`,
          coding: l.coding,
          projectCode: l.projectCode || '—',
          serviceTerm: l.serviceTerm || '—',
          treatment: l.treatment,
          routing: l.issuesAs,
          catalogueStatus: l.isCustom ? 'Product-Definition-Required' : 'Catalogue',
          uploadSource: l.uploadSource || 'manual'
        };
      })),
      requiredBy: state.order.requiredBy || '—'
    };

    /* ---------- ID counters ----------
       RFQ-2026-NNNN / REQ-2026-NNNN are continuous across submissions. The
       offset comes from how many of each type already exist in the ledger so
       numbers never repeat. Production would persist a counter; the artefact
       infers from ledger length, which is sufficient for the demo. */
    const existingRfqCount = selectRfqEvents(state.ledger).length;
    const existingReqCount = selectRequisitionEvents(state.ledger).length;

    /* ---------- RFQ events (one per RFQ-routed line) ----------
       Spec: one supplier per line, status pending until quote received.
       parentEventId links back to the order so AssociatedRequisitionsPanel-style
       lineage works downstream. */
    const rfqEvents = routingPlan.rfqs.map((line, idx) => {
      const site = state.sites.find(s => s.siteId === line.siteId);
      return {
        eventId: uid('EVT'),
        eventType: EVENT_TYPE.RFQ,
        parentEventId: orderEventId,
        timestamp: submittedAt,
        status: 'pending',  // pending | quoted | accepted | rejected | timed_out
        rfqId: newRfqId(existingRfqCount + idx + 1),
        legalEntity: line.coding.legalEntity,
        siteId: line.siteId,
        siteName: site?.siteName || line.siteId,
        supplier: line.supplier,
        line: {
          product: line.name,
          sku: line.sku,
          qty: line.qty,
          uom: line.uom,
          targetPrice: line.price || 0,  // operator's expected price; 0 = no anchor given
          vatPct: line.vat,
          coding: line.coding,
          codingString: `${line.coding.legalEntity} · ${line.siteId} · ${line.coding.outlet} · ${line.coding.dept} · ${line.coding.costCentre} · ${line.coding.glAccount}`,
          projectCode: line.projectCode || '—',
          serviceTerm: line.serviceTerm || '—',
          catalogueStatus: line.isCustom ? 'Product-Definition-Required' : 'Catalogue',
          treatment: line.treatment
        },
        quote: null,  // set when quote received: { unitPrice, currency, validUntil, supplierResponse, deltaVsTarget }
        requester: state.order.requester
      };
    });

    /* ---------- REQUISITION events (one per LE | Site | Supplier partition) ----------
       Status starts 'draft' — operator submits-for-approval to move to
       'pending_approval', which gates the downstream PO send-to-supplier.
       Budget chip derived now so the wireframe can render it without a backing
       store. partitionKey carried for the eventual PO emission. */
    const reqEvents = routingPlan.reqs.map((group, idx) => {
      const site = state.sites.find(s => s.siteId === group.siteId);
      const groupNet = group.lines.reduce((sum, l) => sum + (l.qty * l.price), 0);
      const groupTax = group.lines.reduce((sum, l) => sum + (l.qty * l.price * (l.vat / 100)), 0);
      return {
        eventId: uid('EVT'),
        eventType: EVENT_TYPE.REQUISITION,
        parentEventId: orderEventId,
        timestamp: submittedAt,
        status: 'draft',  // draft | pending_approval | approved | rejected | sent_back
        requisitionId: newReqId(existingReqCount + idx + 1),
        legalEntity: group.legalEntity,
        siteId: group.siteId,
        siteName: site?.siteName || group.siteId,
        supplier: group.supplier,
        partitionKey: `${group.legalEntity}__${group.siteId}__${group.supplier}`,
        lines: group.lines.map(l => ({
          product: l.name,
          sku: l.sku,
          qty: l.qty,
          uom: l.uom,
          unitPrice: l.price,
          vatPct: l.vat,
          net: l.qty * l.price,
          tax: l.qty * l.price * (l.vat / 100),
          gross: l.qty * l.price * (1 + l.vat / 100),
          supplier: l.supplier,
          coding: l.coding,
          codingString: `${l.coding.legalEntity} · ${group.siteId} · ${l.coding.outlet} · ${l.coding.dept} · ${l.coding.costCentre} · ${l.coding.glAccount}`,
          projectCode: l.projectCode || '—',
          serviceTerm: l.serviceTerm || '—',
          treatment: l.treatment,
          catalogueStatus: l.isCustom ? 'Product-Definition-Required' : 'Catalogue'
        })),
        netTotal: groupNet,
        taxTotal: groupTax,
        grossTotal: groupNet + groupTax,
        budgetStatus: deriveBudgetStatus(groupNet),
        approvalFlow: null,  // populated on submit-for-approval: { stages: [...], currentStage }
        poEventId: null,     // set once approved and PO event is emitted
        requester: state.order.requester
      };
    });

    const events = [orderEvent, ...rfqEvents, ...reqEvents];
    dispatch({ type: 'SUBMIT_ORDER', events });
    setRoutingModalOpen(false);
    // After submit: jump straight to the tracker for the newly-created order so
    // the requester can see the thread spawn (RFQs / requisitions / etc.) in
    // real time. The Orders tab is still reachable explicitly if they want it.
    const newOrderId = state.order.id;
    dispatch({ type: 'NEW_ORDER' });   // mint a fresh draft for next time
    setTrackerOrigin({ kind: 'order', id: newOrderId });
    setActiveNav('tracker');
  };

  const newOrder = () => {
    dispatch({ type: 'NEW_ORDER' });
    setView('order');
  };

  /* ---------- filtered catalogue ---------- */
  const filteredCatalogue = useMemo(() => {
    // Dept/CC filters use the linkage chain: product → GL (via category or product.gl)
    // → set of CCs that GL is allowed for → set of Depts those CCs belong to.
    // A product is shown only if it's compatible with the active Dept/CC.
    return state.catalogue.filter(p => {
      if (activeCategory !== 'All' && p.category !== activeCategory) return false;
      if (activeSupplier !== 'All' && p.supplier !== activeSupplier) return false;
      if (searchTerm && !p.name.toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm.toLowerCase()) && !p.sku.toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm.toLowerCase())) return false;
      if (activeCC !== 'All' || activeDept !== 'All') {
        // Resolve product → GL → eligible CCs → check against active filter
        const productGL = p.gl;
        if (!productGL) return false;  // no GL means we can't link to a CC
        const eligibleCCs = ccsForGL(productGL);
        if (activeCC !== 'All') {
          if (!eligibleCCs.some(c => c.code === activeCC)) return false;
        }
        if (activeDept !== 'All') {
          if (!eligibleCCs.some(c => c.dept === activeDept)) return false;
        }
      }
      return true;
    });
  }, [state.catalogue, activeCategory, activeSupplier, activeDept, activeCC, searchTerm]);

  /* ---------- validation ---------- */
  const validation = useMemo(() => {
    const issues = [];
    state.order.sites.forEach(s => {
      s.lines.forEach(l => {
        if (!l.supplier) {
          issues.push({ lineId: l.lineId, name: l.name, msg: 'Supplier needed', kind: 'missing' });
        }
        const c = l.coding;
        if (!c.legalEntity || !c.outlet || !c.dept || !c.costCentre || !c.glAccount) {
          issues.push({ lineId: l.lineId, name: l.name, msg: 'Missing required coding', kind: 'missing' });
        }
      });
    });
    return issues;
  }, [state.order]);

  return (
    <div className="pf-root pf-page-outer">
      <style>{STYLES}</style>
      <div className="pf-page">
        <div className="pf-shell">
          <Sidebar activeNav={activeNav} setActiveNav={setActiveNav} currentUser={currentUser} switchUser={switchUser} resetDb={resetDb} />
          <div className="pf-main">
            <TopBar
              user={state.user}
              agentOpen={state.agent.open}
              onToggleAgent={() => dispatch({ type: 'TOGGLE_AGENT', open: !state.agent.open })}
              pendingSuggestions={state.agent.pendingSuggestions?.length || 0}
            />
            {view === 'order' ? (
              <CataloguePanel
                catalogue={state.catalogue}
                filtered={filteredCatalogue}
                suppliers={state.suppliers}
                sites={state.sites}
                userAssignedSites={state.user.assignedSites}
                recentlyAdded={state.recentlyAdded}
                searchTerm={searchTerm}
                setSearchTerm={setSearchTerm}
                activeCategory={activeCategory}
                setActiveCategory={setActiveCategory}
                activeSupplier={activeSupplier}
                setActiveSupplier={setActiveSupplier}
                activeDept={activeDept}
                setActiveDept={setActiveDept}
                activeCC={activeCC}
                setActiveCC={setActiveCC}
                onAdd={requestAddFromCatalogue}
                onAddCustom={() => { setNewProductSeed({ name: '', supplier: '', siteId: state.user.assignedSites[0] }); setNewProductOpen(true); }}
                onUploadList={() => { setBulkUploadSiteId(state.order.routing?.siteId || state.user.assignedSites[0]); setBulkUploadOpen(true); }}
                activeRouting={state.order.routing}
                cartExpanded={cartExpanded}
                setCartExpanded={setCartExpanded}
                totals={totals}
                hasLines={state.order.sites.some(s => s.lines.length > 0)}
                validation={validation}
                onSubmit={submitOrder}
                onSaveDraft={() => {}}
                onDiscard={newOrder}
                state={state}
                dispatch={dispatch}
                addCatalogueItem={addCatalogueItem}
                activeSiteId={state.order.activeSiteId}
                onSetActiveSite={(siteId) => dispatch({ type: 'SET_ACTIVE_SITE', siteId })}
              />
          ) : view === 'invoicing' ? (
            <InvoicingView
              state={state}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              currentUser={currentUser}
            />
          ) : view === 'flow-requests' ? (
            <FlowRequestsListView
              requests={state.flowRequests}
              suppliers={state.suppliers}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              onNew={() => setActiveNav('new-flow-request')}
              onOpenTracker={(originDoc) => { setTrackerOrigin(originDoc || null); setActiveNav('tracker'); }}
            />
          ) : view === 'new-flow-request' ? (
            <NewFlowRequestView
              suppliers={state.suppliers}
              currentUser={currentUser}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              onDone={() => setActiveNav('flow-requests')}
            />
          ) : view === 'orders' ? (
            <OrdersListView
              ledger={selectOrderEvents(state.ledger)}
              onNewOrder={() => { setActiveNav('new-order'); }}
              onOpenTracker={(originDoc) => { setTrackerOrigin(originDoc || null); setActiveNav('tracker'); }}
            />
          ) : view === 'tracker' ? (
            trackerOrigin ? (
              <ProgressTrackerView
                originDoc={trackerOrigin}
                ledger={state.ledger}
                dispatch={dispatch}
                currentUser={currentUser}
                onNavigate={(navId, focusEvId) => { if (focusEvId) setApprovalFocus(focusEvId); setActiveNav(navId); }}
                onNewOrder={() => { setActiveNav('new-order'); }}
                onBack={() => { setTrackerOrigin(null); }}
              />
            ) : (
              <TrackerListView
                ledger={state.ledger}
                currentUser={currentUser}
                onOpen={(originDoc) => setTrackerOrigin(originDoc)}
                onNewOrder={() => setActiveNav('new-order')}
              />
            )
          ) : view === 'sup-portal' ? (
            <SupplierPortalView
              ledger={state.ledger}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              currentUser={currentUser}
              activeNav={activeNav}
              setActiveNav={setActiveNav}
              onOpenTracker={(originDoc) => { setTrackerOrigin(originDoc || null); setActiveNav('tracker'); }}
            />
          ) : view === 'rfqs' ? (
            <RfqsView
              ledger={state.ledger}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              onNewOrder={() => { setActiveNav('new-order'); }}
              suppliers={state.suppliers}
              sites={state.sites}
              onOpenTracker={(originDoc) => { setTrackerOrigin(originDoc || null); setActiveNav('tracker'); }}
            />
          ) : view === 'requisitions' ? (
            <RequisitionsView
              ledger={state.ledger}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              currentUser={currentUser}
              onNewOrder={() => { setActiveNav('new-order'); }}
              onOpenTracker={(originDoc) => { setTrackerOrigin(originDoc || null); setActiveNav('tracker'); }}
            />
          ) : view === 'po' ? (
            <POsView
              ledger={state.ledger}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              currentUser={currentUser}
              onNewOrder={() => { setActiveNav('new-order'); }}
              onOpenTracker={(originDoc) => { setTrackerOrigin(originDoc || null); setActiveNav('tracker'); }}
              onReviewInApprovals={(eventId) => { setApprovalFocus(eventId || null); setActiveNav('po-approvals'); }}
            />
          ) : view === 'po-approvals' ? (
            <POApprovalsView
              ledger={state.ledger}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              currentUser={currentUser}
              onNewOrder={() => { setActiveNav('new-order'); }}
              focusId={approvalFocus}
            />
          ) : view === 'confirmations' ? (
            <ConfirmationsView
              ledger={state.ledger}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              onNewOrder={() => { setActiveNav('new-order'); }}
            />
          ) : view === 'grn' ? (
            <GRNsView
              ledger={state.ledger}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              onNewOrder={() => { setActiveNav('new-order'); }}
            />
          ) : view === 'invoices' ? (
            <InvoicesView
              ledger={state.ledger}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              suppliers={state.suppliers}
              onNewOrder={() => { setActiveNav('new-order'); }}
              onOpenInMatching={() => setActiveNav('invoice-matching')}
              onOpenTracker={(originDoc) => { setTrackerOrigin(originDoc || null); setActiveNav('tracker'); }}
              onReviewInApprovals={(eventId) => { setApprovalFocus(eventId || null); setActiveNav('invoice-approvals'); }}
            />
          ) : view === 'invoice-matching' ? (
            <InvoiceMatchingView
              ledger={state.ledger}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              suppliers={state.suppliers}
              onNewOrder={() => { setActiveNav('new-order'); }}
            />
          ) : view === 'invoice-ingestion' ? (
            <InvoiceIngestionView
              ledger={state.ledger}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              onNewOrder={() => { setActiveNav('new-order'); }}
              onCommitted={() => { setActiveNav('invoice-matching'); }}
            />
          ) : view === 'rfq-ingestion' ? (
            <RfqIngestionView
              ledger={state.ledger}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              onNewOrder={() => { setActiveNav('new-order'); }}
            />
          ) : view === 'invoice-approvals' ? (
            <InvoiceApprovalsView
              ledger={state.ledger}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              currentUser={currentUser}
              onNewOrder={() => { setActiveNav('new-order'); }}
              focusId={approvalFocus}
            />
          ) : view === 'suppliers' ? (
            <SuppliersView
              suppliers={state.suppliers}
              sites={state.sites}
              dispatch={dispatch}
            />
          ) : (
            /* Fallback: previously rendered the SubmittedView (transaction
               ledger). That view is deprecated — the submit-handler now mints
               a fresh draft and stays on the canvas. If we ever land here
               (e.g. stale restored view-state from before this change), show
               an empty new-order workspace by routing to it. */
            <div style={{ flex: 1, padding: '40px 24px', background: '#ECEFF5', display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center' }}>
              <div className="pf-display" style={{ fontSize: '18px', fontWeight: 600, color: '#0D1424', marginBottom: '8px' }}>Order submitted</div>
              <div style={{ fontSize: '12.5px', color: '#586278', marginBottom: '14px' }}>Start a new draft, or check the Orders tab to see what was just submitted.</div>
              <button onClick={newOrder} className="pf-btn-primary">
                <span style={{ display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}><Plus size={11} /> New order</span>
              </button>
            </div>
          )}
        </div>

        {/* P2P Assistant side drawer — sibling of .pf-main inside .pf-shell */}
        {state.agent.open && (
          <FloatingAgent
            state={state}
            dispatch={dispatch}
            onAcceptProposal={acceptAgentProposal}
            onNavigate={(navId) => { setActiveNav(navId); }}
          />
        )}
        </div>

      {/* Modals render inside pf-page, outside pf-shell */}
      {/* New product modal */}
      {newProductOpen && (
        <NewProductModal
          seed={newProductSeed}
          suppliers={state.suppliers}
          sites={state.sites.filter(s => state.user.assignedSites.includes(s.siteId))}
          onCancel={() => setNewProductOpen(false)}
          onSubmit={handleCreateProduct}
        />
      )}
      {bulkUploadOpen && (
        <BulkUploadModal
          seedSiteId={bulkUploadSiteId || state.user.assignedSites[0]}
          sites={state.sites.filter(s => state.user.assignedSites.includes(s.siteId))}
          suppliers={state.suppliers}
          state={state}
          onCancel={() => setBulkUploadOpen(false)}
          onConfirm={handleBulkConfirm}
        />
      )}
      {routingModalOpen && (
        <RoutingPreviewModal
          plan={routingPlan}
          totals={totals}
          onCancel={() => setRoutingModalOpen(false)}
          onConfirm={confirmSubmit}
        />
      )}
      {sitePickerModal && (() => {
        const permittedSitesList = state.sites.filter(s => state.user.assignedSites.includes(s.siteId));
        const permittedLeNames = Array.from(new Set(permittedSitesList.map(s => s.legalEntity)));
        const permittedLEsList = LEGAL_ENTITIES.filter(le => permittedLeNames.includes(le.name));
        const product = state.catalogue.find(p => p.id === sitePickerModal.productId);
        return (
          <SitePickerModal
            permittedSites={permittedSitesList}
            permittedLEs={permittedLEsList}
            currentOrderSiteIds={state.order.sites.map(s => s.siteId)}
            productName={product?.name || null}
            onClose={() => setSitePickerModal(null)}
            onPick={onSitePickerResolved}
          />
        );
      })()}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

/* =====================================================
   FLOW REQUESTS — New Request wizard + list view
   ===================================================== */

// Status pill helper
function FRStatusPill({ status }) {
  const map = {
    draft:               { label: 'Draft',            bg: '#E8ECF4', color: '#586278' },
    sent:                { label: 'Sent to supplier', bg: 'rgba(15,122,216,0.10)', color: '#0F7AD8' },
    supplier_responded:  { label: 'Response received', bg: 'rgba(14,140,158,0.12)', color: '#0E8C9E' },
    accepted:            { label: 'Accepted',          bg: 'rgba(14,140,158,0.12)', color: '#0E8C9E' },
    rejected:            { label: 'Rejected',          bg: 'rgba(179,58,31,0.10)', color: '#B33A1F' },
  };
  const s = map[status] || map.draft;
  return (
    <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9px', padding: '2px 8px', borderRadius: '3px', background: s.bg, color: s.color, border: `1px solid ${s.color}40`, fontWeight: 600, letterSpacing: '0.06em', textTransform: 'uppercase' }}>
      {s.label}
    </span>
  );
}

/* ── Requests list ── */
function FlowRequestsListView({ requests, suppliers, dispatch, onNew, onOpenTracker }) {
  const [selected, setSelected] = useState(null);
  const req = selected ? requests.find(r => r.id === selected) : null;

  return (
    <div style={{ flex: 1, display: 'flex', overflow: 'hidden', background: '#ECEFF5' }}>
      {/* Left: table */}
      <div style={{ flex: 1, display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', minWidth: 0 }}>
        {/* Header */}
        <div style={{ background: '#fff', borderBottom: '1px solid #CBD3E0', padding: '12px 20px', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '12px' }}>
          <div>
            <div className="pf-display" style={{ fontSize: '16px', fontWeight: 600 }}>Requests</div>
            <div style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#8892A6', marginTop: '2px' }}>{requests.length} total · {requests.filter(r => r.status === 'supplier_responded').length} awaiting your review</div>
          </div>
          <button onClick={onNew} className="pf-btn-primary" style={{ marginLeft: 'auto', display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px', fontSize: '11.5px' }}>
            <Plus size={12} /> New request
          </button>
        </div>

        {/* Table */}
        <div style={{ flex: 1, overflowY: 'auto', padding: '16px 20px' }} className="pf-scroll">
          {requests.length === 0 ? (
            <div style={{ border: '1.5px dashed #CBD3E0', borderRadius: '10px', padding: '60px 24px', textAlign: 'center', background: '#fff' }}>
              <Send size={28} color="#CBD3E0" strokeWidth={1.5} style={{ margin: '0 auto 12px' }} />
              <div style={{ fontSize: '14px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500 }}>No requests yet</div>
              <div style={{ fontSize: '12px', color: '#586278', margin: '6px 0 16px' }}>Send a request to a supplier for products not yet in your catalogue.</div>
              <button onClick={onNew} className="pf-btn-primary" style={{ display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}>
                <Plus size={12} /> New request
              </button>
            </div>
          ) : (
            <div style={{ background: '#fff', border: '1px solid #CBD3E0', borderRadius: '8px', overflow: 'hidden' }}>
              {/* Col headers */}
              <div style={{ display: 'grid', gridTemplateColumns: '120px 1fr 160px 100px 80px', gap: '0', padding: '8px 16px', background: '#ECEFF5', borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4' }} className="pf-label">
                <span>ID</span><span>Summary</span><span>Supplier</span><span>Status</span><span style={{ textAlign: 'right' }}>Lines</span>
              </div>
              {requests.map((r, i) => (
                <div key={r.id}
                  onClick={() => setSelected(r.id === selected ? null : r.id)}
                  style={{ display: 'grid', gridTemplateColumns: '120px 1fr 160px 100px 80px', gap: '0', padding: '11px 16px', borderBottom: i < requests.length - 1 ? '1px solid #E8ECF4' : 'none', cursor: 'pointer', background: r.id === selected ? 'rgba(15,122,216,0.04)' : '#fff', borderLeft: r.id === selected ? '3px solid #0F7AD8' : '3px solid transparent' }}
                >
                  <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#0F7AD8' }}>{r.id}</span>
                  <div>
                    <div style={{ fontSize: '12px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500 }}>{r.lines.map(l => l.name).join(', ').slice(0, 60)}{r.lines.map(l => l.name).join(', ').length > 60 ? '…' : ''}</div>
                    <div style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#8892A6', marginTop: '1px' }}>{new Date(r.createdAt).toLocaleDateString('en-GB', { day: 'numeric', month: 'short', year: 'numeric' })}</div>
                  </div>
                  <span style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', color: '#586278', alignSelf: 'center' }}>{r.supplierName || <span style={{ color: '#CBD3E0' }}>—</span>}</span>
                  <span style={{ alignSelf: 'center' }}><FRStatusPill status={r.status} /></span>
                  <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#586278', textAlign: 'right', alignSelf: 'center' }}>{r.lines.length}</span>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          )}
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Right: detail panel */}
      {req && (
        <div className="pf-fade-in" style={{ width: '400px', flexShrink: 0, borderLeft: '1px solid #CBD3E0', background: '#fff', display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', overflow: 'hidden' }}>
          <FlowRequestDetail
            req={req}
            suppliers={suppliers}
            dispatch={dispatch}
            onClose={() => setSelected(null)}
          />
        </div>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}

/* ── Request detail panel ── */
function FlowRequestDetail({ req, suppliers, dispatch, onClose }) {
  const [supplierNote, setSupplierNote] = useState('');
  const [simulateOpen, setSimulateOpen] = useState(false);
  const [simPrices, setSimPrices] = useState({});

  const canAccept = req.status === 'supplier_responded' && req.supplierLines;

  // Demo: simulate supplier responding
  const handleSimulateResponse = () => {
    const prices = {};
    req.lines.forEach(l => { prices[l.id] = l.estPrice ? l.estPrice * (0.9 + Math.random() * 0.25) : 10 + Math.random() * 40; });
    dispatch({ type: 'FLOW_REQUEST_SUPPLIER_RESPOND', id: req.id, prices, supplierNote: 'Thank you for your enquiry. Please see our pricing below. All items available for next-day delivery.' });
    setSimulateOpen(false);
  };

  const handleAccept = () => {
    dispatch({ type: 'FLOW_REQUEST_ACCEPT', id: req.id });
    // TODO: in full impl, create draft order from supplierLines
  };

  return (
    <>
      {/* Panel header */}
      <div style={{ padding: '12px 16px', borderBottom: '1px solid #CBD3E0', background: '#FAFBFD', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px' }}>
        <div style={{ flex: 1 }}>
          <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#0F7AD8' }}>{req.id}</span>
          <div style={{ fontSize: '12px', fontWeight: 600, color: '#0D1424', marginTop: '2px' }}>{req.supplierName || 'No supplier selected'}</div>
        </div>
        <FRStatusPill status={req.status} />
        <button onClick={onClose} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ width: '26px', height: '26px', padding: 0, display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center' }}><X size={12} /></button>
      </div>

      <div style={{ flex: 1, overflowY: 'auto', padding: '14px 16px' }} className="pf-scroll">
        {/* Lines requested */}
        <div className="pf-label" style={{ marginBottom: '8px' }}>Requested items</div>
        <div style={{ border: '1px solid #E8ECF4', borderRadius: '6px', overflow: 'hidden', marginBottom: '14px' }}>
          {req.lines.map((l, i) => (
            <div key={l.id} style={{ display: 'grid', gridTemplateColumns: '1fr 50px 70px 70px', gap: '8px', padding: '8px 12px', borderBottom: i < req.lines.length - 1 ? '1px solid #E8ECF4' : 'none', background: i % 2 === 0 ? '#fff' : '#FAFBFD', alignItems: 'center' }}>
              <div>
                <div style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500 }}>{l.name}</div>
                {l.note && <div style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#8892A6' }}>{l.note}</div>}
              </div>
              <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#586278' }}>×{l.qty}</span>
              <span style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#8892A6' }}>{l.uom}</span>
              <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#586278', textAlign: 'right' }}>{l.estPrice ? `£${l.estPrice.toFixed(2)}` : '—'}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        {/* Supplier response */}
        {req.supplierLines && (
          <>
            <div className="pf-label" style={{ marginBottom: '8px', color: '#0E8C9E' }}>Supplier response</div>
            {req.supplierNote && (
              <div style={{ padding: '8px 12px', background: 'rgba(14,140,158,0.06)', border: '1px solid rgba(14,140,158,0.20)', borderRadius: '6px', fontSize: '11.5px', color: '#0D1424', marginBottom: '10px', lineHeight: 1.5 }}>
                {req.supplierNote}
              </div>
            )}
            <div style={{ border: '1px solid #E8ECF4', borderRadius: '6px', overflow: 'hidden', marginBottom: '14px' }}>
              {req.supplierLines.map((l, i) => (
                <div key={l.id} style={{ display: 'grid', gridTemplateColumns: '1fr 50px 80px', gap: '8px', padding: '8px 12px', borderBottom: i < req.supplierLines.length - 1 ? '1px solid #E8ECF4' : 'none', background: i % 2 === 0 ? '#fff' : '#FAFBFD', alignItems: 'center' }}>
                  <div>
                    <div style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500 }}>{l.name}</div>
                    {l.supplierNote && <div style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#8892A6' }}>{l.supplierNote}</div>}
                    {!l.available && <div style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#B33A1F', fontWeight: 500 }}>Not available</div>}
                  </div>
                  <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#586278' }}>×{l.qty}</span>
                  <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '12px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 600, textAlign: 'right' }}>£{(l.supplierPrice || 0).toFixed(2)}</span>
                </div>
              ))}
              <div style={{ padding: '8px 12px', background: '#ECEFF5', display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'space-between', alignItems: 'center' }}>
                <span style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#586278' }}>Total (est.)</span>
                <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '13px', fontWeight: 700, color: '#0D1424' }}>
                  £{req.supplierLines.reduce((s, l) => s + (l.available !== false ? (l.supplierPrice || 0) * l.qty : 0), 0).toFixed(2)}
                </span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </>
        )}

        {/* Thread */}
        {req.thread.length > 0 && (
          <>
            <div className="pf-label" style={{ marginBottom: '8px' }}>Activity</div>
            <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '6px', marginBottom: '14px' }}>
              {req.thread.map((t, i) => (
                <div key={i} style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#586278', display: 'flex', gap: '8px' }}>
                  <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9px', color: '#8892A6', flexShrink: 0, marginTop: '1px' }}>{new Date(t.at).toLocaleDateString('en-GB', { day: 'numeric', month: 'short' })}</span>
                  <span><b style={{ color: '#0D1424' }}>{t.by}</b> — {t.text}</span>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </>
        )}

        {/* Demo: simulate supplier response */}
        {req.status === 'sent' && (
          <div style={{ padding: '10px 12px', background: 'rgba(15,122,216,0.05)', border: '1px dashed rgba(15,122,216,0.25)', borderRadius: '6px', fontSize: '11px', color: '#586278' }}>
            <div style={{ fontWeight: 500, color: '#0F7AD8', marginBottom: '4px' }}>Demo</div>
            Simulate the supplier responding with pricing:
            <button onClick={handleSimulateResponse} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', marginTop: '8px', display: 'block', width: '100%' }}>
              Simulate supplier response →
            </button>
          </div>
        )}
      </div>

      {/* Action bar */}
      {canAccept && req.status !== 'accepted' && req.status !== 'rejected' && (
        <div style={{ padding: '10px 16px', borderTop: '1px solid #CBD3E0', display: 'flex', gap: '8px', background: '#FAFBFD' }}>
          <button onClick={() => dispatch({ type: 'FLOW_REQUEST_REJECT', id: req.id })} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#B33A1F' }}>Decline</button>
          <button onClick={handleAccept} className="pf-btn-primary" style={{ flex: 1, fontSize: '11.5px' }}>
            Accept &amp; create draft order
          </button>
        </div>
      )}
      {req.status === 'accepted' && (
        <div style={{ padding: '10px 16px', borderTop: '1px solid #CBD3E0', background: 'rgba(14,140,158,0.05)', fontSize: '11.5px', color: '#0E8C9E', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '6px' }}>
          <Check size={13} /> Accepted — draft order created
        </div>
      )}
    </>
  );
}

/* ── New request wizard ── */
const FR_CHAT_PLACEHOLDER = `Type what you need — e.g.\n"20 boxes of nitrile gloves size M, 10 antibacterial hand soaps, 5 litres of floor cleaner"`;

function NewFlowRequestView({ suppliers, currentUser, dispatch, onDone }) {
  const [stage, setStage] = useState('chat'); // chat | review | supplier | sent
  const [input, setInput] = useState('');
  const [messages, setMessages] = useState([
    { role: 'assistant', text: 'Hi! Tell me what products you need and how many. You can be as specific or as brief as you like — I\'ll turn it into a request for you.' }
  ]);
  const [lines, setLines] = useState([]); // parsed items
  const [parsing, setParsing] = useState(false);
  const [selectedSupplier, setSelectedSupplier] = useState('');
  const [supplierTypeFilter, setSupplierTypeFilter] = useState('All');
  const [buyerNote, setBuyerNote] = useState('');
  const [editingLine, setEditingLine] = useState(null);
  const bottomRef = useRef(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (bottomRef.current) bottomRef.current.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' });
  }, [messages, parsing]);

  const parseProductsFromText = async (text) => {
    setParsing(true);
    try {
      const response = await fetch('https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({
          model: 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514',
          max_tokens: 1000,
          system: `You are a procurement assistant. The user will describe products they need. Extract them into a JSON array.
Each item: { "name": string, "qty": number, "uom": string (EACH/BOX/KG/LTR/CASE/PACK/ROLL/PAIR), "estPrice": null, "note": string }.
Infer sensible UoM from the product name. Return ONLY the JSON array, no other text.`,
          messages: [{ role: 'user', content: text }]
        })
      });
      const data = await response.json();
      const raw = data.content?.[0]?.text || '[]';
      const clean = raw.replace(/```json|```/g, '').trim();
      const parsed = JSON.parse(clean);
      const withIds = parsed.map((l, i) => ({ ...l, id: `line_${Date.now()}_${i}` }));
      setLines(withIds);
      setMessages(prev => [...prev,
        { role: 'user', text },
        { role: 'assistant', text: `I've pulled out ${withIds.length} item${withIds.length !== 1 ? 's' : ''} from your message. Review them below and make any changes before selecting a supplier.`, items: withIds }
      ]);
      setStage('review');
    } catch (e) {
      setMessages(prev => [...prev,
        { role: 'user', text },
        { role: 'assistant', text: 'Sorry, I had trouble parsing that. Could you try again with a clearer list?' }
      ]);
    }
    setParsing(false);
  };

  const handleSend = () => {
    const t = input.trim();
    if (!t) return;
    setInput('');
    if (stage === 'chat') {
      parseProductsFromText(t);
    } else {
      setMessages(prev => [...prev, { role: 'user', text: t }, { role: 'assistant', text: 'Got it! Review your items in the table and select a supplier when ready.' }]);
    }
  };

  const handleSubmit = () => {
    if (!selectedSupplier || lines.length === 0) return;
    const sup = suppliers.find(s => s.id === selectedSupplier);
    const id = `FRQ-${Date.now()}`;
    dispatch({ type: 'FLOW_REQUEST_CREATE', lines, buyerNote, createdBy: currentUser?.name || 'You' });
    // Find the newly created request and send it
    setTimeout(() => {
      dispatch({
        type: 'FLOW_REQUEST_SEND',
        id: id,
        supplierId: selectedSupplier,
        supplierName: sup?.name || selectedSupplier
      });
    }, 50);
    setStage('sent');
  };

  // Line editing helpers
  const updateLine = (id, patch) => setLines(ls => ls.map(l => l.id === id ? { ...l, ...patch } : l));
  const removeLine = (id) => setLines(ls => ls.filter(l => l.id !== id));
  const addLine = () => setLines(ls => [...ls, { id: `line_${Date.now()}`, name: '', qty: 1, uom: 'EACH', estPrice: null, note: '' }]);

  if (stage === 'sent') {
    return (
      <div style={{ flex: 1, display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center', background: '#ECEFF5', gap: '12px', padding: '40px' }}>
        <div style={{ width: '56px', height: '56px', borderRadius: '50%', background: 'rgba(14,140,158,0.12)', border: '2px solid #0E8C9E', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center' }}>
          <Send size={22} color="#0E8C9E" />
        </div>
        <div className="pf-display" style={{ fontSize: '18px', fontWeight: 600, color: '#0D1424' }}>Request sent!</div>
        <div style={{ fontSize: '12.5px', color: '#586278', textAlign: 'center', maxWidth: '360px' }}>Your request has been sent to the supplier. You'll be notified when they respond with pricing.</div>
        <div style={{ display: 'flex', gap: '10px', marginTop: '8px' }}>
          <button onClick={onDone} className="pf-btn-primary">View requests</button>
          <button onClick={() => { setStage('chat'); setLines([]); setMessages([{ role: 'assistant', text: 'Hi! Tell me what products you need and how many.' }]); setSelectedSupplier(''); setBuyerNote(''); setInput(''); }} className="pf-btn-ghost">New request</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    );
  }

  return (
    <div style={{ flex: 1, display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', overflow: 'hidden', background: '#ECEFF5' }}>
      {/* Top bar */}
      <div style={{ background: '#fff', borderBottom: '1px solid #CBD3E0', padding: '10px 20px', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '10px' }}>
        <button onClick={onDone} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ fontSize: '11px', display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}>
          <ArrowLeft size={12} /> Requests
        </button>
        <div className="pf-display" style={{ fontSize: '15px', fontWeight: 600, flex: 1 }}>New request</div>
        {/* Stage pills */}
        {['chat', 'review', 'supplier'].map((s, i) => (
          <React.Fragment key={s}>
            <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}>
              <div style={{ width: '20px', height: '20px', borderRadius: '50%', background: stage === s ? '#0F7AD8' : ((['review','supplier'].indexOf(stage) > ['review','supplier'].indexOf(s) || (stage === 'review' && s === 'chat') || (stage === 'supplier' && s !== 'supplier')) ? '#0E8C9E' : '#E8ECF4'), display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center', fontSize: '10px', color: stage === s || (stage !== s && i < ['chat','review','supplier'].indexOf(stage)) ? '#fff' : '#8892A6', fontWeight: 600 }}>
                {i + 1}
              </div>
              <span style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: stage === s ? '#0D1424' : '#8892A6', fontWeight: stage === s ? 600 : 400 }}>
                {s === 'chat' ? 'Describe' : s === 'review' ? 'Review items' : 'Select supplier'}
              </span>
            </div>
            {i < 2 && <span style={{ color: '#CBD3E0', fontSize: '12px' }}>›</span>}
          </React.Fragment>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div style={{ flex: 1, display: 'flex', overflow: 'hidden' }}>
        {/* Left: chat */}
        <div style={{ width: '380px', flexShrink: 0, display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', borderRight: '1px solid #CBD3E0', background: '#fff' }}>
          {/* Messages */}
          <div style={{ flex: 1, overflowY: 'auto', padding: '16px' }} className="pf-scroll">
            {messages.map((m, i) => (
              <div key={i} style={{ marginBottom: '12px', display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', alignItems: m.role === 'user' ? 'flex-end' : 'flex-start' }}>
                <div style={{ maxWidth: '88%', padding: '9px 13px', borderRadius: m.role === 'user' ? '12px 12px 2px 12px' : '12px 12px 12px 2px', background: m.role === 'user' ? '#0F7AD8' : '#F4F7FC', color: m.role === 'user' ? '#fff' : '#0D1424', fontSize: '12px', lineHeight: 1.5, border: m.role === 'user' ? 'none' : '1px solid #E8ECF4' }}>
                  {m.text}
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
            {parsing && (
              <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px', padding: '8px 12px', background: '#F4F7FC', borderRadius: '8px', fontSize: '11.5px', color: '#586278', border: '1px solid #E8ECF4' }}>
                <Loader size={12} style={{ animation: 'spin 1s linear infinite' }} color="#0F7AD8" /> Parsing your request…
              </div>
            )}
            <div ref={bottomRef} />
          </div>
          {/* Input */}
          <div style={{ padding: '12px', borderTop: '1px solid #E8ECF4' }}>
            <div style={{ display: 'flex', gap: '8px', alignItems: 'flex-end' }}>
              <textarea
                value={input}
                onChange={e => setInput(e.target.value)}
                onKeyDown={e => { if (e.key === 'Enter' && !e.shiftKey) { e.preventDefault(); handleSend(); } }}
                placeholder={stage === 'chat' ? 'Describe what you need and quantities…' : 'Add a message or note…'}
                className="pf-input"
                style={{ flex: 1, resize: 'none', fontSize: '12px', height: '60px', lineHeight: 1.5 }}
                disabled={parsing}
              />
              <button onClick={handleSend} disabled={!input.trim() || parsing} className="pf-btn-primary" style={{ height: '38px', width: '38px', padding: 0, display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center', flexShrink: 0 }}>
                <Send size={14} />
              </button>
            </div>
            {stage === 'chat' && <div style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#8892A6', marginTop: '5px' }}>Press Enter to send · Shift+Enter for new line</div>}
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Right: items table + supplier picker */}
        <div style={{ flex: 1, display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', overflow: 'hidden' }}>
          {stage === 'chat' && lines.length === 0 && (
            <div style={{ flex: 1, display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center', color: '#CBD3E0', gap: '12px' }}>
              <ListChecks size={40} strokeWidth={1.2} />
              <div style={{ fontSize: '13px', color: '#8892A6' }}>Your items will appear here</div>
            </div>
          )}

          {(stage === 'review' || stage === 'supplier' || lines.length > 0) && (
            <div style={{ flex: 1, overflowY: 'auto', padding: '20px' }} className="pf-scroll">
              {/* Items table */}
              <div style={{ marginBottom: '20px' }}>
                <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px', marginBottom: '10px' }}>
                  <div className="pf-display" style={{ fontSize: '14px', fontWeight: 600 }}>Requested items</div>
                  <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#8892A6' }}>{lines.length} items</span>
                  <button onClick={addLine} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ marginLeft: 'auto', fontSize: '10.5px', display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '4px' }}>
                    <Plus size={11} /> Add item
                  </button>
                </div>
                <div style={{ background: '#fff', border: '1px solid #CBD3E0', borderRadius: '8px', overflow: 'hidden' }}>
                  {/* Header */}
                  <div style={{ display: 'grid', gridTemplateColumns: '1fr 60px 70px 90px 1fr 30px', gap: '8px', padding: '7px 12px', background: '#ECEFF5', borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4' }} className="pf-label">
                    <span>Product</span><span>Qty</span><span>UoM</span><span>Est. price</span><span>Note</span><span/>
                  </div>
                  {lines.map((l, i) => (
                    <div key={l.id} style={{ display: 'grid', gridTemplateColumns: '1fr 60px 70px 90px 1fr 30px', gap: '8px', padding: '7px 12px', borderBottom: i < lines.length - 1 ? '1px solid #E8ECF4' : 'none', alignItems: 'center', background: i % 2 === 0 ? '#fff' : '#FAFBFD' }}>
                      <input value={l.name} onChange={e => updateLine(l.id, { name: e.target.value })} className="pf-input" style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', height: '28px', padding: '3px 7px' }} placeholder="Product name" />
                      <input type="number" value={l.qty} onChange={e => updateLine(l.id, { qty: Math.max(1, parseInt(e.target.value) || 1) })} className="pf-input pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', height: '28px', padding: '3px 7px', textAlign: 'right' }} min="1" />
                      <select value={l.uom} onChange={e => updateLine(l.id, { uom: e.target.value })} className="pf-input" style={{ fontSize: '11px', height: '28px', padding: '3px 5px' }}>
                        {['EACH','BOX','KG','LTR','CASE','PACK','ROLL','PAIR','SET','BOTTLE'].map(u => <option key={u}>{u}</option>)}
                      </select>
                      <div style={{ position: 'relative' }}>
                        <span style={{ position: 'absolute', left: '8px', top: '50%', transform: 'translateY(-50%)', fontSize: '11px', color: '#8892A6' }}>£</span>
                        <input type="number" value={l.estPrice || ''} onChange={e => updateLine(l.id, { estPrice: e.target.value ? parseFloat(e.target.value) : null })} className="pf-input pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', height: '28px', paddingLeft: '18px', paddingRight: '5px' }} placeholder="—" min="0" step="0.01" />
                      </div>
                      <input value={l.note} onChange={e => updateLine(l.id, { note: e.target.value })} className="pf-input" style={{ fontSize: '11px', height: '28px', padding: '3px 7px' }} placeholder="Optional note" />
                      <button onClick={() => removeLine(l.id)} style={{ background: 'none', border: 'none', cursor: 'pointer', color: '#B33A1F', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center' }}>
                        <X size={13} />
                      </button>
                    </div>
                  ))}
                </div>
              </div>

              {/* Supplier selection */}
              {(stage === 'review' || stage === 'supplier') && lines.length > 0 && (
                <div>
                  <div className="pf-display" style={{ fontSize: '14px', fontWeight: 600, marginBottom: '10px' }}>Select supplier</div>

                  {/* Type filter chips */}
                  {(() => {
                    const types = ['All', ...Array.from(new Set(suppliers.map(s => (s.category || '').split('/')[0].trim()).filter(Boolean))).sort()];
                    return (
                      <div style={{ display: 'flex', gap: '6px', flexWrap: 'wrap', marginBottom: '12px' }}>
                        {types.map(t => (
                          <button key={t} type="button"
                            onClick={() => setSupplierTypeFilter(t)}
                            style={{ padding: '4px 12px', borderRadius: '20px', fontSize: '11px', fontWeight: supplierTypeFilter === t ? 600 : 400, cursor: 'pointer', border: `1px solid ${supplierTypeFilter === t ? '#0F7AD8' : '#CBD3E0'}`, background: supplierTypeFilter === t ? '#0F7AD8' : '#fff', color: supplierTypeFilter === t ? '#fff' : '#586278', transition: 'all 0.12s' }}>
                            {t}
                          </button>
                        ))}
                      </div>
                    );
                  })()}

                  <div style={{ display: 'grid', gridTemplateColumns: 'repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr))', gap: '10px', marginBottom: '14px' }}>
                    {suppliers
                      .filter(s => supplierTypeFilter === 'All' || (s.category || '').split('/')[0].trim() === supplierTypeFilter)
                      .map(s => (
                      <div key={s.id} onClick={() => { setSelectedSupplier(s.id); setStage('supplier'); }}
                        style={{ padding: '12px 14px', border: `2px solid ${selectedSupplier === s.id ? '#0F7AD8' : '#CBD3E0'}`, borderRadius: '8px', cursor: 'pointer', background: selectedSupplier === s.id ? 'rgba(15,122,216,0.05)' : '#fff', transition: 'all 0.15s' }}>
                        <div style={{ fontSize: '12.5px', fontWeight: 600, color: selectedSupplier === s.id ? '#0F7AD8' : '#0D1424' }}>{s.name}</div>
                        <div style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#8892A6', marginTop: '2px' }}>{s.category || 'General supplier'}</div>
                        {selectedSupplier === s.id && <div style={{ marginTop: '6px', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '4px', fontSize: '10px', color: '#0F7AD8' }}><Check size={10} /> Selected</div>}
                      </div>
                    ))}
                  </div>

                  {selectedSupplier && (
                    <div style={{ marginBottom: '14px' }}>
                      <div className="pf-label" style={{ marginBottom: '5px' }}>Message to supplier (optional)</div>
                      <textarea value={buyerNote} onChange={e => setBuyerNote(e.target.value)} className="pf-input" style={{ width: '100%', height: '70px', resize: 'vertical', fontSize: '12px', lineHeight: 1.5 }} placeholder="Any additional context, delivery requirements, urgency…" />
                    </div>
                  )}
                </div>
              )}
            </div>
          )}

          {/* Bottom action bar */}
          {lines.length > 0 && (
            <div style={{ padding: '12px 20px', borderTop: '1px solid #CBD3E0', background: '#fff', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px' }}>
              <span style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#586278', flex: 1 }}>
                {lines.length} item{lines.length !== 1 ? 's' : ''}
                {selectedSupplier ? ` · ${suppliers.find(s => s.id === selectedSupplier)?.name}` : ' · No supplier selected'}
              </span>
              <button onClick={onDone} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ fontSize: '11.5px' }}>Cancel</button>
              <button
                onClick={handleSubmit}
                disabled={!selectedSupplier || lines.length === 0 || lines.some(l => !l.name.trim())}
                className="pf-btn-primary"
                style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}
              >
                <Send size={12} /> Send request
              </button>
            </div>
          )}
        </div>
      </div>

      <style>{`@keyframes spin { from { transform: rotate(0deg); } to { transform: rotate(360deg); } }`}</style>
    </div>
  );
}

/* =====================================================
   SIDEBAR
   ===================================================== */
const NAV = [
  { group: 'Overview', items: [
    { id: 'home',         label: 'Home',      icon: Home,      active: false },
    { id: 'dashboard',    label: 'Dashboard', icon: BarChart3, active: false },
  ]},
  { group: 'Procurement', items: [
    { id: 'tracker',       label: 'Orders',           icon: GitCompare,  active: true },
    { id: 'flow-requests', label: 'Requests',         icon: Send,        active: true },
    { id: 'invoicing',     label: 'Invoicing',        icon: Receipt,     active: true },
    { id: 'requisitions',  label: 'Requisitions',     icon: ClipboardList, active: true },
    { id: 'po',            label: 'Purchase orders',  icon: ScrollText,  active: true },
    { id: 'po-approvals',  label: 'PO approvals',     icon: Check,       active: true },
    { id: 'grn',           label: 'Goods receipts',   icon: Truck,       active: true },
  ]},
  { group: 'Masters', items: [
    { id: 'sup-dir',   label: 'Suppliers',      icon: Users,    active: true },
    { id: 'products',  label: 'Products',       icon: Boxes,    active: false },
    { id: 'catalogue', label: 'Item catalogue', icon: Database, active: false },
    { id: 'prices',    label: 'Price history',  icon: History,  active: false }
  ]},
  { group: 'Admin', items: [
    { id: 'business', label: 'Business structure', icon: Building2, active: false },
    { id: 'config',   label: 'Configuration',      icon: Sliders,   active: false },
    { id: 'users',    label: 'Users',               icon: User,      active: false }
  ]}
];

/* Supplier portal navigation — much narrower than the customer-side nav.
   Suppliers only see the documents that involve them: POs they need to
   confirm and invoices they've issued. They don't see internal coding,
   approvals, or other suppliers' data. */
const SUPPLIER_NAV = [
  { group: 'Supplier Portal', items: [
    { id: 'sup-home',          label: 'Dashboard',                icon: Home,           active: true },
    { id: 'sup-pos',           label: 'POs to confirm',           icon: ScrollText,     active: true },
    { id: 'sup-invoices',      label: 'My invoices',              icon: Receipt,        active: true },
    { id: 'sup-queries',       label: 'Open queries',             icon: FileText,       active: true },
    { id: 'tracker',           label: 'Order tracker',            icon: GitBranch,      active: true },
  ]},
];

function Sidebar({ activeNav, setActiveNav, currentUser, switchUser, resetDb }) {
  const navSource = currentUser?.role === 'supplier' ? SUPPLIER_NAV : NAV;
  const [collapsed, setCollapsed] = useState(true);
  const [hovered, setHovered] = useState(false);
  const [resetArmed, setResetArmed] = useState(false);
  const expanded = !collapsed || hovered;

  return (
    <aside
      onMouseEnter={() => setHovered(true)}
      onMouseLeave={() => setHovered(false)}
      style={{
        width: expanded ? '224px' : '60px',
        flexShrink: 0,
        background: '#111318',
        borderRight: '1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06)',
        display: 'flex',
        flexDirection: 'column',
        overflow: 'hidden',
        transition: 'width 0.35s cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1)',
        position: 'relative',
        zIndex: 10,
      }}
    >
      {/* Logo */}
      <div style={{ padding: expanded ? '18px 16px 16px' : '18px 0 16px', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '12px', justifyContent: expanded ? 'flex-start' : 'center', flexShrink: 0 }}>
        <div style={{ width: '32px', height: '32px', borderRadius: '9px', background: 'linear-gradient(135deg,#0F7AD8,#2A8FD8)', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center', flexShrink: 0, boxShadow: '0 2px 8px rgba(15,122,216,0.40)' }}>
          <Sparkles size={14} color="#fff" />
        </div>
        {expanded && (
          <div style={{ overflow: 'hidden', opacity: expanded ? 1 : 0, transition: 'opacity 0.25s ease 0.1s' }}>
            <div style={{ fontSize: '15px', fontWeight: 700, color: '#fff', letterSpacing: '-0.02em', whiteSpace: 'nowrap', fontFamily: "'Space Grotesk',sans-serif" }}>ProFlow</div>
            <div style={{ fontSize: '8px', color: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.30)', letterSpacing: '0.18em', marginTop: '1px', fontFamily: "'JetBrains Mono',monospace" }}>{currentUser?.role === 'supplier' ? 'SUPPLIER PORTAL' : 'P2P · AGENT v1'}</div>
          </div>
        )}
      </div>

      {/* Nav */}
      <nav style={{ flex: 1, overflowY: 'auto', overflowX: 'hidden', padding: expanded ? '4px 10px' : '4px 10px' }} className="pf-scroll">
        {navSource.map((grp, gi) => (
          <div key={grp.group} style={{ marginBottom: '4px' }}>
            {/* Group label (expanded) or divider (collapsed, between groups) */}
            {expanded ? (
              <div style={{ padding: '10px 6px 4px', fontSize: '9px', fontWeight: 700, letterSpacing: '0.14em', color: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.25)', textTransform: 'uppercase', whiteSpace: 'nowrap' }}>
                {grp.group}
              </div>
            ) : gi > 0 ? (
              <div style={{ height: '1px', background: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.08)', margin: '8px 6px' }} />
            ) : null}

            {grp.items.map(it => {
              const Icon = it.icon;
              const on = activeNav === it.id && it.active;
              const inactive = !it.active;
              return (
                <div
                  key={it.id}
                  onClick={() => it.active && setActiveNav(it.id)}
                  title={!expanded ? it.label : undefined}
                  style={{
                    display: 'flex',
                    alignItems: 'center',
                    gap: '10px',
                    padding: expanded ? '5px 8px' : '5px 0',
                    justifyContent: expanded ? 'flex-start' : 'center',
                    borderRadius: '8px',
                    cursor: it.active ? 'pointer' : 'default',
                    background: on ? 'rgba(15,122,216,0.22)' : 'transparent',
                    transition: 'background 0.13s',
                    marginBottom: '2px',
                    position: 'relative',
                  }}
                  onMouseEnter={e => { if (it.active && !on) e.currentTarget.style.background = 'rgba(255,255,255,0.06)'; }}
                  onMouseLeave={e => { if (!on) e.currentTarget.style.background = 'transparent'; }}
                >
                  {/* Icon box */}
                  <div style={{
                    width: '32px', height: '32px', borderRadius: '8px', flexShrink: 0,
                    display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center',
                    background: on ? 'rgba(15,122,216,0.35)' : 'rgba(255,255,255,0.07)',
                    transition: 'background 0.13s',
                  }}>
                    <Icon size={15} strokeWidth={1.75} color={inactive ? 'rgba(255,255,255,0.45)' : on ? '#fff' : 'rgba(255,255,255,0.75)'} />
                  </div>
                  {expanded && (
                    <>
                      <span style={{ flex: 1, fontSize: '12.5px', fontWeight: on ? 600 : 400, color: inactive ? 'rgba(255,255,255,0.45)' : on ? '#fff' : 'rgba(255,255,255,0.80)', overflow: 'hidden', textOverflow: 'ellipsis', whiteSpace: 'nowrap', opacity: expanded ? 1 : 0, transition: 'opacity 0.25s ease 0.1s' }}>
                        {it.label}
                      </span>
                      {inactive && (
                        <span style={{ fontSize: '7px', letterSpacing: '0.08em', color: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.25)', border: '1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12)', padding: '1px 4px', borderRadius: '3px', flexShrink: 0, fontFamily: "'JetBrains Mono',monospace", opacity: expanded ? 1 : 0, transition: 'opacity 0.25s ease 0.1s' }}>SOON</span>
                      )}
                    </>
                  )}
                </div>
              );
            })}
          </div>
        ))}
      </nav>

      {/* User footer */}
      <div style={{ padding: expanded ? '12px 10px' : '12px 0', borderTop: '1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07)', flexShrink: 0 }}>
        <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '10px', justifyContent: expanded ? 'flex-start' : 'center', padding: expanded ? '0' : '0' }}>
          {/* Avatar */}
          <div style={{
            width: '36px', height: '36px', borderRadius: '50%', flexShrink: 0,
            background: currentUser?.role === 'approver' ? '#0E4A52' : currentUser?.role === 'supplier' ? '#5C3A0A' : '#0A3A5C',
            color: currentUser?.role === 'approver' ? '#4DD9E8' : currentUser?.role === 'supplier' ? '#F59E0B' : '#60AEDE',
            display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center',
            fontSize: '14px', fontWeight: 700, cursor: 'pointer',
            boxShadow: '0 0 0 2px rgba(255,255,255,0.10)',
          }} title={currentUser?.name}>
            {(currentUser?.name || 'F')[0]}
          </div>
          {expanded && (
            <div style={{ flex: 1, minWidth: 0, opacity: expanded ? 1 : 0, transition: 'opacity 0.25s ease 0.1s' }}>
              <div style={{ fontSize: '12px', color: '#fff', fontWeight: 600, overflow: 'hidden', textOverflow: 'ellipsis', whiteSpace: 'nowrap' }}>{currentUser?.name || 'Flo Brunner'}</div>
              <div style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.40)', marginTop: '1px', overflow: 'hidden', textOverflow: 'ellipsis', whiteSpace: 'nowrap' }}>{currentUser?.title || 'Property Director'}</div>
            </div>
          )}
        </div>
        {switchUser && expanded && (
          <button onClick={switchUser} style={{ marginTop: '8px', width: '100%', fontSize: '10px', padding: '5px 8px', borderRadius: '6px', cursor: 'pointer', border: '1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.10)', background: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.04)', color: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.45)', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center', gap: '5px' }}>
            <RefreshCw size={10} /> Switch to {currentUser?.role === 'requester' ? 'Marcus (Approver)' : currentUser?.role === 'approver' ? 'Sarah (Supplier)' : 'Flo (Requester)'}
          </button>
        )}
        {resetDb && expanded && (
          <button
            onClick={() => { if (!resetArmed) { setResetArmed(true); return; } setResetArmed(false); resetDb(); }}
            onMouseLeave={() => setResetArmed(false)}
            style={{ marginTop: '4px', width: '100%', fontSize: '10px', padding: '4px 8px', borderRadius: '6px', cursor: 'pointer', border: `1px solid ${resetArmed ? 'rgba(179,58,31,0.60)' : 'rgba(255,255,255,0.07)'}`, background: resetArmed ? 'rgba(179,58,31,0.18)' : 'transparent', color: resetArmed ? '#E07060' : 'rgba(255,255,255,0.25)', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center', gap: '5px' }}
          >
            <Trash2 size={9} /> {resetArmed ? 'Confirm reset' : 'Reset demo data'}
          </button>
        )}
      </div>
    </aside>
  );
}

/* =====================================================
   TOP BAR
   ===================================================== */
function TopBar({ user, agentOpen, onToggleAgent, pendingSuggestions }) {
  return (
    <header style={{
      display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'space-between',
      padding: '10px 20px', borderBottom: '1px solid #CBD3E0', background: '#FFFFFF', flexShrink: 0
    }}>
      <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '10px' }} className="pf-mono">
        <span style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#8892A6', letterSpacing: '0.06em' }}>ProFlow</span>
        <ChevronRight size={11} color="#CBD3E0" />
        <span style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#8892A6', letterSpacing: '0.06em' }}>Procurement</span>
        <ChevronRight size={11} color="#CBD3E0" />
        <span style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 600, letterSpacing: '0.02em' }}>New order</span>
      </div>
      <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px' }}>
        {/* P2P Assistant toggle */}
        <button
          onClick={onToggleAgent}
          className={`pf-agent-button${agentOpen ? ' is-open' : ''}${pendingSuggestions > 0 ? ' pf-pulse' : ''}`}
          title={agentOpen ? 'Close P2P Assistant' : 'Open P2P Assistant'}
          aria-label="P2P Assistant"
        >
          <Sparkles size={15} color={agentOpen ? '#0F7AD8' : '#586278'} />
        </button>
        {/* Profile chip */}
        <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px', padding: '5px 11px', background: '#F4F7FC', border: '1px solid #CBD3E0', borderRadius: '20px' }}>
          <div style={{ width: '22px', height: '22px', borderRadius: '50%', background: 'linear-gradient(135deg, #0F7AD8, #2A8FD8)', color: 'white', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center', fontSize: '10px', fontWeight: 600 }}>FB</div>
          <div style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500 }}>{user.name}</div>
          <div style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#586278' }}>· {user.role} · {user.assignedSites.length} sites</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>
  );
}

/* =====================================================
   CATALOGUE PANEL
   ===================================================== */
/* CatalogueGroupCard — one card per master product. If the product has multiple
   supplier-variants, displays a tab strip letting the user pick which supplier
   to add. Cheapest variant is selected by default. The "Add" button uses the
   variant currently selected.

   Single-variant groups render the same card without the tab strip (so the
   visual rhythm is consistent). */
function CatalogueGroupCard({ variants, qtyState, setQ, handleAdd, recentlyJustAdded, routingReady, siteRecord }) {
  // Selected variant — defaults to first (cheapest after the sort upstream)
  const [selectedId, setSelectedId] = useState(variants[0]?.id);
  const selected = variants.find(v => v.id === selectedId) || variants[0];

  /* Use-as picker — multi-use products (red wine, cleaning chemicals, fresh
     produce that lives in both kitchen and bar) carry an allowedCategories
     list on the catalogue record. We expose those alternates here so the user
     can route ONE click of Add to whichever spend category applies for this
     order. Defaults to the product's primary category. */
  const allowedCategories = useMemo(() => selected ? getProductAllowedCategories(selected) : [], [selected]);
  const isMultiUse = allowedCategories.length > 1;
  const [selectedCategory, setSelectedCategory] = useState(allowedCategories[0] || null);
  // Reset category selection when variant changes (different SKUs of the same
  // master COULD have different allowed lists, though usually they don't)
  useEffect(() => {
    setSelectedCategory(allowedCategories[0] || null);
  }, [selected?.id]);

  if (!selected) return null;

  const hasAlts = variants.length > 1;
  const q = qtyState[selected.id] || 1;
  const justAdded = recentlyJustAdded === selected.id;
  // Best price across variants — used for the "save £X" callout on alts
  const bestPrice = Math.min(...variants.map(v => v.price || 0));

  // The category override only fires when the user has actively picked an
  // alternate. Picking the primary (default) means no override — the cascade
  // runs against the product's own GL as usual.
  const isOverridden = isMultiUse && selectedCategory && selectedCategory !== allowedCategories[0];
  const categoryOverrideArg = isOverridden ? selectedCategory : null;
  const selectedCatLabel = SPEND_CATEGORIES.find(c => c.code === selectedCategory)?.label;

  return (
    <div className="pf-card-lift" style={{
      border: '1px solid #CBD3E0', borderRadius: '8px', padding: '12px',
      background: '#FFFFFF', display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '8px'
    }}>
      {/* Product image with supplier count chip overlaid top-left */}
      <div style={{ position: 'relative', width: '100%', height: '64px', background: '#E8ECF4', borderRadius: '4px', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center', border: '1px solid #CBD3E0', flexShrink: 0 }}>
        <Package size={24} color="#8892A6" strokeWidth={1.5} />
        {hasAlts && (
          <div className="pf-mono" style={{ position: 'absolute', top: '5px', left: '6px', fontSize: '8.5px', fontWeight: 700, padding: '2px 6px', borderRadius: '4px', background: '#0F7AD8', color: '#fff', letterSpacing: '0.04em', boxShadow: '0 1px 4px rgba(15,122,216,0.35)' }}>
            {variants.length} suppliers
          </div>
        )}
        {isMultiUse && (
          <div className="pf-mono" style={{ position: 'absolute', top: '5px', right: '6px', fontSize: '8px', padding: '1px 5px', borderRadius: '3px', background: 'rgba(106,120,173,0.85)', color: '#fff', textTransform: 'uppercase' }}>multi</div>
        )}
      </div>

      <div style={{ flex: 1, minWidth: 0 }}>
        {/* Product name */}
        <div style={{ fontSize: '12px', fontWeight: 600, color: '#0D1424', lineHeight: 1.3 }}>
          {selected.name}
        </div>

        {/* All supplier names on one wrapping line */}
        <div style={{ marginTop: '3px', display: 'flex', flexWrap: 'wrap', gap: '3px', alignItems: 'center' }}>
          {variants.map((v, i) => (
            <span key={v.id} style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: v.id === selectedId ? '#0F7AD8' : '#586278', fontWeight: v.id === selectedId ? 600 : 400 }}>
              {v.supplier.split(' ')[0]}{i < variants.length - 1 ? <span style={{ color: '#CBD3E0', marginLeft: '3px' }}>·</span> : ''}
            </span>
          ))}
        </div>

        <div className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9px', color: '#8892A6', marginTop: '2px' }}>{selected.sku} · {selected.uom}</div>

        {/* Supplier variants — full-width selectable rows */}
        {hasAlts && (
          <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '4px', marginTop: '6px' }}>
            {variants.map(v => {
              const isSel = v.id === selectedId;
              const isBest = (v.price || 0) === bestPrice;
              return (
                <button key={v.id} type="button" onClick={() => setSelectedId(v.id)}
                  style={{
                    width: '100%', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px',
                    padding: '7px 10px', borderRadius: '6px', cursor: 'pointer', textAlign: 'left',
                    border: `1.5px solid ${isSel ? '#0F7AD8' : '#E8ECF4'}`,
                    background: isSel ? 'rgba(15,122,216,0.06)' : '#FAFBFD',
                    transition: 'all 0.12s',
                  }}
                >
                  <div style={{ width: '8px', height: '8px', borderRadius: '50%', flexShrink: 0, background: isSel ? '#0F7AD8' : '#CBD3E0', border: isSel ? 'none' : '1.5px solid #CBD3E0' }} />
                  <span style={{ flex: 1, fontSize: '11px', color: isSel ? '#0D1424' : '#586278', fontWeight: isSel ? 600 : 400, overflow: 'hidden', textOverflow: 'ellipsis', whiteSpace: 'nowrap' }}>{v.supplier}</span>
                  {isBest && !isSel && <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '8px', color: '#0E8C9E', background: 'rgba(14,140,158,0.10)', border: '1px solid rgba(14,140,158,0.25)', borderRadius: '3px', padding: '1px 4px', flexShrink: 0 }}>BEST</span>}
                  <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '12px', fontWeight: 700, color: isSel ? '#0F7AD8' : '#0D1424', flexShrink: 0 }}>{gbp(v.price)}</span>
                </button>
              );
            })}
          </div>
        )}
      </div>

      {/* Price + qty + Add row */}
      <div style={{ borderTop: '1px solid #E8ECF4', paddingTop: '8px', display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '6px' }}>
        <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'space-between' }}>
          <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '14px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 700 }}>{gbp(selected.price)}</span>
          {hasAlts && selected.price > bestPrice && (
            <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9px', color: '#B45309' }}>+£{(selected.price - bestPrice).toFixed(2)}</span>
          )}
        </div>
        <div style={{ display: 'flex', gap: '4px', alignItems: 'center' }}>
          <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', border: '1px solid #CBD3E0', borderRadius: '4px', overflow: 'hidden', flexShrink: 0 }}>
            <button type="button" onClick={() => setQ(selected.id, q - 1)} style={{ width: '22px', height: '24px', background: '#F4F7FC', border: 'none', cursor: 'pointer', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center' }}>
              <Minus size={10} color="#586278" />
            </button>
            <div className="pf-mono" style={{ minWidth: '22px', textAlign: 'center', fontSize: '11px', color: '#0D1424' }}>{q}</div>
            <button type="button" onClick={() => setQ(selected.id, q + 1)} style={{ width: '22px', height: '24px', background: '#F4F7FC', border: 'none', cursor: 'pointer', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center' }}>
              <Plus size={10} color="#586278" />
            </button>
          </div>
          <button
            type="button"
            onClick={() => handleAdd(selected, categoryOverrideArg)}
            className="pf-btn-primary"
            style={{ flex: 1, padding: '4px 8px', fontSize: '10.5px', background: justAdded ? '#0E8C9E' : '#0F7AD8' }}
          >
            {justAdded
              ? <span style={{ display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '4px' }}><Check size={11} /> Added</span>
              : 'Add to order'
            }
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

function CataloguePanel({
  catalogue, filtered, suppliers, sites, userAssignedSites, recentlyAdded,
  searchTerm, setSearchTerm, activeCategory, setActiveCategory,
  activeSupplier, setActiveSupplier,
  activeDept, setActiveDept, activeCC, setActiveCC,
  onAdd, onAddCustom, onUploadList,
  activeRouting, pendingAdd, onCollapse,
  /* new: cart state passed in from parent */
  cartExpanded, setCartExpanded, totals, hasLines, validation, onSubmit, onSaveDraft, onDiscard,
  /* order detail */
  state, dispatch, addCatalogueItem,
  /* site selection */
  activeSiteId, onSetActiveSite
}) {
  const [qtyState, setQtyState] = useState({});
  const [recentlyJustAdded, setRecentlyJustAdded] = useState(null);
  const [siteSearch, setSiteSearch] = useState('');
  const [siteDropOpen, setSiteDropOpen] = useState(false);
  const siteDropRef = useRef(null);

  // Close dropdown on outside click
  useEffect(() => {
    const handler = (e) => { if (siteDropRef.current && !siteDropRef.current.contains(e.target)) setSiteDropOpen(false); };
    document.addEventListener('mousedown', handler);
    return () => document.removeEventListener('mousedown', handler);
  }, []);

  const permittedSites = (sites || []).filter(s => (userAssignedSites || []).includes(s.siteId));
  const filteredSiteOptions = siteSearch.trim()
    ? permittedSites.filter(s => s.name.toLowerCase().includes(siteSearch.toLowerCase()) || s.siteId.toLowerCase().includes(siteSearch.toLowerCase()))
    : permittedSites;
  const activeSiteRecord = permittedSites.find(s => s.siteId === activeSiteId);

  // Auto-select first permitted site if none set
  useEffect(() => {
    if (!activeSiteId && permittedSites.length > 0) {
      onSetActiveSite(permittedSites[0].siteId);
    }
  }, []);

  const routingReady = Boolean(
    activeRouting && activeRouting.legalEntity && activeRouting.siteId
  );
  const siteRecord = activeRouting?.siteId ? sites.find(s => s.siteId === activeRouting.siteId) : null;

  const codingOverride = useMemo(() => {
    if (activeDept === 'All' && activeCC === 'All') return null;
    const ov = {};
    if (activeDept !== 'All') ov.dept = activeDept;
    if (activeCC !== 'All') {
      ov.costCentre = activeCC;
      const cc = COST_CENTRES.find(c => c.code === activeCC);
      if (cc) ov.dept = cc.dept;
    }
    return ov;
  }, [activeDept, activeCC]);

  const ccChips = useMemo(() => {
    return activeDept === 'All' ? COST_CENTRES : ccsForDept(activeDept);
  }, [activeDept]);

  const cats = useMemo(() => {
    const m = {};
    catalogue.forEach(p => { m[p.category] = (m[p.category] || 0) + 1; });
    return Object.entries(m).map(([k, v]) => ({ name: k, count: v }));
  }, [catalogue]);

  const handleAdd = (p, categoryOverride = null) => {
    const q = qtyState[p.id] || 1;
    onAdd(p.id, q, codingOverride, categoryOverride);
    setRecentlyJustAdded(p.id);
    setTimeout(() => setRecentlyJustAdded(null), 1200);
  };

  const setQ = (id, v) => setQtyState(s => ({ ...s, [id]: Math.max(1, v) }));

  // Build product groups
  const groupList = useMemo(() => {
    const groups = new Map();
    filtered.forEach(p => {
      const key = p.masterProductId || `__solo_${p.id}`;
      if (!groups.has(key)) groups.set(key, []);
      groups.get(key).push(p);
    });
    return Array.from(groups.entries()).map(([key, variants]) => ({
      key,
      variants: [...variants].sort((a, b) => (a.price || 0) - (b.price || 0))
    }));
  }, [filtered]);

  return (
    <div className="pf-cat-layout" style={{ position: 'relative' }}>
      {/* ── TOP SEARCH BAR (spans full width) ── */}
      <div className="pf-cat-search-bar">
        <div style={{ position: 'relative', flex: 1, maxWidth: '520px' }}>
          <Search size={14} style={{ position: 'absolute', left: '10px', top: '50%', transform: 'translateY(-50%)', color: '#8892A6' }} />
          <input
            type="text"
            placeholder="Search catalogue…"
            value={searchTerm}
            onChange={e => setSearchTerm(e.target.value)}
            className="pf-mono pf-input"
            style={{ paddingLeft: '32px', fontSize: '12px', height: '34px' }}
          />
          {searchTerm && (
            <button onClick={() => setSearchTerm('')} style={{ position: 'absolute', right: '8px', top: '50%', transform: 'translateY(-50%)', background: 'none', border: 'none', cursor: 'pointer', color: '#8892A6', padding: 0 }}>
              <X size={12} />
            </button>
          )}
        </div>
        <div className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#8892A6', whiteSpace: 'nowrap' }}>
          {filtered.length} of {catalogue.length} items
        </div>

        {/* Site selector dropdown */}
        <div ref={siteDropRef} style={{ position: 'relative', flexShrink: 0 }}>
          <button
            onClick={() => setSiteDropOpen(o => !o)}
            style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '6px', height: '34px', padding: '0 10px', border: `1.5px solid ${activeSiteId ? '#0F7AD8' : '#CBD3E0'}`, borderRadius: '6px', background: activeSiteId ? 'rgba(15,122,216,0.06)' : '#fff', cursor: 'pointer', fontSize: '12px', fontWeight: 600, color: activeSiteId ? '#0F7AD8' : '#586278', whiteSpace: 'nowrap', maxWidth: '200px' }}
          >
            <MapPin size={12} />
            <span style={{ overflow: 'hidden', textOverflow: 'ellipsis' }}>{activeSiteRecord?.name || 'Select site'}</span>
            <ChevronDown size={11} style={{ flexShrink: 0, transform: siteDropOpen ? 'rotate(180deg)' : 'none', transition: 'transform 0.15s' }} />
          </button>
          {siteDropOpen && (
            <div style={{ position: 'absolute', top: '38px', left: 0, zIndex: 50, background: '#fff', border: '1px solid #CBD3E0', borderRadius: '8px', boxShadow: '0 8px 24px rgba(13,20,36,0.12)', minWidth: '240px', overflow: 'hidden' }}>
              {/* Search */}
              {permittedSites.length > 5 && (
                <div style={{ padding: '8px 10px', borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4' }}>
                  <div style={{ position: 'relative' }}>
                    <Search size={11} style={{ position: 'absolute', left: '8px', top: '50%', transform: 'translateY(-50%)', color: '#8892A6' }} />
                    <input autoFocus type="text" placeholder="Search sites…" value={siteSearch} onChange={e => setSiteSearch(e.target.value)}
                      className="pf-input pf-mono" style={{ paddingLeft: '26px', fontSize: '11px', height: '28px' }} />
                  </div>
                </div>
              )}
              <div style={{ maxHeight: '220px', overflowY: 'auto' }} className="pf-scroll">
                {filteredSiteOptions.map(s => (
                  <div key={s.siteId}
                    onClick={() => { onSetActiveSite(s.siteId); setSiteDropOpen(false); setSiteSearch(''); }}
                    style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px', padding: '8px 12px', cursor: 'pointer', background: s.siteId === activeSiteId ? 'rgba(15,122,216,0.06)' : '#fff', borderLeft: `3px solid ${s.siteId === activeSiteId ? '#0F7AD8' : 'transparent'}` }}
                    onMouseEnter={e => { if (s.siteId !== activeSiteId) e.currentTarget.style.background = '#F4F7FC'; }}
                    onMouseLeave={e => { if (s.siteId !== activeSiteId) e.currentTarget.style.background = '#fff'; }}
                  >
                    <MapPin size={12} color={s.siteId === activeSiteId ? '#0F7AD8' : '#8892A6'} />
                    <div style={{ flex: 1 }}>
                      <div style={{ fontSize: '12px', fontWeight: s.siteId === activeSiteId ? 600 : 400, color: s.siteId === activeSiteId ? '#0F7AD8' : '#0D1424' }}>{s.name}</div>
                      <div className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9px', color: '#8892A6' }}>{s.siteId}</div>
                    </div>
                    {s.siteId === activeSiteId && <Check size={12} color="#0F7AD8" />}
                  </div>
                ))}
                {filteredSiteOptions.length === 0 && <div style={{ padding: '12px', fontSize: '11px', color: '#8892A6', textAlign: 'center' }}>No sites found</div>}
              </div>
            </div>
          )}
        </div>
        {(activeCategory !== 'All' || activeSupplier !== 'All' || activeDept !== 'All' || activeCC !== 'All') && (
          <div style={{ display: 'flex', gap: '4px', flexWrap: 'wrap' }}>
            {activeCategory !== 'All' && (
              <span className="pf-chip pf-chip-accent" onClick={() => setActiveCategory('All')} style={{ cursor: 'pointer' }}>
                {activeCategory} <X size={9} />
              </span>
            )}
            {activeSupplier !== 'All' && (
              <span className="pf-chip pf-chip-accent" onClick={() => setActiveSupplier('All')} style={{ cursor: 'pointer' }}>
                {activeSupplier} <X size={9} />
              </span>
            )}
            {activeDept !== 'All' && (
              <span className="pf-chip pf-chip-warn" onClick={() => { setActiveDept('All'); setActiveCC('All'); }} style={{ cursor: 'pointer' }}>
                {activeDept} <X size={9} />
              </span>
            )}
            {activeCC !== 'All' && (
              <span className="pf-chip pf-chip-warn" onClick={() => setActiveCC('All')} style={{ cursor: 'pointer' }}>
                {activeCC} <X size={9} />
              </span>
            )}
          </div>
        )}
        <div style={{ marginLeft: 'auto', display: 'flex', gap: '6px' }}>
          <button onClick={onUploadList} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px', height: '34px', borderColor: 'rgba(15,122,216,0.40)', color: '#0F7AD8', background: 'rgba(15,122,216,0.04)' }}>
            <Upload size={12} /> Upload list
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* ── LEFT FILTER SIDEBAR ── */}
      <div className="pf-cat-filters pf-scroll">
        {/* Quick reorder */}
        {recentlyAdded.length > 0 && (
          <div style={{ padding: '10px 14px 10px', borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4' }}>
            <div className="pf-label" style={{ marginBottom: '6px' }}>Quick reorder</div>
            {recentlyAdded.slice(0, 5).map((r, i) => (
              <div key={i}
                style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '6px', padding: '5px 6px', marginBottom: '3px', borderRadius: '4px', background: '#F4F7FC', border: '1px solid #E8ECF4', fontSize: '10.5px', cursor: 'pointer' }}
                onClick={() => onAdd(r.productId, r.qty, codingOverride)}
              >
                <RotateCcw size={9} color="#0F7AD8" />
                <span style={{ flex: 1, overflow: 'hidden', textOverflow: 'ellipsis', whiteSpace: 'nowrap', color: '#0D1424' }}>{r.name}</span>
                <span className="pf-mono" style={{ color: '#8892A6', fontSize: '9px' }}>×{r.qty}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        )}

        {/* Spend categories */}
        <div style={{ padding: '10px 14px 8px' }}>
          <div className="pf-label" style={{ marginBottom: '6px' }}>Category</div>
          <FilterRow label="All" count={catalogue.length} active={activeCategory === 'All'} onClick={() => setActiveCategory('All')} />
          {cats.map(c => (
            <FilterRow key={c.name} label={c.name} count={c.count} active={activeCategory === c.name} onClick={() => setActiveCategory(c.name)} />
          ))}
        </div>

        {/* Suppliers */}
        <div style={{ padding: '10px 14px 8px', borderTop: '1px solid #E8ECF4' }}>
          <div className="pf-label" style={{ marginBottom: '6px' }}>Supplier</div>
          <FilterRow label="All" count={catalogue.length} active={activeSupplier === 'All'} onClick={() => setActiveSupplier('All')} />
          {suppliers.map(s => (
            <FilterRow key={s.id} label={s.name} count={catalogue.filter(p => p.supplier === s.name).length} active={activeSupplier === s.name} onClick={() => setActiveSupplier(s.name)} />
          ))}
        </div>

        {/* Department / Cost Centre */}
        <div style={{ padding: '10px 14px 8px', borderTop: '1px solid #E8ECF4' }}>
          <div className="pf-label" style={{ marginBottom: '6px' }}>Department</div>
          <FilterRow label="All" count={catalogue.length} active={activeDept === 'All'} onClick={() => { setActiveDept('All'); setActiveCC('All'); }} />
          {DEPARTMENTS.map(d => (
            <FilterRow key={d.code} label={d.name} count={catalogue.filter(p => p.dept === d.code || p.category === d.code).length || null} active={activeDept === d.code}
              onClick={() => {
                setActiveDept(d.code);
                const cc = COST_CENTRES.find(c => c.code === activeCC);
                if (cc && cc.dept !== d.code) setActiveCC('All');
              }} />
          ))}
          {(activeDept !== 'All' || activeCC !== 'All') && (
            <>
              <div className="pf-label" style={{ marginTop: '10px', marginBottom: '6px' }}>Cost centre</div>
              <FilterRow label="All" count={null} active={activeCC === 'All'} onClick={() => setActiveCC('All')} />
              {ccChips.map(c => (
                <FilterRow key={c.code} label={c.name} count={null} active={activeCC === c.code}
                  onClick={() => { setActiveCC(c.code); if (activeDept === 'All') setActiveDept(c.dept); }}
                  title={`${c.code} · posts to ${c.allowedGLs.join(', ')}`} />
              ))}
            </>
          )}
          {codingOverride && (
            <div style={{ marginTop: '8px', padding: '5px 8px', background: 'rgba(15,122,216,0.08)', border: '1px solid rgba(15,122,216,0.30)', borderRadius: '3px', fontSize: '10px', color: '#0F7AD8', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}>
              <Sparkles size={10} />
              <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9px' }}>Lines coded to {codingOverride.dept}{codingOverride.costCentre ? ` · ${ccNameOf(codingOverride.costCentre)}` : ''}</span>
            </div>
          )}
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* ── CENTRE: PRODUCT GRID ── */}
      <div className="pf-cat-main pf-scroll">
        {groupList.length === 0 ? (
          <div style={{ padding: '48px 16px', textAlign: 'center', color: '#8892A6', fontSize: '12px' }}>No items match your filters.</div>
        ) : (
          <div className="pf-cat-product-grid">
            {groupList.map(g => (
              <CatalogueGroupCard
                key={g.key}
                variants={g.variants}
                qtyState={qtyState}
                setQ={setQ}
                handleAdd={handleAdd}
                recentlyJustAdded={recentlyJustAdded}
                routingReady={routingReady}
                siteRecord={siteRecord}
              />
            ))}
          </div>
        )}
      </div>

      {/* ── RIGHT: CART (collapsed strip) ── */}
      <div className="pf-cat-cart">
        {/* Cart header — always visible, click to expand drawer */}
        <div
          className="pf-cart-collapsed"
          onClick={() => setCartExpanded(e => !e)}
          style={{ padding: '12px 16px', borderBottom: cartExpanded ? '1px solid #CBD3E0' : 'none', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px', background: '#FAFBFD', userSelect: 'none' }}
        >
          <ShoppingCart size={15} color="#0F7AD8" />
          <div style={{ flex: 1 }}>
            <div className="pf-display" style={{ fontSize: '13px', fontWeight: 600, color: '#0D1424' }}>Order</div>
            <div className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9.5px', color: '#8892A6', marginTop: '1px' }}>{totals.lines} line{totals.lines !== 1 ? 's' : ''} · {totals.sites} site{totals.sites !== 1 ? 's' : ''}</div>
          </div>
          <div style={{ textAlign: 'right' }}>
            <div className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '16px', fontWeight: 700, color: '#0D1424' }}>{gbp(totals.gross)}</div>
            <div className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9px', color: '#8892A6' }}>inc. VAT</div>
          </div>
          <ChevronDown size={14} color="#586278" style={{ transform: cartExpanded ? 'rotate(180deg)' : 'rotate(0deg)', transition: 'transform 0.18s', flexShrink: 0 }} />
        </div>

        {/* Collapsed: mini-cart with product lines grouped by supplier */}
        {!cartExpanded && (
          <div style={{ flex: 1, overflowY: 'auto', display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column' }} className="pf-scroll">
            {!hasLines ? (
              <div style={{ padding: '20px 16px', textAlign: 'center' }}>
                <ShoppingCart size={22} color="#E8ECF4" strokeWidth={1.5} style={{ margin: '0 auto 8px' }} />
                <div style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#CBD3E0' }}>Add items to start your order</div>
              </div>
            ) : (
              <div style={{ padding: '8px 12px', display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '10px' }}>
                {state.order.sites.map(sg => {
                  const site = state.sites?.find(s => s.siteId === sg.siteId);
                  const siteName = site?.name || sg.siteId;
                  const lines = sg.lines || [];
                  if (lines.length === 0) return null;
                  const siteTotal = lines.reduce((sum, l) => sum + (l.lineGross ?? (l.unitPrice ?? 0) * l.qty * 1.2), 0);
                  return (
                    <div key={sg.siteId}
                      onDragOver={e => { e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.style.background = 'rgba(15,122,216,0.05)'; e.currentTarget.style.outline = '2px dashed #0F7AD8'; e.currentTarget.style.borderRadius = '6px'; }}
                      onDragLeave={e => { e.currentTarget.style.background = ''; e.currentTarget.style.outline = ''; }}
                      onDrop={e => {
                        e.preventDefault();
                        e.currentTarget.style.background = '';
                        e.currentTarget.style.outline = '';
                        try {
                          const { lineId, fromSiteId } = JSON.parse(e.dataTransfer.getData('text/plain'));
                          if (fromSiteId !== sg.siteId) {
                            dispatch({ type: 'MOVE_LINE_TO_SITE', lineId, fromSiteId, toSiteId: sg.siteId });
                          }
                        } catch {}
                      }}
                    >
                      {/* Site header */}
                      <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px', marginBottom: '5px' }}>
                        <MapPin size={10} color="#0F7AD8" />
                        <span style={{ fontSize: '10px', fontWeight: 700, color: '#0F7AD8', overflow: 'hidden', textOverflow: 'ellipsis', whiteSpace: 'nowrap', flex: 1 }}>{siteName}</span>
                        <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9px', color: '#8892A6', flexShrink: 0 }}>{lines.length} line{lines.length !== 1 ? 's' : ''}</span>
                      </div>
                      {/* Draggable lines */}
                      <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '3px' }}>
                        {lines.map((l, i) => (
                          <div key={i}
                            draggable
                            onDragStart={e => { e.dataTransfer.setData('text/plain', JSON.stringify({ lineId: l.lineId || l.id || i, fromSiteId: sg.siteId })); e.currentTarget.style.opacity = '0.5'; }}
                            onDragEnd={e => { e.currentTarget.style.opacity = '1'; }}
                            style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'baseline', gap: '6px', padding: '4px 8px', background: '#F4F7FC', borderRadius: '5px', border: '1px solid #E8ECF4', cursor: 'grab' }}
                            title="Drag to move to another site"
                          >
                            <MoreHorizontal size={9} color="#CBD3E0" style={{ flexShrink: 0, alignSelf: 'center' }} />
                            <span style={{ flex: 1, fontSize: '11px', color: '#0D1424', overflow: 'hidden', textOverflow: 'ellipsis', whiteSpace: 'nowrap', fontWeight: 500 }}>{l.name || l.productName}</span>
                            <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9.5px', color: '#8892A6', flexShrink: 0 }}>×{l.qty}</span>
                            <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 600, flexShrink: 0 }}>{l.lineGross != null ? gbp(l.lineGross) : l.unitPrice != null ? gbp(l.unitPrice * l.qty * 1.2) : ''}</span>
                          </div>
                        ))}
                      </div>
                      {/* Site subtotal */}
                      <div style={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'flex-end', marginTop: '4px', paddingRight: '2px' }}>
                        <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#586278' }}>{gbp(siteTotal)}</span>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  );
                })}
                {/* Divider + totals */}
                <div style={{ borderTop: '1px solid #E8ECF4', paddingTop: '8px', display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '3px' }}>
                  <SumRow label="Net" value={gbp(totals.net)} mono />
                  <SumRow label="VAT" value={gbp(totals.tax)} mono />
                  {totals.rfq > 0 && <SumRow label="RFQs pending" value={totals.rfq} accent />}
                  {validation.length > 0 && (
                    <div style={{ marginTop: '4px', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px', fontSize: '10px', color: '#B45309' }}>
                      <AlertCircle size={10} />
                      <span>{validation.length} line{validation.length !== 1 ? 's' : ''} need coding</span>
                    </div>
                  )}
                </div>
              </div>
            )}
          </div>
        )}
      </div>

      {/* ── ORDER DETAIL DRAWER — slides over the catalogue when cart is open ── */}
      {cartExpanded && (
        <div className="pf-fade-in" style={{
          position: 'absolute', top: 0, right: 0, bottom: 56, /* above action bar */
          width: '68%',
          background: '#FFFFFF',
          borderLeft: '1px solid #CBD3E0',
          display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column',
          zIndex: 10,
          boxShadow: '-6px 0 24px rgba(13,20,36,0.10)'
        }}>
          {/* Drawer header */}
          <div style={{ padding: '12px 18px', borderBottom: '1px solid #CBD3E0', background: 'linear-gradient(180deg,#F4F7FC,#fff)', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '12px' }}>
            <ShoppingCart size={15} color="#0F7AD8" />
            <div style={{ flex: 1 }}>
              <span className="pf-display" style={{ fontSize: '15px', fontWeight: 600, color: '#0D1424' }}>Order lines</span>
              <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#586278', marginLeft: '10px' }}>{state.order.id} · DRAFT</span>
            </div>
            {/* Summary inline */}
            <div style={{ display: 'flex', gap: '16px', alignItems: 'baseline' }}>
              <span style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#586278' }}>{totals.lines} lines · {totals.sites} sites · {totals.suppliers} suppliers</span>
              <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '15px', fontWeight: 700, color: '#0D1424' }}>{gbp(totals.gross)}</span>
            </div>
            <button onClick={() => setCartExpanded(false)} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ width: '28px', height: '28px', padding: 0, display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center' }} title="Close order detail">
              <X size={13} />
            </button>
          </div>

          {/* Order header fields */}
          <div style={{ padding: '10px 18px', borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4', display: 'grid', gridTemplateColumns: '2fr 1fr 1fr', gap: '10px', background: '#ECEFF5' }}>
            <CartField label="Description">
              <input type="text" placeholder="e.g. Week 21 produce + linen replenishment"
                value={state.order.description}
                onChange={e => dispatch({ type: 'SET_ORDER_FIELD', field: 'description', value: e.target.value })}
                className="pf-input" style={{ fontSize: '11.5px' }} />
            </CartField>
            <CartField label="Requester">
              <div className="pf-input" style={{ background: '#F4F7FC', cursor: 'default', fontSize: '11.5px' }}>{state.order.requester}</div>
            </CartField>
            <CartField label="Required by">
              <input type="date"
                value={state.order.requiredBy}
                onChange={e => dispatch({ type: 'SET_ORDER_FIELD', field: 'requiredBy', value: e.target.value })}
                className="pf-input pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '11.5px' }} />
            </CartField>
          </div>

          {/* Validation strip */}
          {validation.length > 0 && (
            <div style={{ padding: '7px 18px', background: 'rgba(217,119,6,0.06)', borderBottom: '1px solid rgba(217,119,6,0.20)', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px' }}>
              <AlertCircle size={13} color="#B45309" />
              <span style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', color: '#B45309', fontWeight: 500 }}>{validation.length} {validation.length === 1 ? 'line' : 'lines'} missing required coding</span>
            </div>
          )}

          {/* Line table — SiteGroup with drag-and-drop drop zones */}
          <div style={{ flex: 1, overflowY: 'auto', padding: '12px 18px' }} className="pf-scroll">
            {state.order.sites.length === 0 ? (
              <div style={{ border: '1.5px dashed #CBD3E0', borderRadius: '8px', padding: '40px 24px', textAlign: 'center', background: '#ECEFF5' }}>
                <Package size={28} color="#CBD3E0" strokeWidth={1.5} style={{ margin: '0 auto 10px' }} />
                <div style={{ fontSize: '13px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500 }}>No lines yet</div>
                <div style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', color: '#586278', marginTop: '4px' }}>Add items from the catalogue to start building your order.</div>
              </div>
            ) : (() => {
              const cols = 'minmax(160px,2fr) 60px 50px minmax(70px,1fr) 50px minmax(70px,1fr) minmax(70px,1fr) minmax(110px,1.4fr) minmax(130px,1.2fr) minmax(120px,1fr) 70px 30px';
              const tableMinWidth = 1100;
              return (
                <div style={{ marginBottom: '14px' }}>
                  {state.order.sites.map(siteEntry => {
                    const site = state.sites.find(s => s.siteId === siteEntry.siteId);
                    return (
                      <div key={siteEntry.siteId}
                        onDragOver={e => { e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.querySelector('.pf-drop-zone').style.display = 'flex'; }}
                        onDragLeave={e => { if (!e.currentTarget.contains(e.relatedTarget)) e.currentTarget.querySelector('.pf-drop-zone').style.display = 'none'; }}
                        onDrop={e => {
                          e.preventDefault();
                          e.currentTarget.querySelector('.pf-drop-zone').style.display = 'none';
                          try {
                            const { lineId, fromSiteId } = JSON.parse(e.dataTransfer.getData('text/plain'));
                            if (fromSiteId !== siteEntry.siteId) {
                              dispatch({ type: 'MOVE_LINE_TO_SITE', lineId, fromSiteId, toSiteId: siteEntry.siteId });
                            }
                          } catch {}
                        }}
                        style={{ marginBottom: '10px', position: 'relative' }}
                      >
                        {/* Drop indicator — hidden until dragging over */}
                        <div className="pf-drop-zone" style={{ display: 'none', position: 'absolute', inset: 0, zIndex: 5, border: '2px dashed #0F7AD8', borderRadius: '8px', background: 'rgba(15,122,216,0.06)', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center', pointerEvents: 'none' }}>
                          <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px', padding: '8px 16px', background: 'rgba(15,122,216,0.90)', borderRadius: '6px', color: '#fff', fontSize: '12px', fontWeight: 600 }}>
                            <MapPin size={13} /> Move to {site?.name || siteEntry.siteId}
                          </div>
                        </div>
                        <SiteGroup
                          site={site}
                          siteEntry={siteEntry}
                          dispatch={dispatch}
                          showCodingCols={false}
                          showClusters={false}
                          catalogue={state.catalogue}
                          addCatalogueItem={addCatalogueItem}
                          onAddCustomLine={() => { onAddCustom?.(); }}
                          onUploadList={() => { onUploadList?.(); }}
                          allSites={state.sites}
                          userAssignedSites={state.user.assignedSites}
                          cols={cols}
                          draggable
                          onLineDragStart={(lineId) => { window.__dragLineId = lineId; window.__dragFromSiteId = siteEntry.siteId; }}
                        />
                      </div>
                    );
                  })}
                </div>
              );
            })()}

            {/* RFQ notice */}
            {totals.rfq > 0 && (
              <div style={{ padding: '8px 12px', background: 'rgba(106,120,173,0.10)', border: '1px solid rgba(106,120,173,0.30)', borderRadius: '4px', fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#5a6498', lineHeight: 1.4 }}>
                <span style={{ fontWeight: 600 }}>{totals.rfq} {totals.rfq === 1 ? 'line' : 'lines'} excluded from totals</span> — pricing populates once RFQ is awarded.
              </div>
            )}
          </div>

          {/* Drawer footer — totals */}
          <div style={{ padding: '10px 18px', borderTop: '1px solid #CBD3E0', background: '#FAFBFD', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '20px', justifyContent: 'flex-end' }}>
            <SumRow label="Net" value={gbp(totals.net)} mono />
            <SumRow label="VAT" value={gbp(totals.tax)} mono />
            <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'baseline', gap: '8px', paddingLeft: '16px', borderLeft: '1px solid #E8ECF4' }}>
              <span style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#586278' }}>Total (gross)</span>
              <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '18px', fontWeight: 700, color: '#0D1424' }}>{gbp(totals.gross)}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      )}

      {/* ── PINNED ACTION BAR ── */}
      <div className="pf-action-bar">
        <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#8892A6', marginRight: 'auto' }}>
          {hasLines ? `${totals.lines} line${totals.lines !== 1 ? 's' : ''} · ${gbp(totals.gross)} total` : 'No items added yet'}
        </span>
        <button
          onClick={onDiscard}
          className="pf-btn-ghost pf-btn-danger"
          style={{ fontSize: '11.5px' }}
        >
          Discard
        </button>
        <button
          onClick={onSaveDraft}
          className="pf-btn-ghost"
          style={{ fontSize: '11.5px' }}
        >
          Save draft
        </button>
        <button
          onClick={onSubmit}
          disabled={!hasLines || validation.length > 0}
          className="pf-btn-primary"
          style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', minWidth: '90px' }}
          title={!hasLines ? 'Add lines first' : validation.length > 0 ? 'Resolve coding issues before submit' : 'Submit order'}
        >
          Submit order
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

function CartField({ label, children }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <div className="pf-label" style={{ marginBottom: '4px' }}>{label}</div>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}

function FilterRow({ label, count, active, onClick, title }) {
  return (
    <div onClick={onClick} title={title} style={{
      display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'space-between', alignItems: 'center',
      padding: '5px 8px', marginLeft: '-8px', marginRight: '-8px',
      borderLeft: `2px solid ${active ? '#0F7AD8' : 'transparent'}`,
      background: active ? 'rgba(15,122,216,0.06)' : 'transparent',
      cursor: 'pointer', borderRadius: '0 4px 4px 0',
      transition: 'background 0.1s'
    }}
    onMouseEnter={e => { if (!active) e.currentTarget.style.background = '#F4F7FC'; }}
    onMouseLeave={e => { if (!active) e.currentTarget.style.background = 'transparent'; }}
    >
      <span style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', color: active ? '#0F7AD8' : '#0D1424', fontWeight: active ? 600 : 400 }}>{label}</span>
      {count != null && <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9.5px', color: '#8892A6' }}>{count}</span>}
    </div>
  );
}

/* PillChip — compact inline pill used for Department / Cost Centre filters in
   the catalogue panel. Same visual language as the routing history chips so
   the user reads them as a single "current filter context" gesture. */
function PillChip({ label, active, onClick, title }) {
  return (
    <button
      onClick={onClick}
      title={title}
      className="pf-mono"
      style={{
        fontSize: '10px', padding: '3px 9px', borderRadius: '12px',
        border: `1px solid ${active ? '#0F7AD8' : '#CBD3E0'}`,
        background: active ? 'rgba(15,122,216,0.12)' : '#FFFFFF',
        color: active ? '#0F7AD8' : '#0D1424',
        fontWeight: active ? 600 : 400,
        cursor: 'pointer',
        whiteSpace: 'nowrap'
      }}
    >{label}</button>
  );
}

/* =====================================================
   ORDER CANVAS
   ===================================================== */
/* ====== ROUTING STRIP — controls where the next manual add lands ======
   Cascade Entity → Site. Outlet defaults silently to the site's default outlet
   (users can edit per-line if needed). Click "Add" on a product in the left
   panel without routing set → pendingAdd queues, focus jumps to Entity, then
   to Site, and the product fires the moment Site resolves. */
function RoutingStrip({ state, dispatch, catalogue }) {
  const routing = state.order.routing || { legalEntity: '', siteId: '', outletId: '' };
  const history = state.order.routingHistory || [];
  const pendingAdd = state.order.pendingAdd;
  const entityRef = useRef(null);
  const siteRef = useRef(null);

  const permittedSites = useMemo(
    () => state.sites.filter(s => state.user.assignedSites.includes(s.siteId)),
    [state.sites, state.user.assignedSites]
  );
  const permittedLENames = useMemo(
    () => Array.from(new Set(permittedSites.map(s => s.legalEntity))),
    [permittedSites]
  );
  const permittedLEs = useMemo(
    () => LEGAL_ENTITIES.filter(le => permittedLENames.includes(le.name)),
    [permittedLENames]
  );
  const sitesForLE = useMemo(
    () => permittedSites.filter(s => s.legalEntity === routing.legalEntity),
    [permittedSites, routing.legalEntity]
  );
  const siteRecord = state.sites.find(s => s.siteId === routing.siteId) || null;
  const outletDefault = siteRecord?.defaults?.outlet || siteRecord?.outlets?.[0]?.outletId || '';
  const outletDefaultRecord = siteRecord?.outlets?.find(o => o.outletId === outletDefault) || null;

  // Auto-resolve singletons.
  useEffect(() => {
    if (!routing.legalEntity && permittedLEs.length === 1) {
      dispatch({ type: 'SET_ROUTING', patch: { legalEntity: permittedLEs[0].name } });
    }
  }, [routing.legalEntity, permittedLEs, dispatch]);
  useEffect(() => {
    if (routing.legalEntity && !routing.siteId && sitesForLE.length === 1) {
      dispatch({ type: 'SET_ROUTING', patch: { siteId: sitesForLE[0].siteId } });
    }
  }, [routing.legalEntity, routing.siteId, sitesForLE, dispatch]);
  // Outlet silently resolves to the site default the moment Site is picked.
  useEffect(() => {
    if (routing.siteId && !routing.outletId && outletDefault) {
      dispatch({ type: 'SET_ROUTING', patch: { outletId: outletDefault } });
    }
  }, [routing.siteId, routing.outletId, outletDefault, dispatch]);

  // Focus jumping — guides the user through Entity → Site whenever routing is
  // incomplete AND the user hasn't yet confirmed. Driven by routingUserConfirmed:
  //   undefined (legacy draft)  → never focus (don't disrupt restored work)
  //   true  (user confirmed)    → never focus
  //   false (mid-edit or fresh) → focus the next empty field
  // Also fires on pendingAdd from the catalogue regardless of confirmation state.
  useEffect(() => {
    const incomplete = !routing.legalEntity || !routing.siteId;
    if (!incomplete) return;

    const isEditing = state.order.routingUserConfirmed === false;
    if (!isEditing && !pendingAdd) return;

    const target = !routing.legalEntity ? entityRef.current
                 : !routing.siteId ? siteRef.current
                 : null;
    if (target) {
      target.focus();
      if (pendingAdd) target.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'center' });
    }
  }, [pendingAdd, routing.legalEntity, routing.siteId, state.order.routingUserConfirmed]);

  const ready = Boolean(routing.legalEntity && routing.siteId);
  // Routing needs the user's attention. Fires the pulse / orange border / focus jump.
  // Two distinct cases:
  //   1. Fresh empty order — no lines, no LE/Site yet
  //   2. Mid-edit — user is in the process of picking, hasn't completed both fields
  //      (typically: agent populated, user changed LE which cascade-cleared site)
  // Both share the visual cue: pulse the next empty field.
  const needsInitialRouting = (!routing.legalEntity || !routing.siteId) && (
    state.order.sites.every(s => s.lines.length === 0) ||
    state.order.routingUserConfirmed === false
  );
  // Agent-suggested but human hasn't confirmed — values are populated but the
  // submit gate stays closed until the user actively picks (or clicks Confirm).
  // Legacy compat: only explicit false triggers; undefined (old draft) passes.
  const agentSuggestedRouting = Boolean(routing.legalEntity && routing.siteId) && state.order.routingUserConfirmed === false && state.order.sites.some(s => s.lines.length > 0);
  // userInitiated: true tells the reducer this is a real human pick — flips routingUserConfirmed.
  const setLE = (v) => dispatch({ type: 'SET_ROUTING', patch: { legalEntity: v }, userInitiated: true });
  const setSite = (v) => dispatch({ type: 'SET_ROUTING', patch: { siteId: v }, userInitiated: true });
  const confirmRouting = () => dispatch({ type: 'SET_ROUTING', patch: {}, userInitiated: true });
  // Clearing routing IS a user action — flag flips to false so the gate re-engages.
  const clearRouting = () => dispatch({ type: 'SET_ROUTING', patch: { legalEntity: '', siteId: '', outletId: '' }, userInitiated: true });
  const cancelPending = () => dispatch({ type: 'CLEAR_PENDING_ADD' });
  const jumpTo = (r) => dispatch({ type: 'SET_ROUTING', patch: r });

  // Merge explicit history with implicit targets derived from existing clusters
  // in the order. An agent-populated order with three clusters should expose all
  // three as quick-jump chips even if the user never typed them.
  const allTargets = useMemo(() => {
    const seen = new Set();
    const out = [];
    const push = (r) => {
      if (!r.legalEntity || !r.siteId) return;
      const k = `${r.legalEntity}|${r.siteId}`;
      if (seen.has(k)) return;
      seen.add(k);
      out.push(r);
    };
    history.forEach(push);
    state.order.sites.forEach(se => {
      const s = state.sites.find(x => x.siteId === se.siteId);
      if (s) push({ legalEntity: s.legalEntity, siteId: se.siteId, outletId: s.defaults?.outlet || '' });
    });
    return out;
  }, [history, state.order.sites, state.sites]);

  // Pending product label
  const pendingProduct = pendingAdd ? catalogue.find(p => p.id === pendingAdd.productId) : null;

  // Compact label for history chips
  const chipLabel = (r) => {
    const s = state.sites.find(x => x.siteId === r.siteId);
    return s?.name || r.siteId;
  };
  const isActive = (r) => r.legalEntity === routing.legalEntity && r.siteId === routing.siteId;

  return (
    <div style={{
      background: pendingAdd ? 'linear-gradient(180deg, #FFF6F0 0%, #FFEEE4 100%)'
                : ready ? 'linear-gradient(180deg, #F4F7FC 0%, #ECEFF5 100%)'
                : 'linear-gradient(180deg, #FFFFFF 0%, #F4F7FC 100%)',
      border: `1px solid ${pendingAdd ? '#E89B7A' : '#CBD3E0'}`,
      borderRadius: '8px',
      padding: '10px 14px',
      marginBottom: '14px',
      display: 'flex',
      flexDirection: 'column',
      gap: '8px',
      transition: 'background 0.2s, border-color 0.2s'
    }}>
      {/* Pending-add pill — only when something is queued */}
      {pendingProduct && (
        <div style={{
          display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px',
          padding: '6px 10px', background: '#FFFFFF',
          border: '1px solid #E89B7A', borderRadius: '6px',
          fontSize: '11px'
        }}>
          <Sparkles size={11} color="#D86B1F" />
          <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9.5px', letterSpacing: '0.1em', color: '#D86B1F' }}>QUEUED TO ADD</span>
          <span style={{ color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500 }}>{pendingProduct.name}</span>
          <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#8892A6' }}>× {pendingAdd.qty}</span>
          <span style={{ flex: 1 }} />
          <span style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#586278' }}>
            {!routing.legalEntity ? '→ pick Entity' : !routing.siteId ? '→ pick Site' : '→ adding…'}
          </span>
          <button onClick={cancelPending} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ fontSize: '10px', padding: '2px 6px' }} title="Cancel">
            <X size={10} />
          </button>
        </div>
      )}

      {/* Cascade row — Entity → Site (outlet silent) */}
      <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '10px', flexWrap: 'wrap' }}>
        <div className="pf-mono" style={{
          fontSize: '9.5px', letterSpacing: '0.12em',
          color: agentSuggestedRouting ? '#B45309' : (ready ? '#586278' : '#8892A6'),
          display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px',
          minWidth: '128px'
        }}>
          {agentSuggestedRouting
            ? <><Sparkles size={10} color="#B45309" /> AGENT-SUGGESTED · CONFIRM</>
            : ready
              ? <><Check size={10} color="#10A36E" /> ADDS ROUTE TO</>
              : <>ROUTING TARGET</>}
        </div>

        <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '6px', flexWrap: 'wrap', flex: 1 }}>
          {/* Entity */}
          <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}>
            <span className="pf-label">Entity</span>
            <select
              ref={entityRef}
              value={routing.legalEntity}
              onChange={e => setLE(e.target.value)}
              className={`pf-input ${((pendingAdd || needsInitialRouting) && !routing.legalEntity) || agentSuggestedRouting ? 'pf-pulse' : ''}`}
              style={{
                fontSize: '11px', padding: '4px 7px', minWidth: '160px',
                borderColor: routing.legalEntity ? (agentSuggestedRouting ? '#E89B7A' : '#CBD3E0') : ((pendingAdd || needsInitialRouting) ? '#E89B7A' : '#CBD3E0')
              }}
            >
              <option value="">— pick —</option>
              {permittedLEs.map(le => (
                <option key={le.code} value={le.name}>{le.name}</option>
              ))}
            </select>
          </div>

          <ChevronRight size={12} color="#8892A6" />

          {/* Site */}
          <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}>
            <span className="pf-label">Site</span>
            <select
              ref={siteRef}
              value={routing.siteId}
              onChange={e => setSite(e.target.value)}
              disabled={!routing.legalEntity}
              className={`pf-input ${((pendingAdd || needsInitialRouting) && routing.legalEntity && !routing.siteId) || agentSuggestedRouting ? 'pf-pulse' : ''}`}
              style={{
                fontSize: '11px', padding: '4px 7px', minWidth: '200px',
                borderColor: routing.siteId ? (agentSuggestedRouting ? '#E89B7A' : '#CBD3E0') : ((pendingAdd || needsInitialRouting) && routing.legalEntity ? '#E89B7A' : '#CBD3E0'),
                opacity: routing.legalEntity ? 1 : 0.55
              }}
            >
              <option value="">{routing.legalEntity ? '— pick —' : '— pick entity —'}</option>
              {sitesForLE.map(s => (
                <option key={s.siteId} value={s.siteId}>{s.name}</option>
              ))}
            </select>
          </div>

          {ready && outletDefaultRecord && (
            <span style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#8892A6', marginLeft: '4px' }}>
              · default outlet <span style={{ color: '#0D1424' }}>{outletDefaultRecord.name}</span>
            </span>
          )}
        </div>

        {agentSuggestedRouting && (
          <button
            onClick={confirmRouting}
            className="pf-btn-primary pf-pulse"
            style={{ fontSize: '12px', padding: '7px 14px', display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '6px', fontWeight: 600 }}
            title="Confirm the agent-suggested legal entity and site — required before submit"
          >
            <Check size={13} /> Confirm routing
          </button>
        )}

        {(routing.legalEntity || routing.siteId) && (
          <button onClick={clearRouting} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ fontSize: '10px', padding: '3px 7px' }} title="Clear routing target">
            <X size={10} />
          </button>
        )}
      </div>

      {/* History row — quick-jump chips */}
      {allTargets.length > 0 && (
        <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '6px', flexWrap: 'wrap', borderTop: '1px dashed #CBD3E0', paddingTop: '8px' }}>
          <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9.5px', letterSpacing: '0.1em', color: '#8892A6', minWidth: '128px' }}>TARGETS ON THIS ORDER</span>
          {allTargets.map((r, i) => {
            const active = isActive(r);
            return (
              <button
                key={i}
                onClick={() => jumpTo(r)}
                className="pf-mono"
                style={{
                  fontSize: '10px', padding: '3px 8px', borderRadius: '12px',
                  border: `1px solid ${active ? '#0F7AD8' : '#CBD3E0'}`,
                  background: active ? 'rgba(15,122,216,0.12)' : '#FFFFFF',
                  color: active ? '#0F7AD8' : '#0D1424',
                  cursor: 'pointer',
                  fontWeight: active ? 600 : 400
                }}
                title={active ? 'Currently active' : 'Switch to this routing'}
              >
                {chipLabel(r)}
              </button>
            );
          })}
        </div>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}

function OrderCanvas({ state, dispatch, showCodingCols, setShowCodingCols, showClusters, setShowClusters, onAddSite, onAddLineSearch, addCatalogueItem, onNewOrder, onUploadList, validation }) {
  const [sitePickerOpen, setSitePickerOpen] = useState(false);
  const availableSitesToAdd = state.sites.filter(s =>
    state.user.assignedSites.includes(s.siteId) &&
    !state.order.sites.find(os => os.siteId === s.siteId)
  );
  const lineCount = state.order.sites.reduce((n, s) => n + s.lines.length, 0);
  const hasLines = lineCount > 0;

  // Inline arm-then-confirm: first click arms the button (changes label, glows),
  // second click within 3 seconds fires the action. Replaces window.confirm
  // which can silently no-op inside sandboxed iframes.
  const [deleteArmed, setDeleteArmed] = useState(false);
  const [newOrderArmed, setNewOrderArmed] = useState(false);
  useEffect(() => {
    if (!deleteArmed) return;
    const t = setTimeout(() => setDeleteArmed(false), 3000);
    return () => clearTimeout(t);
  }, [deleteArmed]);
  useEffect(() => {
    if (!newOrderArmed) return;
    const t = setTimeout(() => setNewOrderArmed(false), 3000);
    return () => clearTimeout(t);
  }, [newOrderArmed]);

  const handleDelete = () => {
    if (!hasLines) return;                              // button is also disabled in this state
    if (deleteArmed) { onNewOrder(); setDeleteArmed(false); return; }
    setDeleteArmed(true);
  };
  /* Starter template download — generates a CSV in order_list flavour using
     the first site currently in the order (or first assigned site as fallback).
     Coding columns are hints; the agent infers from outlet defaults if left blank.
     Available from the toolbar at any time so users can grab it before uploading. */
  const downloadOrderTemplate = () => {
    // Minimal template — product + qty are the only required columns.
    // Legal entity, site, and outlet are optional routing hints; if omitted the
    // user assigns the site/LE combo in the bulk upload modal and coding cascades
    // from product + outlet defaults. No Dept / CC / GL in the template.
    const headers = ['Product', 'Quantity', 'Unit', 'Supplier (optional)', 'Legal entity (optional)', 'Site (optional)', 'Outlet (optional)'];
    const rows = [
      ['Vine tomatoes', '20', 'kg', 'Premier Produce Co.', '', '', ''],
      ['Tonic water', '24', 'ea', '', '', '', ''],
      ['Bath towels', '12', 'ea', '', '', '', '']
    ];

    const esc = (v) => { const s = String(v ?? ''); return /[",\n]/.test(s) ? `"${s.replace(/"/g, '""')}"` : s; };
    const csv = [headers, ...rows].map(r => r.map(esc).join(',')).join('\n') + '\n';
    const blob = new Blob([csv], { type: 'text/csv;charset=utf-8;' });
    const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
    const a = document.createElement('a');
    a.href = url; a.download = 'proflow_order_list_template.csv';
    document.body.appendChild(a); a.click(); document.body.removeChild(a);
    URL.revokeObjectURL(url);
  };

  const handleNewOrder = () => {
    if (!hasLines) { onNewOrder(); return; }            // nothing to lose — fire immediately
    if (newOrderArmed) { onNewOrder(); setNewOrderArmed(false); return; }
    setNewOrderArmed(true);
  };

  return (
    <main style={{ background: '#FFFFFF', border: '1px solid #CBD3E0', borderRadius: '8px', display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', overflow: 'hidden', minHeight: 0 }}>
      {/* Header */}
      <div style={{ padding: '14px 18px 12px', borderBottom: '1px solid #CBD3E0', display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'space-between', alignItems: 'center' }}>
        <div>
          <div className="pf-display" style={{ fontSize: '17px', fontWeight: 600, color: '#0D1424' }}>New order</div>
          <div className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#586278', letterSpacing: '0.06em', marginTop: '2px' }}>
            {state.order.id} · DRAFT · {lineCount} lines
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px' }}>
          {state.order.sites.length >= 2 && (() => {
            // Collapse-all / expand-all toggle. Visible only when there are 2+ site
            // panels so it doesn't add chrome when there's nothing to compress.
            const allCollapsed = state.order.sites.every(s => s.collapsed);
            return (
              <button
                className="pf-btn-ghost"
                onClick={() => dispatch({ type: 'SET_ALL_SITES_COLLAPSED', collapsed: !allCollapsed })}
                style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}
                title={allCollapsed ? 'Expand every site panel' : 'Collapse every site panel'}
              >
                {allCollapsed ? <><ChevronDown size={11} /> Expand all</> : <><ChevronRight size={11} /> Collapse all</>}
              </button>
            );
          })()}
          <button
            className="pf-btn-ghost"
            onClick={() => setShowCodingCols(v => !v)}
            style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}
          >
            <ChevronsUpDown size={11} /> {showCodingCols ? 'Hide' : 'Show'} coding cols
          </button>
          <button
            className="pf-btn-ghost"
            onClick={() => setShowClusters(v => !v)}
            style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}
          >
            <ChevronsUpDown size={11} /> {showClusters ? 'Hide' : 'Show'} clusters
          </button>
          <button
            className="pf-btn-ghost"
            onClick={downloadOrderTemplate}
            style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}
            title="Download a starter CSV for bulk upload. The agent maps your own sheet just as well."
          >
            <Download size={11} /> Starter template
          </button>
          <button
            className={`pf-btn-ghost pf-btn-danger${deleteArmed ? ' pf-armed' : ''}`}
            onClick={handleDelete}
            disabled={!hasLines}
            style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px', opacity: hasLines ? 1 : 0.45, cursor: hasLines ? 'pointer' : 'not-allowed' }}
            title={hasLines ? (deleteArmed ? 'Click again to confirm' : 'Discard this draft order') : 'Nothing to delete yet'}
          >
            <Trash2 size={11} /> {deleteArmed ? 'Click to confirm' : 'Delete'}
          </button>
          <button
            className={`pf-btn-primary${newOrderArmed ? ' pf-armed' : ''}`}
            onClick={handleNewOrder}
            style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}
            title={newOrderArmed ? 'Click again to confirm' : 'Start a new draft order'}
          >
            <Plus size={11} /> {newOrderArmed ? 'Click to confirm' : 'New order'}
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Order header fields */}
      <div style={{ padding: '12px 18px', borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4', display: 'grid', gridTemplateColumns: '2fr 1fr 1fr 1fr', gap: '10px', background: '#ECEFF5' }}>
        <Field label="Description">
          <input type="text" placeholder="e.g. Week 21 produce + linen replenishment"
            value={state.order.description}
            onChange={e => dispatch({ type: 'SET_ORDER_FIELD', field: 'description', value: e.target.value })}
            className="pf-input" />
        </Field>
        <Field label="Requester">
          <div className="pf-input" style={{ background: '#F4F7FC', cursor: 'default' }}>{state.order.requester}</div>
        </Field>
        <Field label="Required by">
          <input type="date"
            value={state.order.requiredBy}
            onChange={e => dispatch({ type: 'SET_ORDER_FIELD', field: 'requiredBy', value: e.target.value })}
            className="pf-input pf-mono" />
        </Field>
        <Field label="Default business area">
          <div className="pf-input" style={{ background: '#F4F7FC', cursor: 'default', fontSize: '11.5px' }}>
            {state.order.sites.length > 1 ? 'multi-site' : (state.order.sites[0]?.siteId || '—')}
          </div>
        </Field>
      </div>

      {/* Validation strip */}
      {validation.length > 0 && (
        <div style={{ padding: '8px 18px', background: 'rgba(217,119,6,0.06)', borderBottom: '1px solid rgba(217,119,6,0.20)', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px' }}>
          <AlertCircle size={13} color="#B45309" />
          <span style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', color: '#B45309', fontWeight: 500 }}>
            {validation.length} {validation.length === 1 ? 'line' : 'lines'} missing required coding
          </span>
        </div>
      )}

      {/* Site groups — single horizontal scroll wrapper and one column header row
          shared across all sites. This ensures headers appear only once at the
          top and the scrollbar spans the full multi-site table. */}
      <div style={{ flex: 1, overflowY: 'auto', padding: '14px 18px 60px', minHeight: 0 }} className="pf-scroll">
        {state.order.sites.length === 0 && (
          <div style={{
            border: '1.5px dashed #CBD3E0', borderRadius: '8px', padding: '40px 24px',
            textAlign: 'center', background: '#ECEFF5'
          }}>
            <Package size={28} color="#CBD3E0" strokeWidth={1.5} style={{ margin: '0 auto 10px' }} />
            <div style={{ fontSize: '13px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500 }}>No lines yet</div>
            <div style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', color: '#586278', marginTop: '4px' }}>
              Add items from the catalogue on the left, or click below to pick a site.
            </div>
            <button onClick={() => setSitePickerOpen(true)} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ marginTop: '14px' }}>
              <span style={{ display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}><Plus size={11} /> Add a site</span>
            </button>
          </div>
        )}

        {state.order.sites.length > 0 && (() => {
          const cols = showCodingCols
            ? 'minmax(150px,1.3fr) 48px 38px minmax(58px,0.7fr) 38px minmax(64px,0.8fr) minmax(64px,0.8fr) minmax(110px,1.1fr) minmax(150px,1.3fr) minmax(135px,1.1fr) 6px minmax(165px,1.4fr) minmax(115px,1fr) minmax(135px,1.1fr) minmax(160px,1.3fr) 56px 24px'
            : 'minmax(180px,2fr) 60px 50px minmax(80px,1fr) 50px minmax(80px,1fr) minmax(80px,1fr) minmax(120px,1.5fr) minmax(150px,1.3fr) minmax(135px,1.1fr) 70px 30px';
          const tableMinWidth = showCodingCols ? 1750 : 1150;
          return (
            <div style={{ border: '1px solid #CBD3E0', borderRadius: '8px', overflow: 'hidden', marginBottom: '14px' }}>
              <div style={{ overflowX: 'auto', overflowY: 'visible' }} className="pf-scroll pf-table-scroll">
                <div style={{ minWidth: `${tableMinWidth}px` }}>
                  {/* Single column header row for all sites */}
                  <div style={{ display: 'grid', gridTemplateColumns: `16px ${cols}`, gap: '6px', padding: '6px 14px', background: '#ECEFF5', borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4', position: 'sticky', top: 0, zIndex: 2 }} className="pf-label">
                    <span />
                    <span className="pf-sticky-cell pf-sticky-cell-header">Item</span>
                    <span style={{ textAlign: 'right' }}>Qty</span>
                    <span>UoM</span>
                    <span style={{ textAlign: 'right' }}>Price</span>
                    <span style={{ textAlign: 'right' }}>VAT</span>
                    <span style={{ textAlign: 'right' }}>Net</span>
                    <span style={{ textAlign: 'right' }}>Gross</span>
                    <span>Supplier</span>
                    <span style={{ color: '#0F7AD8' }}>Site</span>
                    <span style={{ color: '#0F7AD8' }}>LE</span>
                    {showCodingCols && <>
                      <span style={{ borderLeft: '1px solid #CBD3E0', height: '14px' }} />
                      <span style={{ color: '#0F7AD8' }}>Outlet</span>
                      <span style={{ color: '#0F7AD8' }}>Dept</span>
                      <span style={{ color: '#0F7AD8' }}>Cost centre</span>
                      <span style={{ color: '#0F7AD8' }}>GL account</span>
                    </>}
                    <span>Routes as</span>
                    <span />
                  </div>
                  {/* All site groups rendered inside the shared scroll */}
                  {state.order.sites.map(siteEntry => {
                    const site = state.sites.find(s => s.siteId === siteEntry.siteId);
                    return (
                      <SiteGroup
                        key={siteEntry.siteId}
                        site={site}
                        siteEntry={siteEntry}
                        dispatch={dispatch}
                        showCodingCols={showCodingCols}
                        showClusters={showClusters}
                        catalogue={state.catalogue}
                        addCatalogueItem={addCatalogueItem}
                        onAddCustomLine={(seedQuery) => onAddLineSearch(siteEntry.siteId, seedQuery)}
                        onUploadList={() => onUploadList && onUploadList(siteEntry.siteId)}
                        allSites={state.sites}
                        userAssignedSites={state.user.assignedSites}
                        cols={cols}
                      />
                    );
                  })}
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          );
        })()}

        {state.order.sites.length > 0 && availableSitesToAdd.length > 0 && (
          <div style={{ marginTop: '12px' }}>
            <button onClick={() => setSitePickerOpen(true)} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ width: '100%', borderStyle: 'dashed', padding: '9px' }}>
              <span style={{ display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '6px' }}><Plus size={11} /> Add another site</span>
            </button>
          </div>
        )}

        {sitePickerOpen && (
          <div className="pf-fade-in" style={{ marginTop: '8px', border: '1px solid #CBD3E0', borderRadius: '6px', background: '#FFFFFF', boxShadow: '0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08)' }}>
            <div style={{ padding: '8px 12px', borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4', display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'space-between', alignItems: 'center' }}>
              <span className="pf-label">Pick a site</span>
              <X size={13} color="#8892A6" style={{ cursor: 'pointer' }} onClick={() => setSitePickerOpen(false)} />
            </div>
            {availableSitesToAdd.map(s => (
              <div key={s.siteId} onClick={() => { onAddSite(s.siteId); setSitePickerOpen(false); }}
                className="pf-row-hover"
                style={{ padding: '10px 12px', borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4', cursor: 'pointer' }}>
                <div style={{ fontSize: '12.5px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500 }}>{s.name}</div>
                <div className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#586278', marginTop: '1px' }}>{s.siteId} · {s.legalEntity}</div>
              </div>
            ))}
            {availableSitesToAdd.length === 0 && (
              <div style={{ padding: '10px 12px', fontSize: '11.5px', color: '#8892A6' }}>All assigned sites are already on the order.</div>
            )}
          </div>
        )}
      </div>
    </main>
  );
}

function Field({ label, children }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <div className="pf-label" style={{ marginBottom: '4px' }}>{label}</div>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}

/* =====================================================
   SITE GROUP
   ===================================================== */
function SiteGroup({ site, siteEntry, dispatch, showCodingCols, showClusters, catalogue, addCatalogueItem, onAddCustomLine, onUploadList, allSites, userAssignedSites, cols }) {
  const totalNet = siteEntry.lines.reduce((s, l) => s + (l.issuesAs === 'RFQ' ? 0 : l.qty * l.price), 0);
  const reqCount = siteEntry.lines.filter(l => l.issuesAs === 'REQ').length;
  const rfqCount = siteEntry.lines.filter(l => l.issuesAs === 'RFQ').length;
  const [pickerOpen, setPickerOpen] = useState(false);
  const [pickerQuery, setPickerQuery] = useState('');

  // Filter catalogue by the live search query. Show all when empty (max 8 to keep the
  // picker compact); typing narrows it.
  const pickerResults = (() => {
    if (!catalogue) return [];
    const q = pickerQuery.trim().toLowerCase();
    const filtered = !q ? catalogue : catalogue.filter(p =>
      p.name.toLowerCase().includes(q) ||
      p.sku.toLowerCase().includes(q) ||
      p.supplier.toLowerCase().includes(q)
    );
    return filtered.slice(0, 8);
  })();

  return (
    <div className="pf-slide-up" style={{ marginBottom: '2px', borderLeft: '1px solid #CBD3E0', borderRight: '1px solid #CBD3E0', background: '#FFFFFF' }}>
      {/* Group header — entire header is clickable to collapse/expand. */}
      <div
        onClick={() => dispatch({ type: 'TOGGLE_SITE_COLLAPSE', siteId: site.siteId })}
        style={{
          padding: '10px 14px', background: '#F4F7FC', borderBottom: siteEntry.collapsed ? '1px solid transparent' : '1px solid #CBD3E0',
          display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '10px', cursor: 'pointer', userSelect: 'none'
        }}
        title={siteEntry.collapsed ? 'Click to expand this site' : 'Click to collapse this site'}
      >
        <span style={{ display: 'flex' }}>
          {siteEntry.collapsed ? <ChevronRight size={14} color="#586278" /> : <ChevronDown size={14} color="#586278" />}
        </span>
        <Building2 size={13} color="#0F7AD8" />
        <span className="pf-display" style={{ fontSize: '13.5px', fontWeight: 600, color: '#0D1424' }}>{site.name}</span>
        <span className="pf-mono-tag">{site.siteId}</span>
        <span className="pf-mono-tag">{site.legalEntity}</span>
        <div style={{ flex: 1 }} />
        <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#586278' }}>
          {siteEntry.lines.length} lines · <span style={{ color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 600 }}>{gbp(totalNet)} net</span>
        </span>
        <X
          size={13}
          color="#8892A6"
          style={{ cursor: 'pointer' }}
          onClick={e => { e.stopPropagation(); dispatch({ type: 'REMOVE_SITE_GROUP', siteId: site.siteId }); }}
        />
      </div>

      {!siteEntry.collapsed && (
        <>
          {/* Lines table — clustered by coding signature */}
          <LinesTable
            site={site}
            siteEntry={siteEntry}
            dispatch={dispatch}
            showCodingCols={showCodingCols}
            showClusters={showClusters}
            cols={cols}
            allSites={allSites}
            userAssignedSites={userAssignedSites}
          />

          {/* Footer — collapsed button OR open inline picker */}
          {!pickerOpen ? (
            <div style={{ padding: '8px 14px', borderTop: '1px solid #E8ECF4', background: '#ECEFF5' }}>
              <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '10px', marginBottom: '6px' }}>
                <button onClick={() => setPickerOpen(true)} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ borderStyle: 'dashed', flex: 1, justifyContent: 'flex-start', textAlign: 'left' }}>
                  <span style={{ display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '6px' }}>
                    <Plus size={11} /> Add line — pick from catalogue or add custom…
                  </span>
                </button>
                <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9.5px', color: '#586278', letterSpacing: '0.06em' }}>
                  ROUTES TO <span style={{ color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 600 }}>{reqCount > 0 ? '1 REQ' : '0 REQ'}</span> · <span style={{ color: '#5a6498', fontWeight: 600 }}>{rfqCount} RFQ</span>
                </span>
              </div>
              <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px' }}>
                <button onClick={onUploadList} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ borderStyle: 'dashed', justifyContent: 'flex-start', textAlign: 'left', padding: '5px 10px' }}>
                  <span style={{ display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '6px' }}>
                    <Upload size={11} /> Upload list
                  </span>
                </button>
              </div>
            </div>
          ) : (
            <InlineCataloguePicker
              site={site}
              query={pickerQuery}
              setQuery={setPickerQuery}
              results={pickerResults}
              onPick={(productId, outletId) => {
                addCatalogueItem(productId, site.siteId, 1, outletId);
                // Keep picker open so the user can add multiple lines in one pass.
                setPickerQuery('');
              }}
              onAddCustom={(seedQuery) => { setPickerOpen(false); onAddCustomLine(seedQuery); }}
              onClose={() => { setPickerOpen(false); setPickerQuery(''); }}
            />
          )}
        </>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}

/* Inline picker — opens inside a site card when the user clicks "Add line".
   Lets the user manually choose from the catalogue without involving the agent.
   The Outlet selector at the top determines which business-area cluster the line
   lands in — the picker can be used to add to multiple outlets in one session
   (change outlet → add a few more → change outlet → etc). */
function InlineCataloguePicker({ site, query, setQuery, results, onPick, onAddCustom, onClose }) {
  // Default to the site's "general" / default outlet — matches what the area master
  // would have produced before this picker existed.
  const defaultOutletId = site?.defaults?.outlet || site?.outlets?.[0]?.outletId || '';
  const [outletId, setOutletId] = useState(defaultOutletId);
  const outlets = site?.outlets || [];
  const selectedOutlet = outlets.find(o => o.outletId === outletId);
  const targetCluster = selectedOutlet
    ? `${selectedOutlet.name} · ${ccNameOf(selectedOutlet.cc)} · GL ${selectedOutlet.defaultGL}`
    : 'Site default coding';

  return (
    <div style={{ borderTop: '1px solid #E8ECF4', background: '#ECEFF5' }}>
      {/* Outlet selector — determines which business-area cluster the next add lands in */}
      <div style={{
        padding: '8px 14px', borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4',
        display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '10px', flexWrap: 'wrap',
        background: 'linear-gradient(180deg, #F4F7FC 0%, #ECEFF5 100%)'
      }}>
        <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9.5px', color: '#586278', letterSpacing: '0.06em' }}>
          ADD TO
        </span>
        <select
          value={outletId}
          onChange={(e) => setOutletId(e.target.value)}
          className="pf-input"
          style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', padding: '4px 8px', minWidth: '180px' }}
        >
          {outlets.map(o => (
            <option key={o.outletId} value={o.outletId}>{o.name}</option>
          ))}
        </select>
        <span style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#8892A6' }}>
          → cluster: <span style={{ color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500 }}>{targetCluster}</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <div style={{ padding: '10px 14px 8px', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px' }}>
        <div style={{ position: 'relative', flex: 1 }}>
          <Search size={12} style={{ position: 'absolute', left: '8px', top: '50%', transform: 'translateY(-50%)', color: '#8892A6' }} />
          <input
            type="text"
            autoFocus
            placeholder="Search catalogue — name, SKU, supplier…"
            value={query}
            onChange={e => setQuery(e.target.value)}
            className="pf-input"
            style={{ paddingLeft: '26px', fontSize: '11.5px' }}
          />
        </div>
        <button onClick={onClose} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', padding: '4px 10px' }}>
          <span style={{ display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}>
            <X size={10} /> Done
          </span>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div style={{ maxHeight: '240px', overflowY: 'auto', background: '#FFFFFF', borderTop: '1px solid #E8ECF4' }} className="pf-scroll">
        {results.length === 0 ? (
          <div style={{ padding: '18px 14px', display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', alignItems: 'center', gap: '10px' }}>
            <div style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', color: '#8892A6', textAlign: 'center' }}>
              {query.trim()
                ? <>No catalogue items match <span className="pf-mono" style={{ color: '#586278' }}>"{query}"</span>.</>
                : <>Catalogue is empty for the current filters.</>}
            </div>
            {query.trim() && (
              <button
                onClick={() => onAddCustom(query.trim())}
                className="pf-btn-primary"
                style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', padding: '7px 14px', display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '6px' }}
                title={`Create "${query.trim()}" as a new ad-hoc product`}
              >
                <Plus size={12} /> Create &ldquo;{query.trim()}&rdquo; as new product
              </button>
            )}
            <span style={{ fontSize: '10px', color: '#8892A6', textAlign: 'center', maxWidth: '320px', lineHeight: 1.5 }}>
              A new product is added as AD-HOC. You'll pick a supplier in the wizard;
              pricing comes from the RFQ quote that the supplier returns.
            </span>
          </div>
        ) : (
          results.map(p => (
            <div
              key={p.id}
              className="pf-row-hover"
              onClick={() => onPick(p.id, outletId)}
              style={{
                display: 'grid',
                gridTemplateColumns: 'minmax(0,1.8fr) minmax(0,1.2fr) 70px 60px 60px 24px',
                gap: '10px', padding: '7px 14px', borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4',
                alignItems: 'center', cursor: 'pointer', fontSize: '11.5px'
              }}
            >
              <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', minWidth: 0 }}>
                <span style={{ color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500, overflow: 'hidden', textOverflow: 'ellipsis', whiteSpace: 'nowrap' }}>{p.name}</span>
                <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9.5px', color: '#8892A6' }}>{p.sku}</span>
              </div>
              <span style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#586278', overflow: 'hidden', textOverflow: 'ellipsis', whiteSpace: 'nowrap' }}>{p.supplier}</span>
              <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#586278', textAlign: 'right' }}>{gbp(p.price)}</span>
              <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#8892A6' }}>{p.uom}</span>
              <span className="pf-chip pf-chip-mut" style={{ fontSize: '9px' }}>{p.category}</span>
              <Plus size={12} color="#0F7AD8" />
            </div>
          ))
        )}
      </div>
      <div style={{ padding: '8px 14px', borderTop: '1px solid #E8ECF4', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'space-between', gap: '10px', flexWrap: 'wrap' }}>
        <span style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#8892A6' }}>
          Click an item to add it to <span style={{ color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500 }}>{selectedOutlet?.name || 'this site'}</span>.
        </span>
        <button onClick={() => onAddCustom(query.trim() || '')} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', padding: '4px 10px' }}>
          <span style={{ display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}>
            <Plus size={10} /> Create new product
          </span>
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

/* =====================================================
   AREA MASTER PANEL
   ===================================================== */
function AreaMasterPanel({ site, siteEntry, dispatch }) {
  const am = siteEntry.areaMaster;
  const linesCount = siteEntry.lines.length;
  const outletOptions = (site?.outlets || []).map(o => ({
    value: o.outletId,
    label: o.isDefault ? `${o.name} · default` : o.name
  }));
  const ccOptions = COST_CENTRES.map(c => ({ value: c.code, label: c.name }));
  const glOptions = CHART_OF_ACCOUNTS
    .filter(g => !['2100', '2090', '1700', '1020'].includes(g.glCode))  // hide pure-BS / transit accounts from manual pick
    .map(g => ({ value: g.glCode, label: `${g.glCode} · ${g.name}` }));
  const deptOptions = [
    { value: 'F&B',   label: 'Food & Beverage' },
    { value: 'Rooms', label: 'Rooms' },
    { value: 'Eng',   label: 'Engineering' },
    { value: 'G&A',   label: 'General & Admin' }
  ];

  if (siteEntry.areaMasterCollapsed) {
    return (
      <div style={{ padding: '10px 14px', borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px', background: '#ECEFF5' }}>
        <ChevronRight size={12} color="#586278" style={{ cursor: 'pointer' }} onClick={() => dispatch({ type: 'TOGGLE_AM_COLLAPSE', siteId: siteEntry.siteId })} />
        <span className="pf-label">Area master</span>
        <span style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#0D1424' }}>
          {am.legalEntity} · {outletNameOf(am.outlet, site ? [site] : [])} · {deptLabelOf(am.departments[0])} · {ccNameOf(am.costCentre)} · <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10.5px' }}>{glLabelOf(am.glAccount)}</span>
        </span>
        <span className="pf-chip pf-chip-mut" style={{ marginLeft: 'auto' }}>Inherits to {linesCount} {linesCount === 1 ? 'line' : 'lines'}</span>
      </div>
    );
  }
  return (
    <div style={{ padding: '12px 14px', borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4', background: '#ECEFF5' }}>
      <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px', marginBottom: '10px' }}>
        <ChevronDown size={12} color="#586278" style={{ cursor: 'pointer' }} onClick={() => dispatch({ type: 'TOGGLE_AM_COLLAPSE', siteId: siteEntry.siteId })} />
        <span className="pf-label">Area master</span>
        <span className="pf-chip pf-chip-warn"><Edit3 size={9} /> Editable · Finance / Procurement role</span>
        <span className="pf-chip pf-chip-mut">Inherits to {linesCount} {linesCount === 1 ? 'line' : 'lines'} · override per row</span>
      </div>
      <div style={{ display: 'grid', gridTemplateColumns: 'repeat(5, 1fr)', gap: '10px' }}>
        <AmField label="Legal entity" value={am.legalEntity} onChange={(v) => dispatch({ type: 'UPDATE_AREA_MASTER', siteId: siteEntry.siteId, patch: { legalEntity: v } })} />
        <AmSelect label="Outlet"      value={am.outlet}          options={outletOptions} onChange={(v) => dispatch({ type: 'UPDATE_AREA_MASTER', siteId: siteEntry.siteId, patch: { outlet: v } })} />
        <AmSelect label="Department"  value={am.departments[0]}  options={deptOptions}   onChange={(v) => dispatch({ type: 'UPDATE_AREA_MASTER', siteId: siteEntry.siteId, patch: { departments: [v] } })} />
        <AmSelect label="Cost centre" value={am.costCentre}      options={ccOptions}     onChange={(v) => dispatch({ type: 'UPDATE_AREA_MASTER', siteId: siteEntry.siteId, patch: { costCentre: v } })} />
        <AmSelect label="GL account"  value={am.glAccount}       options={glOptions}     onChange={(v) => dispatch({ type: 'UPDATE_AREA_MASTER', siteId: siteEntry.siteId, patch: { glAccount: v } })} />
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

function AmField({ label, value, onChange, mono }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <div className="pf-label" style={{ marginBottom: '4px' }}>{label}</div>
      <input
        type="text"
        value={value}
        onChange={e => onChange(e.target.value)}
        className={`pf-input ${mono ? 'pf-mono' : ''}`}
        style={{ fontSize: '11px', background: '#FFFFFF' }}
      />
    </div>
  );
}

/* Dropdown selector — stores codes, displays human-readable labels.
   options: [{ value, label, sublabel? }, ...] */
function AmSelect({ label, value, options, onChange, placeholder }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <div className="pf-label" style={{ marginBottom: '4px' }}>{label}</div>
      <div style={{ position: 'relative' }}>
        <select
          value={value || ''}
          onChange={e => onChange(e.target.value)}
          className="pf-input"
          style={{ fontSize: '11px', background: '#FFFFFF', appearance: 'none', paddingRight: '22px', cursor: 'pointer' }}
        >
          {placeholder && <option value="">{placeholder}</option>}
          {options.map(opt => (
            <option key={opt.value} value={opt.value}>{opt.label}</option>
          ))}
        </select>
        <ChevronDown size={11} color="#8892A6" style={{ position: 'absolute', right: '7px', top: '50%', transform: 'translateY(-50%)', pointerEvents: 'none' }} />
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

/* InlineSelect — for editing coding directly inside a data-table cell.
   Renders as a soft-bordered dropdown that reads as a form field, but stays compact.
   Hover/focus deepens the contrast to signal interactivity. */
function InlineSelect({ value, options, onChange, mono, danger, title }) {
  const matched = options.find(o => o.value === value);
  const displayLabel = matched ? matched.label : (value || '—');
  const isEmpty = !value;
  return (
    <div
      style={{ position: 'relative', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', minWidth: 0 }}
      onClick={e => e.stopPropagation()}
      title={title || displayLabel}
    >
      <select
        value={value || ''}
        onChange={e => onChange(e.target.value)}
        className={mono ? 'pf-mono pf-inline-select' : 'pf-inline-select'}
        style={{
          fontSize: '10.5px',
          color: danger || isEmpty ? '#B33A1F' : '#0D1424',
          background: danger || isEmpty ? 'rgba(179,58,31,0.04)' : '#FFFFFF',
          border: `1px solid ${danger || isEmpty ? '#E8C9C0' : '#DFE4EE'}`,
          borderRadius: '3px',
          padding: '3px 16px 3px 6px',
          appearance: 'none',
          cursor: 'pointer',
          width: '100%',
          minWidth: 0,
          overflow: 'hidden',
          textOverflow: 'ellipsis',
          whiteSpace: 'nowrap',
          fontWeight: 500
        }}
      >
        {(!matched || isEmpty) && <option value={value || ''}>{displayLabel}</option>}
        {options.map(opt => (
          <option key={opt.value} value={opt.value}>{opt.label}</option>
        ))}
      </select>
      <ChevronDown size={9} color="#8892A6" style={{ position: 'absolute', right: '4px', pointerEvents: 'none' }} />
    </div>
  );
}

/* Cluster key — operational coding signature within a site (Outlet × Dept × CC × GL × LE).
   Used to group lines into business-area clusters. */
const clusterKeyOf = (coding) => {
  return `${coding.legalEntity || '_'}|${coding.outlet || '_'}|${coding.dept || '_'}|${coding.costCentre || '_'}|${coding.glAccount || '_'}`;
};

/* =====================================================
   LINES TABLE — clustered by business-area coding
   ===================================================== */
function LinesTable({ site, siteEntry, dispatch, showCodingCols, showClusters, cols, allSites, userAssignedSites }) {
  // Column template received from parent (shared across all sites).
  // Sites the user can move a line to (only their permitted sites)
  const permittedSites = useMemo(
    () => (allSites || []).filter(s => (userAssignedSites || []).includes(s.siteId)),
    [allSites, userAssignedSites]
  );

  // Cluster lines by the operational coding signature.
  const clusters = (() => {
    const map = new Map();
    siteEntry.lines.forEach(line => {
      const key = clusterKeyOf(line.coding);
      if (!map.has(key)) map.set(key, { key, coding: line.coding, lines: [] });
      map.get(key).lines.push(line);
    });
    return Array.from(map.values());
  })();

  if (siteEntry.lines.length === 0) {
    return (
      <div style={{ padding: '16px 14px', textAlign: 'center', fontSize: '11.5px', color: '#8892A6' }}>
        No lines yet for this site.
      </div>
    );
  }

  return (
    <>
      {clusters.map((cluster, idx) => (
        <React.Fragment key={cluster.key}>
          {showClusters && <ClusterHeader cluster={cluster} site={site} idx={idx} />}
          {cluster.lines.map(line => (
            <LineRow
              key={line.lineId}
              line={line}
              site={site}
              siteId={siteEntry.siteId}
              areaMaster={siteEntry.areaMaster}
              dispatch={dispatch}
              showCodingCols={showCodingCols}
              cols={cols}
              permittedSites={permittedSites}
              allSites={allSites}
            />
          ))}
        </React.Fragment>
      ))}
    </>
  );
}

/* Cluster header — shows the business-area signature + line count + subtotal */
function ClusterHeader({ cluster, site, idx }) {
  const lineCount = cluster.lines.length;
  const subtotalNet = cluster.lines.reduce((s, l) => s + (l.issuesAs === 'RFQ' ? 0 : l.qty * l.price), 0);
  const rfqCount = cluster.lines.filter(l => l.issuesAs === 'RFQ').length;
  // Track lines missing a supplier so the cluster header can hint at incomplete data.
  const supplierMissingCount = cluster.lines.filter(l => !l.supplier).length;

  const outletLbl = outletNameOf(cluster.coding.outlet, site ? [site] : []);
  const deptLbl = deptLabelOf(cluster.coding.dept);
  const ccLbl = ccNameOf(cluster.coding.costCentre);
  const glLbl = glLabelOf(cluster.coding.glAccount);

  return (
    <div className="pf-cluster-band" style={{
      padding: '7px 14px', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px',
      borderTop: idx === 0 ? '1px solid #E8ECF4' : '1px solid #CBD3E0'
    }}>
      <div style={{ position: 'sticky', left: '14px', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px', zIndex: 1 }}>
        <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9.5px', color: '#586278', letterSpacing: '0.08em', textTransform: 'uppercase' }}>
          Cluster {idx + 1}
        </span>
        <span style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500, display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '6px', flexWrap: 'wrap' }}>
          <span>{outletLbl}</span>
          <span style={{ color: '#8892A6' }}>·</span>
          <span style={{ color: '#586278', fontWeight: 400 }}>{deptLbl}</span>
          <span style={{ color: '#8892A6' }}>·</span>
          <span style={{ color: '#586278', fontWeight: 400 }}>{ccLbl}</span>
          <span style={{ color: '#8892A6' }}>·</span>
          <span className="pf-mono" style={{ color: '#586278', fontWeight: 400, fontSize: '10.5px' }}>{glLbl}</span>
        </span>
      </div>
      <span style={{ flex: 1 }} />
      <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#586278' }}>
        {lineCount} {lineCount === 1 ? 'line' : 'lines'}
        {rfqCount > 0 && <span style={{ color: '#5a6498', marginLeft: '6px' }}>· {rfqCount} RFQ</span>}
        {supplierMissingCount > 0 && <span style={{ color: '#B33A1F', marginLeft: '6px' }}>· {supplierMissingCount} need supplier</span>}
      </span>
      <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500, minWidth: '70px', textAlign: 'right' }}>
        {gbp(subtotalNet)}
      </span>
    </div>
  );
}

/* =====================================================
   LINE ROW
   ===================================================== */
function LineRow({ line, site, siteId, areaMaster, dispatch, showCodingCols, cols, permittedSites, allSites }) {
  const [expanded, setExpanded] = useState(false);
  const [menuOpen, setMenuOpen] = useState(false);
  const net = line.qty * line.price;
  const gross = net * (1 + line.vat / 100);
  const showSuggestion = line.agentSuggestion && line.agentSuggestionStatus === 'pending';
  const isRfq = line.issuesAs === 'RFQ';

  // Site options — every site the user can access. Changing site MOVES the line
  // to that group via MOVE_LINE_TO_SITE; LE auto-resolves from the new site.
  const siteOptions = (permittedSites || []).map(s => ({ value: s.siteId, label: s.name }));

  // LE options — the union of LEs across permitted sites. Picking an LE without
  // changing site is a no-op for grouping; the user must also pick a matching
  // site. We expose it as selectable for visibility, but the canonical pick is Site.
  const leOptions = (() => {
    const seen = new Set();
    const out = [];
    (permittedSites || []).forEach(s => {
      if (!seen.has(s.legalEntity)) { seen.add(s.legalEntity); out.push({ value: s.legalEntity, label: s.legalEntity }); }
    });
    return out;
  })();

  return (
    <div className="pf-fade-in"
      draggable
      onDragStart={e => {
        e.dataTransfer.setData('text/plain', JSON.stringify({ lineId: line.lineId, fromSiteId: siteId }));
        e.currentTarget.style.opacity = '0.45';
      }}
      onDragEnd={e => { e.currentTarget.style.opacity = '1'; }}
    >
      <div className="pf-row-hover"
        style={{
          display: 'grid', gridTemplateColumns: `16px ${cols}`, gap: '6px', padding: '8px 14px',
          alignItems: 'center', borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4', cursor: 'pointer',
          fontSize: '11.5px',
          background: showSuggestion ? 'rgba(15,122,216,0.03)' : '#FFFFFF'
        }}
        onClick={() => setExpanded(v => !v)}
      >
        {/* Drag handle */}
        <MoreHorizontal size={11} color="#CBD3E0" style={{ cursor: 'grab', flexShrink: 0 }} onClick={e => e.stopPropagation()} />
        <div className="pf-sticky-cell pf-sticky-cell-row" style={{ padding: '2px 8px 2px 0', marginLeft: '-14px', paddingLeft: '14px', background: showSuggestion ? 'rgba(15,122,216,0.03)' : '#FFFFFF' }}>
          <div style={{ fontSize: '12px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500, lineHeight: 1.3, display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px' }}>
            {line.name}
            {line.agentPopulated && (
              <Sparkles size={10} color="#0F7AD8" style={{ opacity: 0.7 }} title="Agent-populated · adjust inline if needed" />
            )}
          </div>
          <div className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9.5px', color: '#8892A6', marginTop: '1px' }}>
            {line.sku}{line.isCustom ? ' · CUSTOM' : ''}{line.agentPopulated ? ' · AGENT' : ''}
          </div>
        </div>
        <input type="number" value={line.qty} min="1"
          onClick={e => e.stopPropagation()}
          onChange={e => dispatch({ type: 'UPDATE_LINE', siteId, lineId: line.lineId, patch: { qty: Math.max(1, parseInt(e.target.value) || 1) } })}
          className="pf-input pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '11px', textAlign: 'right', padding: '3px 6px' }} />
        <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#586278' }}>{line.uom}</span>
        <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '11px', textAlign: 'right', color: isRfq ? '#8892A6' : '#0D1424' }}>{isRfq ? '—' : gbp(line.price)}</span>
        <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', textAlign: 'right', color: '#586278' }}>{line.vat}%</span>
        <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '11px', textAlign: 'right', color: isRfq ? '#8892A6' : '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500 }}>{isRfq ? '—' : gbp(net)}</span>
        <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '11px', textAlign: 'right', color: isRfq ? '#8892A6' : '#0D1424' }}>{isRfq ? '—' : gbp(gross)}</span>
        <InlineSelect
          value={line.supplier || ''}
          options={SUPPLIERS.map(s => ({ value: s.name, label: s.name }))}
          onChange={v => dispatch({ type: 'UPDATE_LINE', siteId, lineId: line.lineId, patch: { supplier: v } })}
          title={line.supplier || 'Pick a supplier'}
          danger={!line.supplier}
        />
        {/* Site — always visible. Changing it MOVES the line to the target site group. */}
        <InlineSelect
          value={siteId}
          options={siteOptions}
          onChange={v => dispatch({ type: 'MOVE_LINE_TO_SITE', sourceSiteId: siteId, lineId: line.lineId, targetSiteId: v })}
          title={`${site?.name || siteId} — change to move line to another site`}
        />
        {/* LE — always visible. Display-only for now: LE follows Site 1:1, so it
            is derived. Changing LE here resets it but the canonical pick is Site. */}
        <InlineSelect
          value={line.coding.legalEntity || ''}
          options={leOptions}
          onChange={v => dispatch({ type: 'UPDATE_LINE_CODING', siteId, lineId: line.lineId, codingPatch: { legalEntity: v } })}
          title={line.coding.legalEntity || 'unassigned · derived from Site'}
          danger={!line.coding.legalEntity}
        />
        {showCodingCols && <>
          <span style={{ borderLeft: '1px solid #DFE4EE', height: '20px' }} />
          <InlineSelect
            value={line.coding.outlet || ''}
            options={(site?.outlets || []).map(o => ({ value: o.outletId, label: o.isDefault ? `${o.name} · default` : o.name }))}
            onChange={v => {
              // Picking an outlet auto-derives dept/CC/GL from that outlet record — the user
              // can then override individual cells. This makes the data table feel "smart"
              // when the user reorganises lines into business-area clusters.
              const o = (site?.outlets || []).find(x => x.outletId === v);
              const patch = o ? { outlet: v, dept: o.dept, costCentre: o.cc, glAccount: o.defaultGL } : { outlet: v };
              dispatch({ type: 'UPDATE_LINE_CODING', siteId, lineId: line.lineId, codingPatch: patch });
            }}
            title={`${outletNameOf(line.coding.outlet, site ? [site] : [])} · ${line.coding.outlet || 'unassigned'}`}
            danger={!line.coding.outlet}
          />
          {/* Dept / CC / GL all route through reconcileCodingPatch — single helper
              that walks the linkage and fills any field with exactly one candidate,
              blanks anything ambiguous. The cell-level onChange just states intent. */}
          <InlineSelect
            value={line.coding.dept || ''}
            options={DEPARTMENTS.map(d => ({ value: d.code, label: d.name }))}
            onChange={v => {
              const patch = reconcileCodingPatch(line.coding, { dept: v });
              dispatch({ type: 'UPDATE_LINE_CODING', siteId, lineId: line.lineId, codingPatch: patch });
            }}
            danger={!line.coding.dept}
          />
          <InlineSelect
            value={line.coding.costCentre || ''}
            options={ccsForDept(line.coding.dept).map(c => ({
              value: c.code,
              label: line.coding.dept ? c.name : `${c.name} · ${deptLabelOf(c.dept)}`
            }))}
            onChange={v => {
              const patch = reconcileCodingPatch(line.coding, { costCentre: v });
              dispatch({ type: 'UPDATE_LINE_CODING', siteId, lineId: line.lineId, codingPatch: patch });
            }}
            title={`${ccNameOf(line.coding.costCentre)} · ${line.coding.costCentre || 'unassigned'}`}
            danger={!line.coding.costCentre}
          />
          <InlineSelect
            value={line.coding.glAccount || ''}
            options={glsForCC(line.coding.costCentre)
              .filter(g => !['2100','2090','1700','1020'].includes(g.glCode))
              .map(g => ({ value: g.glCode, label: `${g.glCode} · ${g.name}` }))}
            onChange={v => {
              const patch = reconcileCodingPatch(line.coding, { glAccount: v });
              dispatch({ type: 'UPDATE_LINE_CODING', siteId, lineId: line.lineId, codingPatch: patch });
            }}
            mono
            title={glLabelOf(line.coding.glAccount)}
            danger={!line.coding.glAccount}
          />
        </>}
        <span className={`pf-chip ${isRfq ? 'pf-chip-plum' : 'pf-chip-accent'}`}>{line.issuesAs}</span>
        {/* Coding validity indicator — only renders when the Dept↔CC↔GL linkage
            check fails. This surfaces agent-populated lines whose coding is
            internally inconsistent (the cascading inline edits below prevent
            the user from creating an invalid state manually). Hidden when the
            line is fine, so it doesn't clutter the default view. */}
        {(() => {
          const v = validateCoding({
            department: line.coding.dept,
            costCentre: line.coding.costCentre,
            glAccount: line.coding.glAccount
          });
          if (v.ok || v.reason === 'incomplete') return null;
          return (
            <span
              title={v.detail}
              style={{
                display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '3px',
                padding: '2px 6px', borderRadius: '3px',
                background: 'rgba(179,58,31,0.08)', border: '1px solid rgba(179,58,31,0.35)',
                color: '#B33A1F', fontSize: '9.5px', letterSpacing: '0.06em'
              }}
              className="pf-mono"
            >
              <AlertCircle size={9} /> CODING
            </span>
          );
        })()}
        <div style={{ position: 'relative', display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'flex-end' }} onClick={e => e.stopPropagation()}>
          <MoreHorizontal size={14} color="#8892A6" style={{ cursor: 'pointer' }} onClick={() => setMenuOpen(v => !v)} />
          {menuOpen && (
            <div style={{ position: 'absolute', right: 0, top: '18px', background: 'white', border: '1px solid #CBD3E0', borderRadius: '5px', boxShadow: '0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.10)', minWidth: '140px', zIndex: 10, padding: '4px 0' }} className="pf-fade-in">
              <MenuItem icon={Copy} label="Duplicate" onClick={() => { dispatch({ type: 'DUPLICATE_LINE', siteId, lineId: line.lineId }); setMenuOpen(false); }} />
              <MenuItem icon={Trash2} label="Delete" onClick={() => { dispatch({ type: 'REMOVE_LINE', siteId, lineId: line.lineId }); setMenuOpen(false); }} danger />
            </div>
          )}
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Ghost-suggestion row */}
      {showSuggestion && (
        <div className="pf-fade-in" style={{
          padding: '8px 14px 10px', background: 'rgba(15,122,216,0.04)',
          borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '10px'
        }}>
          <Sparkles size={13} color="#0F7AD8" />
          <div style={{ flex: 1 }}>
            <div style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500 }}>Agent suggestion · confidence {line.agentSuggestion.confidence}</div>
            <div style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#586278', marginTop: '1px' }}>{line.agentSuggestion.reasoning}</div>
          </div>
          <button className="pf-btn-primary" style={{ padding: '4px 10px', fontSize: '10.5px' }}
            onClick={() => dispatch({ type: 'ACCEPT_LINE_SUGGESTION', siteId, lineId: line.lineId })}>
            <span style={{ display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '4px' }}><Check size={10} /> Accept</span>
          </button>
          <button className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ padding: '4px 10px', fontSize: '10.5px' }}
            onClick={() => setExpanded(true)}>
            <span style={{ display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '4px' }}><Edit3 size={10} /> Edit</span>
          </button>
          <button className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ padding: '4px 10px', fontSize: '10.5px' }}
            onClick={() => dispatch({ type: 'DISMISS_LINE_SUGGESTION', siteId, lineId: line.lineId })}>
            <span style={{ display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '4px' }}><X size={10} /> Dismiss</span>
          </button>
        </div>
      )}

      {/* Expanded row — notes only; coding now lives inline on the row itself */}
      {expanded && (
        <div className="pf-fade-in" style={{ padding: '8px 14px 10px', background: '#ECEFF5', borderBottom: '1px solid #E8ECF4', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '10px' }}>
          <span className="pf-label" style={{ whiteSpace: 'nowrap' }}>Notes</span>
          <input type="text" placeholder="Optional notes for this line"
            value={line.notes}
            onChange={e => dispatch({ type: 'UPDATE_LINE', siteId, lineId: line.lineId, patch: { notes: e.target.value } })}
            className="pf-input" style={{ fontSize: '11.5px', flex: 1 }} />
        </div>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}

function MenuItem({ icon: Icon, label, onClick, danger }) {
  return (
    <div onClick={onClick} style={{
      padding: '6px 12px', cursor: 'pointer', fontSize: '11.5px',
      color: danger ? '#B91C1C' : '#0D1424', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '7px'
    }}
      onMouseEnter={e => e.currentTarget.style.background = '#F4F7FC'}
      onMouseLeave={e => e.currentTarget.style.background = 'transparent'}
    >
      <Icon size={12} /> {label}
    </div>
  );
}

/* =====================================================
   ORDER SUMMARY (right sticky)
   ===================================================== */
function OrderSummary({ totals, onSubmit, onSaveDraft, hasLines, validation, onCollapse }) {
  return (
    <aside style={{
      background: '#FFFFFF', border: '1px solid #CBD3E0', borderRadius: '8px',
      display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', alignSelf: 'flex-start',
      position: 'sticky', top: '16px', overflow: 'hidden'
    }}>
      <div style={{ padding: '14px 16px 10px', borderBottom: '1px solid #CBD3E0', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'flex-start', justifyContent: 'space-between', gap: '8px' }}>
        <div>
          <div className="pf-display" style={{ fontSize: '14px', fontWeight: 600, color: '#0D1424' }}>Order summary</div>
          <div className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9.5px', color: '#8892A6', letterSpacing: '0.1em', marginTop: '2px' }}>DRAFT</div>
        </div>
        {onCollapse && (
          <button
            onClick={onCollapse}
            className="pf-btn-ghost"
            style={{ width: '24px', height: '24px', padding: 0, display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center', flexShrink: 0 }}
            title="Collapse order summary"
          >
            <ChevronRight size={12} />
          </button>
        )}
      </div>

      <div style={{ padding: '12px 16px', display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '6px' }}>
        <SumRow label="Sites" value={totals.sites} />
        <SumRow label="Lines" value={totals.lines} />
        <SumRow label="Units" value={totals.units} />
        <SumRow label="Suppliers" value={totals.suppliers} />
        <SumRow label="RFQs to issue" value={totals.rfq} accent={totals.rfq > 0} />
      </div>

      <div style={{ borderTop: '1px solid #E8ECF4', padding: '12px 16px', display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '6px' }}>
        <SumRow label="PO subtotal (net)" value={gbp(totals.net)} mono />
        <SumRow label="VAT" value={gbp(totals.tax)} mono />
        <div style={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'space-between', alignItems: 'baseline', marginTop: '6px', paddingTop: '8px', borderTop: '1px solid #E8ECF4' }}>
          <span style={{ fontSize: '12px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 600 }}>Total (gross)</span>
          <span className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '18px', color: '#0D1424', fontWeight: 700 }}>{gbp(totals.gross)}</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      {totals.rfq > 0 && (
        <div style={{
          margin: '0 16px 12px', padding: '8px 10px',
          background: 'rgba(106,120,173,0.10)', border: '1px solid rgba(106,120,173,0.30)',
          borderRadius: '4px'
        }}>
          <div style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#5a6498', lineHeight: 1.4 }}>
            <span style={{ fontWeight: 600 }}>{totals.rfq} {totals.rfq === 1 ? 'line' : 'lines'} excluded from totals</span>
            <br />pricing populates once RFQ is awarded.
          </div>
        </div>
      )}

      {validation.length > 0 && (
        <div style={{
          margin: '0 16px 12px', padding: '8px 10px',
          background: 'rgba(217,119,6,0.08)', border: '1px solid rgba(217,119,6,0.25)',
          borderRadius: '4px'
        }}>
          <div style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#B45309', lineHeight: 1.4, display: 'flex', alignItems: 'flex-start', gap: '6px' }}>
            <AlertCircle size={11} style={{ flexShrink: 0, marginTop: '1px' }} />
            <span>{validation.length} {validation.length === 1 ? 'line needs' : 'lines need'} coding before submit.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      )}

      <div style={{ padding: '12px 16px', borderTop: '1px solid #E8ECF4', display: 'flex', gap: '8px' }}>
        <button onClick={onSaveDraft} className="pf-btn-ghost" style={{ flex: 1 }}>Save draft</button>
        <button
          onClick={onSubmit}
          disabled={!hasLines || validation.length > 0}
          className="pf-btn-primary"
          style={{ flex: 1 }}
          title={!hasLines ? 'Add lines first' : validation.length > 0 ? 'Resolve coding issues before submit' : 'Open the routing preview'}
        >Submit</button>
      </div>
    </aside>
  );
}

function SumRow({ label, value, mono, accent }) {
  return (
    <div style={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'space-between', alignItems: 'baseline' }}>
      <span style={{ fontSize: '11px', color: '#586278' }}>{label}</span>
      <span className={mono ? 'pf-mono' : ''} style={{ fontSize: mono ? '12px' : '12.5px', color: accent ? '#0F7AD8' : '#0D1424', fontWeight: 500 }}>{value}</span>
    </div>
  );
}

/* =====================================================
   FLOATING AGENT
   ===================================================== */
function FloatingAgent({ state, dispatch, onAcceptProposal, onNavigate }) {
  const [input, setInput] = useState('');
  const [attachments, setAttachments] = useState([]);
  const [fileError, setFileError] = useState(null);
  const fileInputRef = useRef(null);
  const scrollRef = useRef(null);
  const { open, messages, typing, pendingSuggestions } = state.agent;

  useEffect(() => {
    if (scrollRef.current) scrollRef.current.scrollTop = scrollRef.current.scrollHeight;
  }, [messages, typing, open]);

  // File picker — accepts PDFs, images, and text-based files (CSV, TXT).
  // Binary files become base64; text files are kept raw and inlined into the prompt.
  const handleFilePick = async (e) => {
    const files = Array.from(e.target.files || []);
    if (files.length === 0) return;
    setFileError(null);
    const next = [];
    for (const file of files) {
      // 8 MB sanity cap — the API will reject larger payloads anyway
      if (file.size > 8 * 1024 * 1024) {
        setFileError(`${file.name} is over 8 MB — skipped.`);
        continue;
      }
      try {
        const isPdf = file.type === 'application/pdf' || file.name.toLowerCase().endsWith('.pdf');
        const isImage = file.type.startsWith('image/');
        const isText = !isPdf && !isImage;  // csv, txt, json, etc — read as plain text
        const data = await new Promise((res, rej) => {
          const r = new FileReader();
          r.onload = () => res(r.result);
          r.onerror = () => rej(new Error('read failed'));
          if (isText) r.readAsText(file); else r.readAsDataURL(file);
        });
        next.push({
          name: file.name,
          type: file.type || (isPdf ? 'application/pdf' : 'text/plain'),
          kind: isPdf ? 'pdf' : (isImage ? 'image' : 'text'),
          data: isText ? data : String(data).split(',')[1] || '',
          size: file.size
        });
      } catch (err) {
        setFileError(`Couldn't read ${file.name}: ${err.message}`);
      }
    }
    setAttachments(prev => [...prev, ...next]);
    if (fileInputRef.current) fileInputRef.current.value = '';  // allow re-selecting the same file
  };

  const removeAttachment = (idx) => {
    setAttachments(prev => prev.filter((_, i) => i !== idx));
  };

  const sendMessage = async () => {
    const text = input.trim();
    if (!text && attachments.length === 0) return;
    // The displayed user message shows the text + attachment names so the chat carries
    // visual evidence of what was sent.
    const fileTagline = attachments.length > 0
      ? `\n📎 ${attachments.map(a => a.name).join(', ')}`
      : '';
    const displayText = (text || '(file attached)') + fileTagline;
    dispatch({ type: 'AGENT_MESSAGE_ADD', message: { id: uid('MSG'), role: 'user', t: nowIso(), text: displayText } });
    setInput('');
    const sentAttachments = attachments;
    setAttachments([]);
    setFileError(null);
    dispatch({ type: 'AGENT_TYPING', typing: true });
    try {
      const ctx = buildAgentContext(state);

      // Populate-the-canvas schema: agent emits actions, not chat
      const populateSchema = `Respond with ONLY a JSON object with this exact shape (no code fences):
{
  "action": "populate_order",
  "description": "short label, e.g. 'Mayfair restaurant restock'",
  "needBy": "YYYY-MM-DD or null",
  "sites": [
    {
      "siteId": "SITE-...",
      "lines": [
        {
          "sku": "exact SKU from catalogue_skus, or null if ad-hoc",
          "name": "product name",
          "qty": <number>,
          "uom": "kg | cs | box | ea | ...",
          "supplier": "supplier name",
          "price": <number or null if ad-hoc>,
          "vat": 20,
          "coding": {
            "legalEntity": "name from LEGAL_ENTITIES (e.g. 'Mayfair Hotels Ltd')",
            "outlet": "outletId from site.outlets",
            "dept": "F&B | Rooms | Eng | G&A",
            "costCentre": "CC-... code",
            "glAccount": "GL code"
          },
          "treatment": "Direct to P&L | Prepayment | Inventory | CapEx",
          "issuesAs": "REQ | RFQ",
          "isCustom": false
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "blocking_questions": ["only LE / Site / ad-hoc Supplier if unresolved"],
  "reasoning": "one short sentence"
}

Rules: populate ALL non-LE/non-Site dimensions silently from master data. Only emit blocking_questions for LE, Site, or an ad-hoc supplier that needs the user's choice. Always populate every coding dimension. NEVER emit a site object with an empty lines array — if you can't produce lines yet, return sites: [] and put the reason in blocking_questions or reasoning.`;

      // Pass conversation history so a multi-turn reply (e.g. "Edinburgh") still has
      // context for the original ask (e.g. "5 deck chairs"). The newly-added user message
      // hasn't reached state yet (dispatch is async), so state.agent.messages holds prior turns only.
      // FILTER: the Anthropic Messages API only accepts 'user' or 'assistant' roles.
      // Our chat surface also uses 'system' messages as inline status markers — we strip those.
      const priorMessages = (state.agent.messages || [])
        .filter(m => m.role === 'user' || m.role === 'assistant')
        .map(m => ({ role: m.role, content: m.text }));

      const resp = await callAgent(text || 'Process the attached file and populate the order.', ctx, populateSchema, priorMessages, sentAttachments);
      const parsed = tryParseJson(resp);
      dispatch({ type: 'AGENT_TYPING', typing: false });

      if (parsed?.action === 'populate_order') {
        // Blocking questions: ask, do NOT populate
        if (parsed.blocking_questions && parsed.blocking_questions.length > 0) {
          dispatch({ type: 'AGENT_MESSAGE_ADD', message: {
            id: uid('MSG'), role: 'assistant', t: nowIso(),
            text: parsed.blocking_questions.length === 1
              ? parsed.blocking_questions[0]
              : `I need to resolve a few things first:\n· ${parsed.blocking_questions.join('\n· ')}`
          }});
          return;
        }

        // Degenerate response: no blocking question but also no usable lines.
        // Surface the reasoning so the user knows what happened — don't silently dispatch a no-op.
        const proposedLineCount = (parsed.sites || []).reduce((n, s) => n + (s.lines?.length || 0), 0);
        if (proposedLineCount === 0) {
          dispatch({ type: 'AGENT_MESSAGE_ADD', message: {
            id: uid('MSG'), role: 'assistant', t: nowIso(),
            text: parsed.reasoning || "I couldn't produce any lines from that. Could you give me a product and quantity?"
          }});
          return;
        }

        // Populate the canvas then offer a direct jump to it.
        dispatch({ type: 'POPULATE_FROM_AGENT', agentOutput: parsed });

        const lineCount = proposedLineCount;
        dispatch({ type: 'AGENT_MESSAGE_ADD', message: {
          id: uid('MSG'), role: 'assistant', t: nowIso(),
          text: `Populated ${lineCount} line${lineCount === 1 ? '' : 's'} in the canvas. Review and adjust any coding inline.`,
          navAction: { label: 'Go to order canvas →', navId: 'new-order' }
        }});
      } else {
        // Fallback: anything not in populate_order shape, just echo the reasoning or raw text
        dispatch({ type: 'AGENT_MESSAGE_ADD', message: {
          id: uid('MSG'), role: 'assistant', t: nowIso(),
          text: parsed?.reasoning || resp || 'No structured response.'
        }});
      }
    } catch (e) {
      dispatch({ type: 'AGENT_TYPING', typing: false });
      dispatch({ type: 'AGENT_MESSAGE_ADD', message: {
        id: uid('MSG'), role: 'assistant', t: nowIso(),
        text: `Couldn't reach the assistant. ${e?.message || ''} — try again or add lines manually from the catalogue.`
      }});
    }
  };

  // Always render as the side drawer — open state is controlled by TopBar
  return (
    <div className="pf-assistant-drawer">
      {/* Drawer header */}
      <div style={{
        padding: '11px 14px', borderBottom: '1px solid #CBD3E0',
        display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px',
        background: 'linear-gradient(180deg, #ECEFF5, #FFFFFF)', flexShrink: 0
      }}>
        <div style={{ width: '24px', height: '24px', borderRadius: '8px', background: 'linear-gradient(135deg, #0F7AD8, #2A8FD8)', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center', flexShrink: 0 }}>
          <Sparkles size={12} color="white" />
        </div>
        <div style={{ flex: 1 }}>
          <div className="pf-display" style={{ fontSize: '12.5px', fontWeight: 600, color: '#0D1424' }}>P2P Assistant</div>
          <div className="pf-mono" style={{ fontSize: '9px', color: '#8892A6', letterSpacing: '0.1em' }}>AGENT v1 · SOVEREIGN AI</div>
        </div>
        <button onClick={() => dispatch({ type: 'TOGGLE_AGENT', open: false })} style={{ background: 'none', border: 'none', cursor: 'pointer', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', padding: '3px' }} title="Close assistant">
          <X size={14} color="#586278" />
        </button>
      </div>

      <div ref={scrollRef} style={{ flex: 1, overflowY: 'auto', padding: '12px 14px', display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '10px' }} className="pf-scroll">
        {messages.length === 0 && (
          <div style={{ textAlign: 'center', padding: '24px 12px', color: '#8892A6' }}>
            <Sparkles size={20} style={{ margin: '0 auto 8px', color: '#0F7AD8', opacity: 0.6 }} />
            <div style={{ fontSize: '12px', color: '#586278', fontWeight: 500 }}>How can I help with this order?</div>
            <div style={{ fontSize: '11px', marginTop: '4px' }}>
              Ask about coding, supplier matches, or proposed analogues for new items.
            </div>
          </div>
        )}
        {messages.map(m => (
          <MessageBubble key={m.id} message={m} onAcceptProposal={onAcceptProposal} dispatch={dispatch} onNavigate={onNavigate} />
        ))}
        {typing && (
          <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '4px', color: '#8892A6', fontSize: '13px', padding: '4px 10px' }} className="pf-typing">
            <span>●</span><span>●</span><span>●</span>
          </div>
        )}
      </div>

      {pendingSuggestions.length > 0 && (
        <div style={{ padding: '6px 14px', borderTop: '1px solid #E8ECF4', background: 'rgba(15,122,216,0.04)' }}>
          <span className="pf-chip pf-chip-accent">{pendingSuggestions.length} suggestion pending</span>
        </div>
      )}

      {/* Scenario picker — fires canned prompts to exercise each path */}
      <ScenarioPicker onPick={(prompt) => setInput(prompt)} />

      {/* Attachment chips — show what's staged for the next message */}
      {(attachments.length > 0 || fileError) && (
        <div style={{ padding: '6px 12px', borderTop: '1px solid #E8ECF4', background: '#F4F7FC', display: 'flex', flexWrap: 'wrap', gap: '6px', alignItems: 'center' }}>
          {attachments.map((a, i) => (
            <span key={i} style={{
              display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '5px',
              padding: '3px 6px 3px 8px', borderRadius: '12px',
              background: '#FFFFFF', border: '1px solid #CBD3E0', fontSize: '10.5px'
            }}>
              {a.kind === 'image' ? <ImageIcon size={10} color="#0F7AD8" /> :
                a.kind === 'pdf' ? <FileText size={10} color="#B33A1F" /> :
                <File size={10} color="#586278" />}
              <span style={{ color: '#0D1424', maxWidth: '140px', overflow: 'hidden', textOverflow: 'ellipsis', whiteSpace: 'nowrap' }}>{a.name}</span>
              <span className="pf-mono" style={{ color: '#8892A6', fontSize: '9px' }}>
                {a.size < 1024 ? `${a.size}B` : a.size < 1024 * 1024 ? `${Math.round(a.size / 1024)}KB` : `${(a.size / (1024 * 1024)).toFixed(1)}MB`}
              </span>
              <X size={10} color="#8892A6" style={{ cursor: 'pointer' }} onClick={() => removeAttachment(i)} />
            </span>
          ))}
          {fileError && (
            <span style={{ fontSize: '10.5px', color: '#B33A1F' }}>{fileError}</span>
          )}
        </div>
      )}

      <div style={{ padding: '10px 12px', borderTop: '1px solid #CBD3E0', display: 'flex', gap: '6px', background: '#ECEFF5', alignItems: 'center' }}>
        <input
          ref={fileInputRef}
          type="file"
          multiple
          accept=".pdf,.csv,.txt,.json,.tsv,.md,image/*,application/pdf,text/*"
          onChange={handleFilePick}
          style={{ display: 'none' }}
        />
        <button
          onClick={() => fileInputRef.current?.click()}
          className="pf-btn-ghost"
          style={{ padding: '6px 8px', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}
          title="Attach files — PDF, image, CSV, TXT"
        >
          <Paperclip size={12} />
        </button>
        <input
          type="text"
          placeholder={attachments.length > 0 ? "Add instructions for the attached file(s)…" : "Ask the assistant…"}
          value={input}
          onChange={e => setInput(e.target.value)}
          onKeyDown={e => { if (e.key === 'Enter') sendMessage(); }}
          className="pf-input"
          style={{ flex: 1, fontSize: '12px' }}
        />
        <button onClick={sendMessage} disabled={(!input.trim() && attachments.length === 0) || typing} className="pf-btn-primary" style={{ padding: '6px 11px' }}>
          <Send size={12} />
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

